var book = {
	"name": "Genesis",
	"numChapters": 50,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In the beginning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1A\"></sup> God created<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1B\"></sup> the heavens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1C\"></sup> and the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now the earth was formless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2E\"></sup> and empty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2F\"></sup> darkness was over the surface of the deep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2G\"></sup> and the Spirit of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2H\"></sup> was hovering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-2I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-2I\"></sup> over the waters.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And God said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3J\"></sup> “Let there be light,” and there was light.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-3K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-3K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>God saw that the light was good,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-4L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-4L\"></sup> and he separated the light from the darkness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-4M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-4M\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>God called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5N\"></sup> the light “day,” and the darkness he called “night.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5O\"></sup> And there was evening, and there was morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-5P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-5P\"></sup>—the first day.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And God said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6Q\"></sup> “Let there be a vault<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6R\"></sup> between the waters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-6S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-6S\"></sup> to separate water from water.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So God made the vault and separated the water under the vault from the water above it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7T\"></sup> And it was so.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-7U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-7U\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>God called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8V\"></sup> the vault “sky.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8W\"></sup> And there was evening, and there was morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-8X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-8X\"></sup>—the second day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And God said, “Let the water under the sky be gathered to one place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9Y\"></sup> and let dry ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9Z\"></sup> appear.” And it was so.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-9AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-9AA\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>God called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10AB\"></sup> the dry ground “land,” and the gathered waters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10AC\"></sup> he called “seas.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10AD\"></sup> And God saw that it was good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-10AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-10AE\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then God said, “Let the land produce vegetation:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11AF\"></sup> seed-bearing plants and trees on the land that bear fruit with seed in it, according to their various kinds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11AG\"></sup>” And it was so.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11AH\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The land produced vegetation: plants bearing seed according to their kinds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12AI\"></sup> and trees bearing fruit with seed in it according to their kinds. And God saw that it was good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12AJ\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And there was evening, and there was morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-13AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-13AK\"></sup>—the third day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And God said, “Let there be lights<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-14AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-14AL\"></sup> in the vault of the sky to separate the day from the night,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-14AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-14AM\"></sup> and let them serve as signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-14AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-14AN\"></sup> to mark sacred times,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-14AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-14AO\"></sup> and days and years,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-14AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-14AP\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and let them be lights in the vault of the sky to give light on the earth.” And it was so.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-15AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-15AQ\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>God made two great lights—the greater light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-16AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-16AR\"></sup> to govern<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-16AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-16AS\"></sup> the day and the lesser light to govern<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-16AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-16AT\"></sup> the night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-16AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-16AU\"></sup> He also made the stars.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-16AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-16AV\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>God set them in the vault of the sky to give light on the earth,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>to govern the day and the night,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-18AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-18AW\"></sup> and to separate light from darkness. And God saw that it was good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-18AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-18AX\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And there was evening, and there was morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-19AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-19AY\"></sup>—the fourth day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And God said, “Let the water teem with living creatures,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-20AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-20AZ\"></sup> and let birds fly above the earth across the vault of the sky.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-20BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-20BA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So God created<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21BB\"></sup> the great creatures of the sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21BC\"></sup> and every living thing with which the water teems and that moves about in it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21BD\"></sup> according to their kinds, and every winged bird according to its kind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21BE\"></sup> And God saw that it was good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-21BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-21BF\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>God blessed them and said, “Be fruitful and increase in number and fill the water in the seas, and let the birds increase on the earth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-22BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-22BG\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And there was evening, and there was morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-23BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-23BH\"></sup>—the fifth day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And God said, “Let the land produce living creatures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24BI\"></sup> according to their kinds:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24BJ\"></sup> the livestock, the creatures that move along the ground, and the wild animals, each according to its kind.” And it was so.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-24BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-24BK\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>God made the wild animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25BL\"></sup> according to their kinds, the livestock according to their kinds, and all the creatures that move along the ground according to their kinds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25BM\"></sup> And God saw that it was good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-25BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-25BN\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then God said, “Let us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26BO\"></sup> make mankind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26BP\"></sup> in our image,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26BQ\"></sup> in our likeness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26BR\"></sup> so that they may rule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26BS\"></sup> over the fish in the sea and the birds in the sky,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26BT\"></sup> over the livestock and all the wild animals, and over all the creatures that move along the ground.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So God created<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27BU\"></sup> mankind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27BV\"></sup> in his own image,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27BW\"></sup>in the image of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27BX\"></sup> he created them;male and female<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27BY\"></sup> he created them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-27BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-27BZ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>God blessed them and said to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-28CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-28CA\"></sup> “Be fruitful and increase in number;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-28CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-28CB\"></sup> fill the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-28CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-28CC\"></sup> and subdue it. Rule over<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-28CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-28CD\"></sup> the fish in the sea and the birds in the sky and over every living creature that moves on the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-28CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-28CE\"></sup>”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then God said, “I give you every seed-bearing plant on the face of the whole earth and every tree that has fruit with seed in it. They will be yours for food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-29CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-29CF\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And to all the beasts of the earth and all the birds in the sky and all the creatures that move along the ground—everything that has the breath of life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-30CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-30CG\"></sup> in it—I give every green plant for food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-30CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-30CH\"></sup>” And it was so.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>God saw all that he had made,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-31CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-31CI\"></sup> and it was very good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-31CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-31CJ\"></sup> And there was evening, and there was morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-31CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-31CK\"></sup>—the sixth day."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Thus the heavens and the earth were completed in all their vast array.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-32A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-32A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>By the seventh day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-33B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-33B\"></sup> God had finished the work he had been doing; so on the seventh day he rested from all his work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-33C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-33C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then God blessed the seventh day and made it holy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-34D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-34D\"></sup> because on it he rested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-34E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-34E\"></sup> from all the work of creating<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-34F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-34F\"></sup> that he had done.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-35G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-35G\"></sup> of the heavens and the earth when they were created,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-35H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-35H\"></sup> when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made the earth and the heavens.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now no shrub had yet appeared on the earth and no plant had yet sprung up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-36I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-36I\"></sup> for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had not sent rain on the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-36J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-36J\"></sup> and there was no one to work the ground,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but streams came up from the earth and watered the whole surface of the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God formed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38K\"></sup> a man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38L\"></sup> from the dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38M\"></sup> of the ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38N\"></sup> and breathed into his nostrils the breath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38O\"></sup> of life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38P\"></sup> and the man became a living being.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-38Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-38Q\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had planted a garden in the east, in Eden;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-39R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-39R\"></sup> and there he put the man he had formed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made all kinds of trees grow out of the ground—trees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-40S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-40S\"></sup> that were pleasing to the eye and good for food. In the middle of the garden were the tree of life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-40T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-40T\"></sup> and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-40U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-40U\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A river<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-41V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-41V\"></sup> watering the garden flowed from Eden;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-41W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-41W\"></sup> from there it was separated into four headwaters.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The name of the first is the Pishon; it winds through the entire land of Havilah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-42X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-42X\"></sup> where there is gold.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>(The gold of that land is good; aromatic resin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-43Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-43Y\"></sup> and onyx are also there.)",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The name of the second river is the Gihon; it winds through the entire land of Cush.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The name of the third river is the Tigris;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-45Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-45Z\"></sup> it runs along the east side of Ashur. And the fourth river is the Euphrates.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-45AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-45AA\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God took the man and put him in the Garden of Eden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-46AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-46AB\"></sup> to work it and take care of it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God commanded the man, “You are free to eat from any tree in the garden;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-47AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-47AC\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>but you must not eat from the tree of the knowledge of good and evil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-48AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-48AD\"></sup> for when you eat from it you will certainly die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-48AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-48AE\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said, “It is not good for the man to be alone. I will make a helper suitable for him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-49AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-49AF\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had formed out of the ground all the wild animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-50AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-50AG\"></sup> and all the birds in the sky.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-50AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-50AH\"></sup> He brought them to the man to see what he would name them; and whatever the man called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-50AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-50AI\"></sup> each living creature,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-50AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-50AJ\"></sup> that was its name.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So the man gave names to all the livestock, the birds in the sky and all the wild animals.But for Adam no suitable helper<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-51AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-51AK\"></sup> was found.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God caused the man to fall into a deep sleep;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-52AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-52AL\"></sup> and while he was sleeping, he took one of the man’s ribs and then closed up the place with flesh.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made a woman from the rib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-53AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-53AM\"></sup> he had taken out of the man, and he brought her to the man.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The man said,“This is now bone of my bonesand flesh of my flesh;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-54AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-54AN\"></sup>she shall be called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-54AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-54AO\"></sup> ‘woman,’for she was taken out of man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-54AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-54AP\"></sup>”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>That is why a man leaves his father and mother and is united<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-55AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-55AQ\"></sup> to his wife, and they become one flesh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-55AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-55AR\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Adam and his wife were both naked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-56AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-56AS\"></sup> and they felt no shame."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now the serpent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-57A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-57A\"></sup> was more crafty than any of the wild animals the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had made. He said to the woman, “Did God really say, ‘You must not eat from any tree in the garden’?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-57B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-57B\"></sup>”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The woman said to the serpent, “We may eat fruit from the trees in the garden,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-58C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-58C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but God did say, ‘You must not eat fruit from the tree that is in the middle of the garden, and you must not touch it, or you will die.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-59D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-59D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“You will not certainly die,” the serpent said to the woman.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-60E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-60E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“For God knows that when you eat from it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-61F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-61F\"></sup> knowing good and evil.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the woman saw that the fruit of the tree was good for food and pleasing to the eye, and also desirable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-62G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-62G\"></sup> for gaining wisdom, she took some and ate it. She also gave some to her husband,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-62H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-62H\"></sup> who was with her, and he ate it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-62I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-62I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they realized they were naked;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-63J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-63J\"></sup> so they sewed fig leaves together and made coverings for themselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-63K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-63K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the man and his wife heard the sound of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God as he was walking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-64L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-64L\"></sup> in the garden in the cool of the day, and they hid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-64M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-64M\"></sup> from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God among the trees of the garden.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God called to the man, “Where are you?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-65N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-65N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He answered, “I heard you in the garden, and I was afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-66O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-66O\"></sup> because I was naked;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-66P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-66P\"></sup> so I hid.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he said, “Who told you that you were naked?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-67Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-67Q\"></sup> Have you eaten from the tree that I commanded you not to eat from?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-67R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-67R\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The man said, “The woman you put here with me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-68S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-68S\"></sup>—she gave me some fruit from the tree, and I ate it.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said to the woman, “What is this you have done?”The woman said, “The serpent deceived me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-69T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-69T\"></sup> and I ate.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said to the serpent, “Because you have done this,“Cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-70U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-70U\"></sup> are you above all livestockand all wild animals!You will crawl on your bellyand you will eat dust<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-70V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-70V\"></sup>all the days of your life.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And I will put enmitybetween you and the woman,and between your offspring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-71W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-71W\"></sup> and hers;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-71X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-71X\"></sup>he will crush your head,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-71Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-71Y\"></sup>and you will strike his heel.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To the woman he said,“I will make your pains in childbearing very severe;with painful labor you will give birth to children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-72Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-72Z\"></sup>Your desire will be for your husband,and he will rule over you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-72AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-72AA\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>To Adam he said, “Because you listened to your wife and ate fruit from the tree about which I commanded you, ‘You must not eat from it,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-73AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-73AB\"></sup>“Cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-73AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-73AC\"></sup> is the ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-73AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-73AD\"></sup> because of you;through painful toil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-73AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-73AE\"></sup> you will eat food from itall the days of your life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-73AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-73AF\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It will produce thorns and thistles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-74AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-74AG\"></sup> for you,and you will eat the plants of the field.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-74AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-74AH\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>By the sweat of your brow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-75AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-75AI\"></sup>you will eat your food<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-75AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-75AJ\"></sup>until you return to the ground,since from it you were taken;for dust you areand to dust you will return.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-75AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-75AK\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Adam named his wife Eve,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-76AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-76AL\"></sup> because she would become the mother of all the living.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made garments of skin for Adam and his wife and clothed them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-77AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-77AM\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said, “The man has now become like one of us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-78AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-78AN\"></sup> knowing good and evil. He must not be allowed to reach out his hand and take also from the tree of life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-78AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-78AO\"></sup> and eat, and live forever.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God banished him from the Garden of Eden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-79AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-79AP\"></sup> to work the ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-79AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-79AQ\"></sup> from which he had been taken.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After he drove the man out, he placed on the east side of the Garden of Eden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-80AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-80AR\"></sup> cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-80AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-80AS\"></sup> and a flaming sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-80AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-80AT\"></sup> flashing back and forth to guard the way to the tree of life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-80AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-80AU\"></sup>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Adam made love to his wife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-81A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-81A\"></sup> Eve,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-81B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-81B\"></sup> and she became pregnant and gave birth to Cain.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-81C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-81C\"></sup> She said, “With the help of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> I have brought forth a man.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Later she gave birth to his brother Abel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-82D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-82D\"></sup>Now Abel kept flocks, and Cain worked the soil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-82E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-82E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the course of time Cain brought some of the fruits of the soil as an offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-83F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-83F\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-83G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-83G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Abel also brought an offering—fat portions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-84H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-84H\"></sup> from some of the firstborn of his flock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-84I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-84I\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looked with favor on Abel and his offering,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-84J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-84J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>but on Cain and his offering he did not look with favor. So Cain was very angry, and his face was downcast.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Cain, “Why are you angry?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-86K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-86K\"></sup> Why is your face downcast?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If you do what is right, will you not be accepted? But if you do not do what is right, sin is crouching at your door;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-87L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-87L\"></sup> it desires to have you, but you must rule over it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-87M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-87M\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Cain said to his brother Abel, “Let’s go out to the field.” While they were in the field, Cain attacked his brother Abel and killed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-88N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-88N\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Cain, “Where is your brother Abel?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-89O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-89O\"></sup>“I don’t know,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-89P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-89P\"></sup>” he replied. “Am I my brother’s keeper?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “What have you done? Listen! Your brother’s blood cries out to me from the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-90Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-90Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now you are under a curse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-91R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-91R\"></sup> and driven from the ground, which opened its mouth to receive your brother’s blood from your hand.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When you work the ground, it will no longer yield its crops for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-92S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-92S\"></sup> You will be a restless wanderer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-92T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-92T\"></sup> on the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-92U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-92U\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Cain said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “My punishment is more than I can bear.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Today you are driving me from the land, and I will be hidden from your presence;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-94V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-94V\"></sup> I will be a restless wanderer on the earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-94W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-94W\"></sup> and whoever finds me will kill me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-94X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-94X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Not so; anyone who kills Cain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-95Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-95Y\"></sup> will suffer vengeance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-95Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-95Z\"></sup> seven times over.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-95AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-95AA\"></sup>” Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put a mark on Cain so that no one who found him would kill him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Cain went out from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s presence<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-96AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-96AB\"></sup> and lived in the land of Nod, east of Eden.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-96AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-96AC\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Cain made love to his wife,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-97AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-97AD\"></sup> and she became pregnant and gave birth to Enoch. Cain was then building a city,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-97AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-97AE\"></sup> and he named it after his son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-97AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-97AF\"></sup> Enoch.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>To Enoch was born Irad, and Irad was the father of Mehujael, and Mehujael was the father of Methushael, and Methushael was the father of Lamech.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Lamech married<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-99AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-99AG\"></sup> two women,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-99AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-99AH\"></sup> one named Adah and the other Zillah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Adah gave birth to Jabal; he was the father of those who live in tents and raise livestock.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>His brother’s name was Jubal; he was the father of all who play stringed instruments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-101AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-101AI\"></sup> and pipes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-101AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-101AJ\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Zillah also had a son, Tubal-Cain, who forged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-102AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-102AK\"></sup> all kinds of tools out of bronze and iron. Tubal-Cain’s sister was Naamah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Lamech said to his wives,“Adah and Zillah, listen to me;wives of Lamech, hear my words.I have killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-103AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-103AL\"></sup> a man for wounding me,a young man for injuring me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>If Cain is avenged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-104AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-104AM\"></sup> seven times,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-104AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-104AN\"></sup>then Lamech seventy-seven times.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-104AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-104AO\"></sup>”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Adam made love to his wife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-105AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-105AP\"></sup> again, and she gave birth to a son and named him Seth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-105AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-105AQ\"></sup> saying, “God has granted me another child in place of Abel, since Cain killed him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-105AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-105AR\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Seth also had a son, and he named him Enosh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-106AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-106AS\"></sup>At that time people began to call on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-106AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-106AT\"></sup>"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>This is the written account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-107A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-107A\"></sup> of Adam’s family line.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-107B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-107B\"></sup>When God created mankind, he made them in the likeness of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-107C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-107C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He created them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-108D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-108D\"></sup> male and female<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-108E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-108E\"></sup> and blessed them. And he named them “Mankind” when they were created.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When Adam had lived 130 years, he had a son in his own likeness, in his own image;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-109F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-109F\"></sup> and he named him Seth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-109G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-109G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>After Seth was born, Adam lived 800 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Altogether, Adam lived a total of 930 years, and then he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-111H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-111H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Seth had lived 105 years, he became the father of Enosh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-112I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-112I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>After he became the father of Enosh, Seth lived 807 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Altogether, Seth lived a total of 912 years, and then he died.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Enosh had lived 90 years, he became the father of Kenan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-115J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-115J\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>After he became the father of Kenan, Enosh lived 815 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Altogether, Enosh lived a total of 905 years, and then he died.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Kenan had lived 70 years, he became the father of Mahalalel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-118K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-118K\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After he became the father of Mahalalel, Kenan lived 840 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Altogether, Kenan lived a total of 910 years, and then he died.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Mahalalel had lived 65 years, he became the father of Jared.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-121L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-121L\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>After he became the father of Jared, Mahalalel lived 830 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Altogether, Mahalalel lived a total of 895 years, and then he died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Jared had lived 162 years, he became the father of Enoch.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-124M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-124M\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After he became the father of Enoch, Jared lived 800 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Altogether, Jared lived a total of 962 years, and then he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Enoch had lived 65 years, he became the father of Methuselah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-127N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-127N\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After he became the father of Methuselah, Enoch walked faithfully with God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-128O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-128O\"></sup> 300 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Altogether, Enoch lived a total of 365 years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Enoch walked faithfully with God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-130P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-130P\"></sup> then he was no more, because God took him away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-130Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-130Q\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Methuselah had lived 187 years, he became the father of Lamech.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-131R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-131R\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>After he became the father of Lamech, Methuselah lived 782 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Altogether, Methuselah lived a total of 969 years, and then he died.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Lamech had lived 182 years, he had a son.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He named him Noah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-135S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-135S\"></sup> and said, “He will comfort us in the labor and painful toil of our hands caused by the ground the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has cursed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-135T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-135T\"></sup>”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>After Noah was born, Lamech lived 595 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Altogether, Lamech lived a total of 777 years, and then he died.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>After Noah was 500 years old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-138U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-138U\"></sup> he became the father of Shem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-138V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-138V\"></sup> Ham and Japheth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-138W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-138W\"></sup>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>When human beings began to increase in number on the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-139A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-139A\"></sup> and daughters were born to them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the sons of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-140B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-140B\"></sup> saw that the daughters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-140C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-140C\"></sup> of humans were beautiful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-140D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-140D\"></sup> and they married<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-140E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-140E\"></sup> any of them they chose.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “My Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-141F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-141F\"></sup> will not contend with humans forever,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-141G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-141G\"></sup> for they are mortal;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-141H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-141H\"></sup> their days will be a hundred and twenty years.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Nephilim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-142I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-142I\"></sup> were on the earth in those days—and also afterward—when the sons of God went to the daughters of humans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-142J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-142J\"></sup> and had children by them. They were the heroes of old, men of renown.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-142K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-142K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw how great the wickedness of the human race had become on the earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-143L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-143L\"></sup> and that every inclination of the thoughts of the human heart was only evil all the time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-143M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-143M\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regretted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-144N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-144N\"></sup> that he had made human beings on the earth, and his heart was deeply troubled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will wipe from the face of the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-145O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-145O\"></sup> the human race I have created—and with them the animals, the birds and the creatures that move along the ground—for I regret that I have made them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-145P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-145P\"></sup>”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Noah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-146Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-146Q\"></sup> found favor in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-146R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-146R\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-147S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-147S\"></sup> of Noah and his family.Noah was a righteous man, blameless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-147T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-147T\"></sup> among the people of his time,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-147U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-147U\"></sup> and he walked faithfully with God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-147V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-147V\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Noah had three sons: Shem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-148W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-148W\"></sup> Ham and Japheth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-148X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-148X\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the earth was corrupt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-149Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-149Y\"></sup> in God’s sight and was full of violence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-149Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-149Z\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>God saw how corrupt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-150AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-150AA\"></sup> the earth had become, for all the people on earth had corrupted their ways.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-150AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-150AB\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So God said to Noah, “I am going to put an end to all people, for the earth is filled with violence because of them. I am surely going to destroy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-151AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-151AC\"></sup> both them and the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-151AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-151AD\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So make yourself an ark of cypress wood;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-152AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-152AE\"></sup> make rooms in it and coat it with pitch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-152AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-152AF\"></sup> inside and out.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>This is how you are to build it: The ark is to be three hundred cubits long, fifty cubits wide and thirty cubits high.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Make a roof for it, leaving below the roof an opening one cubit high all around. Put a door in the side of the ark and make lower, middle and upper decks.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I am going to bring floodwaters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-155AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-155AG\"></sup> on the earth to destroy all life under the heavens, every creature that has the breath of life in it. Everything on earth will perish.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-155AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-155AH\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But I will establish my covenant with you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-156AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-156AI\"></sup> and you will enter the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-156AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-156AJ\"></sup>—you and your sons and your wife and your sons’ wives with you.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You are to bring into the ark two of all living creatures, male and female, to keep them alive with you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-157AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-157AK\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Two<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-158AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-158AL\"></sup> of every kind of bird, of every kind of animal and of every kind<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-158AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-158AM\"></sup> of creature that moves along the ground will come to you to be kept alive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-158AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-158AN\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You are to take every kind of food that is to be eaten and store it away as food for you and for them.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Noah did everything just as God commanded him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-160AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-160AO\"></sup>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> then said to Noah, “Go into the ark, you and your whole family,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-161A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-161A\"></sup> because I have found you righteous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-161B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-161B\"></sup> in this generation.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Take with you seven pairs of every kind of clean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-162C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-162C\"></sup> animal, a male and its mate, and one pair of every kind of unclean animal, a male and its mate,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and also seven pairs of every kind of bird, male and female, to keep their various kinds alive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-163D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-163D\"></sup> throughout the earth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Seven days from now I will send rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-164E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-164E\"></sup> on the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-164F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-164F\"></sup> for forty days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-164G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-164G\"></sup> and forty nights,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-164H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-164H\"></sup> and I will wipe from the face of the earth every living creature I have made.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-164I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-164I\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Noah did all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-165J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-165J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Noah was six hundred years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-166K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-166K\"></sup> when the floodwaters came on the earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Noah and his sons and his wife and his sons’ wives entered the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-167L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-167L\"></sup> to escape the waters of the flood.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Pairs of clean and unclean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-168M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-168M\"></sup> animals, of birds and of all creatures that move along the ground,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>male and female, came to Noah and entered the ark, as God had commanded Noah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-169N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-169N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And after the seven days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-170O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-170O\"></sup> the floodwaters came on the earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In the six hundredth year of Noah’s life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-171P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-171P\"></sup> on the seventeenth day of the second month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-171Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-171Q\"></sup>—on that day all the springs of the great deep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-171R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-171R\"></sup> burst forth, and the floodgates of the heavens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-171S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-171S\"></sup> were opened.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And rain fell on the earth forty days and forty nights.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-172T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-172T\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On that very day Noah and his sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-173U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-173U\"></sup> Shem, Ham and Japheth, together with his wife and the wives of his three sons, entered the ark.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-173V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-173V\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They had with them every wild animal according to its kind, all livestock according to their kinds, every creature that moves along the ground according to its kind and every bird according to its kind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-174W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-174W\"></sup> everything with wings.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Pairs of all creatures that have the breath of life in them came to Noah and entered the ark.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-175X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-175X\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The animals going in were male and female of every living thing, as God had commanded Noah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-176Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-176Y\"></sup> Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shut him in.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For forty days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-177Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-177Z\"></sup> the flood kept coming on the earth, and as the waters increased they lifted the ark high above the earth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The waters rose and increased greatly on the earth, and the ark floated on the surface of the water.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They rose greatly on the earth, and all the high mountains under the entire heavens were covered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-179AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-179AA\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The waters rose and covered the mountains to a depth of more than fifteen cubits. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-180AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-180AB\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Every living thing that moved on land perished—birds, livestock, wild animals, all the creatures that swarm over the earth, and all mankind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-181AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-181AC\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Everything on dry land that had the breath of life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-182AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-182AD\"></sup> in its nostrils died.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Every living thing on the face of the earth was wiped out; people and animals and the creatures that move along the ground and the birds were wiped from the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-183AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-183AE\"></sup> Only Noah was left, and those with him in the ark.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-183AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-183AF\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The waters flooded the earth for a hundred and fifty days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-184AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-184AG\"></sup>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>But God remembered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-185A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-185A\"></sup> Noah and all the wild animals and the livestock that were with him in the ark, and he sent a wind over the earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-185B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-185B\"></sup> and the waters receded.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now the springs of the deep and the floodgates of the heavens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-186C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-186C\"></sup> had been closed, and the rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-186D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-186D\"></sup> had stopped falling from the sky.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The water receded steadily from the earth. At the end of the hundred and fifty days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-187E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-187E\"></sup> the water had gone down,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and on the seventeenth day of the seventh month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-188F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-188F\"></sup> the ark came to rest on the mountains<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-188G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-188G\"></sup> of Ararat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-188H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-188H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The waters continued to recede until the tenth month, and on the first day of the tenth month the tops of the mountains became visible.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After forty days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-190I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-190I\"></sup> Noah opened a window he had made in the ark",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and sent out a raven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-191J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-191J\"></sup> and it kept flying back and forth until the water had dried up from the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-191K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-191K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he sent out a dove<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-192L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-192L\"></sup> to see if the water had receded from the surface of the ground.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the dove could find nowhere to perch because there was water over all the surface of the earth; so it returned to Noah in the ark. He reached out his hand and took the dove and brought it back to himself in the ark.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He waited seven more days and again sent out the dove from the ark.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the dove returned to him in the evening, there in its beak was a freshly plucked olive leaf! Then Noah knew that the water had receded from the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-195M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-195M\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He waited seven more days and sent the dove out again, but this time it did not return to him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>By the first day of the first month of Noah’s six hundred and first year,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-197N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-197N\"></sup> the water had dried up from the earth. Noah then removed the covering from the ark and saw that the surface of the ground was dry.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>By the twenty-seventh day of the second month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-198O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-198O\"></sup> the earth was completely dry.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then God said to Noah,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Come out of the ark, you and your wife and your sons and their wives.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-200P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-200P\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Bring out every kind of living creature that is with you—the birds, the animals, and all the creatures that move along the ground—so they can multiply on the earth and be fruitful and increase in number on it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-201Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-201Q\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Noah came out, together with his sons and his wife and his sons’ wives.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-202R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-202R\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>All the animals and all the creatures that move along the ground and all the birds—everything that moves on land—came out of the ark, one kind after another.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Noah built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-204S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-204S\"></sup> and, taking some of all the clean animals and clean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-204T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-204T\"></sup> birds, he sacrificed burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-204U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-204U\"></sup> on it.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> smelled the pleasing aroma<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-205V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-205V\"></sup> and said in his heart: “Never again will I curse the ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-205W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-205W\"></sup> because of humans, even though every inclination of the human heart is evil from childhood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-205X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-205X\"></sup> And never again will I destroy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-205Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-205Y\"></sup> all living creatures,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-205Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-205Z\"></sup> as I have done.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“As long as the earth endures,seedtime and harvest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-206AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-206AA\"></sup>cold and heat,summer and winter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-206AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-206AB\"></sup>day and nightwill never cease.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-206AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-206AC\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Then God blessed Noah and his sons, saying to them, “Be fruitful and increase in number and fill the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-207A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-207A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The fear and dread of you will fall on all the beasts of the earth, and on all the birds in the sky, on every creature that moves along the ground, and on all the fish in the sea; they are given into your hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-208B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-208B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Everything that lives and moves about will be food for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-209C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-209C\"></sup> Just as I gave you the green plants, I now give you everything.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-209D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-209D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“But you must not eat meat that has its lifeblood still in it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-210E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-210E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And for your lifeblood I will surely demand an accounting.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-211F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-211F\"></sup> I will demand an accounting from every animal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-211G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-211G\"></sup> And from each human being, too, I will demand an accounting for the life of another human being.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-211H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-211H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Whoever sheds human blood,by humans shall their blood be shed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-212I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-212I\"></sup>for in the image of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-212J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-212J\"></sup>has God made mankind.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As for you, be fruitful and increase in number; multiply on the earth and increase upon it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-213K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-213K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then God said to Noah and to his sons with him:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“I now establish my covenant with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-215L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-215L\"></sup> and with your descendants after you",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and with every living creature that was with you—the birds, the livestock and all the wild animals, all those that came out of the ark with you—every living creature on earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I establish my covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-217M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-217M\"></sup> with you:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-217N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-217N\"></sup> Never again will all life be destroyed by the waters of a flood; never again will there be a flood to destroy the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-217O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-217O\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And God said, “This is the sign of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-218P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-218P\"></sup> I am making between me and you and every living creature with you, a covenant for all generations to come:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-218Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-218Q\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I have set my rainbow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-219R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-219R\"></sup> in the clouds, and it will be the sign of the covenant between me and the earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Whenever I bring clouds over the earth and the rainbow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-220S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-220S\"></sup> appears in the clouds,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I will remember my covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-221T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-221T\"></sup> between me and you and all living creatures of every kind. Never again will the waters become a flood to destroy all life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-221U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-221U\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Whenever the rainbow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-222V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-222V\"></sup> appears in the clouds, I will see it and remember the everlasting covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-222W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-222W\"></sup> between God and all living creatures of every kind on the earth.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So God said to Noah, “This is the sign of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-223X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-223X\"></sup> I have established between me and all life on the earth.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Noah who came out of the ark were Shem, Ham and Japheth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-224Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-224Y\"></sup> (Ham was the father of Canaan.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-224Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-224Z\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were the three sons of Noah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-225AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-225AA\"></sup> and from them came the people who were scattered over the whole earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-225AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-225AB\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Noah, a man of the soil, proceeded to plant a vineyard.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When he drank some of its wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-227AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-227AC\"></sup> he became drunk and lay uncovered inside his tent.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ham, the father of Canaan, saw his father naked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-228AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-228AD\"></sup> and told his two brothers outside.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But Shem and Japheth took a garment and laid it across their shoulders; then they walked in backward and covered their father’s naked body. Their faces were turned the other way so that they would not see their father naked.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Noah awoke from his wine and found out what his youngest son had done to him,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>he said,“Cursed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-231AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-231AE\"></sup> be Canaan!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-231AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-231AF\"></sup>The lowest of slaveswill he be to his brothers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-231AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-231AG\"></sup>”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He also said,“Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Shem!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-232AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-232AH\"></sup>May Canaan be the slave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-232AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-232AI\"></sup> of Shem.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>May God extend Japheth’s territory;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-233AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-233AJ\"></sup>may Japheth live in the tents of Shem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-233AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-233AK\"></sup>and may Canaan be the slave of Japheth.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>After the flood Noah lived 350 years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Noah lived a total of 950 years, and then he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-235AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-235AL\"></sup>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-236A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-236A\"></sup> of Shem, Ham and Japheth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-236B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-236B\"></sup> Noah’s sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-236C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-236C\"></sup> who themselves had sons after the flood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The sons of Japheth:Gomer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-237E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-237E\"></sup> Magog,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-237F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-237F\"></sup> Madai, Javan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-237G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-237G\"></sup> Tubal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-237H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-237H\"></sup> Meshek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-237I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-237I\"></sup> and Tiras.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Gomer:Ashkenaz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-238J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-238J\"></sup> Riphath and Togarmah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-238K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-238K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Javan:Elishah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-239L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-239L\"></sup> Tarshish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-239M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-239M\"></sup> the Kittites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-239N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-239N\"></sup> and the Rodanites.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>(From these the maritime peoples spread out into their territories by their clans within their nations, each with its own language.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-240O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-240O\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The sons of Ham:Cush,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-241Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-241Q\"></sup> Egypt, Put<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-241R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-241R\"></sup> and Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-241S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-241S\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Cush:Seba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-242T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-242T\"></sup> Havilah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-242U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-242U\"></sup> Sabtah, Raamah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-242V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-242V\"></sup> and Sabteka.The sons of Raamah:Sheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-242W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-242W\"></sup> and Dedan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-242X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-242X\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Cush was the father of Nimrod,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-243Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-243Y\"></sup> who became a mighty warrior on the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He was a mighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-244Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-244Z\"></sup> hunter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-244AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-244AA\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; that is why it is said, “Like Nimrod, a mighty hunter before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The first centers of his kingdom were Babylon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-245AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-245AB\"></sup> Uruk,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-245AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-245AC\"></sup> Akkad and Kalneh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-245AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-245AD\"></sup> in Shinar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-245AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-245AE\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From that land he went to Assyria,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-246AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-246AF\"></sup> where he built Nineveh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-246AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-246AG\"></sup> Rehoboth Ir, Calah",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and Resen, which is between Nineveh and Calah—which is the great city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Egypt was the father ofthe Ludites, Anamites, Lehabites, Naphtuhites,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Pathrusites, Kasluhites (from whom the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-249AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-249AH\"></sup> came) and Caphtorites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-249AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-249AI\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-250AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-250AJ\"></sup> was the father ofSidon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-250AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-250AK\"></sup> his firstborn,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-250AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-250AL\"></sup> and of the Hittites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-250AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-250AM\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jebusites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-251AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-251AN\"></sup> Amorites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-251AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-251AO\"></sup> Girgashites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-251AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-251AP\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Hivites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-252AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-252AQ\"></sup> Arkites, Sinites,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Arvadites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-253AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-253AR\"></sup> Zemarites and Hamathites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-253AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-253AS\"></sup>Later the Canaanite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-253AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-253AT\"></sup> clans scattered",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and the borders of Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-254AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-254AU\"></sup> reached from Sidon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-254AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-254AV\"></sup> toward Gerar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-254AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-254AW\"></sup> as far as Gaza,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-254AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-254AX\"></sup> and then toward Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah and Zeboyim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-254AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-254AY\"></sup> as far as Lasha.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>These are the sons of Ham by their clans and languages, in their territories and nations.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Sons were also born to Shem, whose older brother was Japheth; Shem was the ancestor of all the sons of Eber.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-256BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-256BA\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Shem:Elam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-257BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-257BB\"></sup> Ashur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-257BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-257BC\"></sup> Arphaxad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-257BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-257BD\"></sup> Lud and Aram.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-257BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-257BE\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Aram:Uz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-258BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-258BF\"></sup> Hul, Gether and Meshek.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Arphaxad was the father of Shelah,and Shelah the father of Eber.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-259BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-259BG\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Two sons were born to Eber:One was named Peleg, because in his time the earth was divided; his brother was named Joktan.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Joktan was the father ofAlmodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Hadoram, Uzal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-262BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-262BH\"></sup> Diklah,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Obal, Abimael, Sheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-263BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-263BI\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Ophir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-264BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-264BJ\"></sup> Havilah and Jobab. All these were sons of Joktan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The region where they lived stretched from Mesha toward Sephar, in the eastern hill country.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are the sons of Shem by their clans and languages, in their territories and nations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the clans of Noah’s sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-267BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-267BK\"></sup> according to their lines of descent, within their nations. From these the nations spread out over the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-267BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-267BL\"></sup> after the flood."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now the whole world had one language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-268A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-268A\"></sup> and a common speech.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>As people moved eastward, they found a plain in Shinar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-269B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-269B\"></sup> and settled there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said to each other, “Come, let’s make bricks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-270C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-270C\"></sup> and bake them thoroughly.” They used brick instead of stone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-270D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-270D\"></sup> and tar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-270E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-270E\"></sup> for mortar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then they said, “Come, let us build ourselves a city, with a tower that reaches to the heavens,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-271F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-271F\"></sup> so that we may make a name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-271G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-271G\"></sup> for ourselves; otherwise we will be scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-271H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-271H\"></sup> over the face of the whole earth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-271I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-271I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-272J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-272J\"></sup> to see the city and the tower the people were building.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “If as one people speaking the same language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-273K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-273K\"></sup> they have begun to do this, then nothing they plan to do will be impossible for them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Come, let us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-274L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-274L\"></sup> go down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-274M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-274M\"></sup> and confuse their language so they will not understand each other.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-274N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-274N\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> scattered them from there over all the earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-275O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-275O\"></sup> and they stopped building the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>That is why it was called Babel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-276P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-276P\"></sup>—because there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> confused the language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-276Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-276Q\"></sup> of the whole world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-276R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-276R\"></sup> From there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-276S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-276S\"></sup> them over the face of the whole earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-277U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-277U\"></sup> of Shem’s family line.Two years after the flood, when Shem was 100 years old, he became the father of Arphaxad.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-277V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-277V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And after he became the father of Arphaxad, Shem lived 500 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Arphaxad had lived 35 years, he became the father of Shelah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-279W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-279W\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And after he became the father of Shelah, Arphaxad lived 403 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Shelah had lived 30 years, he became the father of Eber.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-281X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-281X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And after he became the father of Eber, Shelah lived 403 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Eber had lived 34 years, he became the father of Peleg.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-283Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-283Y\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And after he became the father of Peleg, Eber lived 430 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Peleg had lived 30 years, he became the father of Reu.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-285Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-285Z\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And after he became the father of Reu, Peleg lived 209 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Reu had lived 32 years, he became the father of Serug.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-287AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-287AA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And after he became the father of Serug, Reu lived 207 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Serug had lived 30 years, he became the father of Nahor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-289AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-289AB\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And after he became the father of Nahor, Serug lived 200 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Nahor had lived 29 years, he became the father of Terah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-291AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-291AC\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And after he became the father of Terah, Nahor lived 119 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>After Terah had lived 70 years, he became the father of Abram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-293AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-293AD\"></sup> Nahor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-293AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-293AE\"></sup> and Haran.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-293AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-293AF\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-294AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-294AG\"></sup> of Terah’s family line.Terah became the father of Abram, Nahor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-294AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-294AH\"></sup> and Haran. And Haran became the father of Lot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-294AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-294AI\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>While his father Terah was still alive, Haran died in Ur of the Chaldeans,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-295AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-295AJ\"></sup> in the land of his birth.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Abram and Nahor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-296AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-296AK\"></sup> both married. The name of Abram’s wife was Sarai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-296AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-296AL\"></sup> and the name of Nahor’s wife was Milkah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-296AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-296AM\"></sup> she was the daughter of Haran, the father of both Milkah and Iskah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now Sarai was childless because she was not able to conceive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-297AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-297AN\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Terah took his son Abram, his grandson Lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-298AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-298AO\"></sup> son of Haran, and his daughter-in-law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-298AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-298AP\"></sup> Sarai, the wife of his son Abram, and together they set out from Ur of the Chaldeans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-298AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-298AQ\"></sup> to go to Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-298AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-298AR\"></sup> But when they came to Harran,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-298AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-298AS\"></sup> they settled there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Terah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-299AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-299AT\"></sup> lived 205 years, and he died in Harran."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to Abram, “Go from your country, your people and your father’s household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-300A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-300A\"></sup> to the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-300B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-300B\"></sup> I will show you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-300C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-300C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“I will make you into a great nation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-301D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-301D\"></sup>and I will bless you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-301E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-301E\"></sup>I will make your name great,and you will be a blessing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-301F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-301F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I will bless those who bless you,and whoever curses you I will curse;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-302G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-302G\"></sup>and all peoples on earthwill be blessed through you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-302H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-302H\"></sup>”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Abram went, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told him; and Lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-303I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-303I\"></sup> went with him. Abram was seventy-five years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-303J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-303J\"></sup> when he set out from Harran.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-303K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-303K\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He took his wife Sarai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-304L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-304L\"></sup> his nephew Lot, all the possessions they had accumulated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-304M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-304M\"></sup> and the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-304N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-304N\"></sup> they had acquired in Harran, and they set out for the land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-304O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-304O\"></sup> and they arrived there.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abram traveled through the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-305P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-305P\"></sup> as far as the site of the great tree of Moreh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-305Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-305Q\"></sup> at Shechem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-305R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-305R\"></sup> At that time the Canaanites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-305S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-305S\"></sup> were in the land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Abram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-306T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-306T\"></sup> and said, “To your offspring I will give this land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-306U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-306U\"></sup>”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-306V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-306V\"></sup> So he built an altar there to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-306W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-306W\"></sup> who had appeared to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From there he went on toward the hills east of Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-307X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-307X\"></sup> and pitched his tent,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-307Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-307Y\"></sup> with Bethel on the west and Ai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-307Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-307Z\"></sup> on the east. There he built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-307AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-307AA\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Abram set out and continued toward the Negev.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-308AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-308AB\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now there was a famine in the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-309AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-309AD\"></sup> and Abram went down to Egypt to live there for a while because the famine was severe.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-309AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-309AE\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As he was about to enter Egypt, he said to his wife Sarai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-310AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-310AF\"></sup> “I know what a beautiful woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-310AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-310AG\"></sup> you are.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the Egyptians see you, they will say, ‘This is his wife.’ Then they will kill me but will let you live.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Say you are my sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-312AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-312AH\"></sup> so that I will be treated well for your sake and my life will be spared because of you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Abram came to Egypt, the Egyptians saw that Sarai was a very beautiful woman.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-313AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-313AI\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when Pharaoh’s officials saw her, they praised her to Pharaoh, and she was taken into his palace.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He treated Abram well for her sake, and Abram acquired sheep and cattle, male and female donkeys, male and female servants, and camels.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-315AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-315AJ\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> inflicted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-316AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-316AK\"></sup> serious diseases on Pharaoh and his household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-316AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-316AL\"></sup> because of Abram’s wife Sarai.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Pharaoh summoned Abram. “What have you done to me?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-317AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-317AM\"></sup> he said. “Why didn’t you tell me she was your wife?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-317AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-317AN\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why did you say, ‘She is my sister,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-318AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-318AO\"></sup> so that I took her to be my wife? Now then, here is your wife. Take her and go!”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Pharaoh gave orders about Abram to his men, and they sent him on his way, with his wife and everything he had."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>So Abram went up from Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-320A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-320A\"></sup> to the Negev,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-320B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-320B\"></sup> with his wife and everything he had, and Lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-320C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-320C\"></sup> went with him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Abram had become very wealthy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-321D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-321D\"></sup> in livestock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-321E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-321E\"></sup> and in silver and gold.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>From the Negev<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-322F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-322F\"></sup> he went from place to place until he came to Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-322G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-322G\"></sup> to the place between Bethel and Ai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-322H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-322H\"></sup> where his tent had been earlier",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and where he had first built an altar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-323I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-323I\"></sup> There Abram called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-323J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-323J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Lot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-324K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-324K\"></sup> who was moving about with Abram, also had flocks and herds and tents.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But the land could not support them while they stayed together, for their possessions were so great that they were not able to stay together.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-325L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-325L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And quarreling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-326M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-326M\"></sup> arose between Abram’s herders and Lot’s. The Canaanites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-326N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-326N\"></sup> and Perizzites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-326O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-326O\"></sup> were also living in the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-326P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-326P\"></sup> at that time.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Abram said to Lot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-327Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-327Q\"></sup> “Let’s not have any quarreling between you and me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-327R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-327R\"></sup> or between your herders and mine, for we are close relatives.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-327S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-327S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Is not the whole land before you? Let’s part company. If you go to the left, I’ll go to the right; if you go to the right, I’ll go to the left.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-328T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-328T\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Lot looked around and saw that the whole plain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-329U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-329U\"></sup> of the Jordan toward Zoar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-329V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-329V\"></sup> was well watered, like the garden of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-329W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-329W\"></sup> like the land of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-329X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-329X\"></sup> (This was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> destroyed Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-329Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-329Y\"></sup> and Gomorrah.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-329Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-329Z\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Lot chose for himself the whole plain of the Jordan and set out toward the east. The two men parted company:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Abram lived in the land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-331AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-331AA\"></sup> while Lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-331AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-331AB\"></sup> lived among the cities of the plain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-331AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-331AC\"></sup> and pitched his tents near Sodom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-331AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-331AD\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now the people of Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-332AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-332AE\"></sup> were wicked and were sinning greatly against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-332AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-332AF\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abram after Lot had parted from him, “Look around from where you are, to the north and south, to the east and west.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-333AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-333AG\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>All the land that you see I will give to you and your offspring forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-334AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-334AH\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will make your offspring like the dust of the earth, so that if anyone could count the dust, then your offspring could be counted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-335AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-335AI\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Go, walk through the length and breadth of the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-336AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-336AJ\"></sup> for I am giving it to you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-336AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-336AK\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Abram went to live near the great trees of Mamre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-337AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-337AL\"></sup> at Hebron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-337AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-337AM\"></sup> where he pitched his tents. There he built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-337AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-337AN\"></sup>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>At the time when Amraphel was king of Shinar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-338A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-338A\"></sup> Arioch king of Ellasar, Kedorlaomer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-338B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-338B\"></sup> king of Elam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-338C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-338C\"></sup> and Tidal king of Goyim,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>these kings went to war against Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah, Shinab king of Admah, Shemeber king of Zeboyim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-339D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-339D\"></sup> and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-339E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-339E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>All these latter kings joined forces in the Valley of Siddim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-340F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-340F\"></sup> (that is, the Dead Sea Valley<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-340G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-340G\"></sup>).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For twelve years they had been subject to Kedorlaomer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-341H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-341H\"></sup> but in the thirteenth year they rebelled.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the fourteenth year, Kedorlaomer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-342I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-342I\"></sup> and the kings allied with him went out and defeated the Rephaites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-342J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-342J\"></sup> in Ashteroth Karnaim, the Zuzites in Ham, the Emites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-342K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-342K\"></sup> in Shaveh Kiriathaim",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the Horites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-343L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-343L\"></sup> in the hill country of Seir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-343M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-343M\"></sup> as far as El Paran<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-343N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-343N\"></sup> near the desert.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they turned back and went to En Mishpat (that is, Kadesh),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-344O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-344O\"></sup> and they conquered the whole territory of the Amalekites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-344P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-344P\"></sup> as well as the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-344Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-344Q\"></sup> who were living in Hazezon Tamar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-344R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-344R\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king of Sodom, the king of Gomorrah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-345S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-345S\"></sup> the king of Admah, the king of Zeboyim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-345T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-345T\"></sup> and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-345U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-345U\"></sup> marched out and drew up their battle lines in the Valley of Siddim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-345V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-345V\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>against Kedorlaomer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-346W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-346W\"></sup> king of Elam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-346X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-346X\"></sup> Tidal king of Goyim, Amraphel king of Shinar and Arioch king of Ellasar—four kings against five.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the Valley of Siddim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-347Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-347Y\"></sup> was full of tar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-347Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-347Z\"></sup> pits, and when the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-347AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-347AA\"></sup> fled, some of the men fell into them and the rest fled to the hills.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-347AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-347AB\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The four kings seized all the goods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-348AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-348AC\"></sup> of Sodom and Gomorrah and all their food; then they went away.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They also carried off Abram’s nephew Lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-349AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-349AD\"></sup> and his possessions, since he was living in Sodom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A man who had escaped came and reported this to Abram the Hebrew.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-350AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-350AE\"></sup> Now Abram was living near the great trees of Mamre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-350AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-350AF\"></sup> the Amorite, a brother of Eshkol<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-350AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-350AG\"></sup> and Aner, all of whom were allied with Abram.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Abram heard that his relative<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-351AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-351AH\"></sup> had been taken captive, he called out the 318 trained<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-351AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-351AI\"></sup> men born in his household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-351AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-351AJ\"></sup> and went in pursuit as far as Dan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-351AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-351AK\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>During the night Abram divided his men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-352AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-352AL\"></sup> to attack them and he routed them, pursuing them as far as Hobah, north of Damascus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-352AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-352AM\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He recovered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-353AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-353AN\"></sup> all the goods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-353AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-353AO\"></sup> and brought back his relative Lot and his possessions, together with the women and the other people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After Abram returned from defeating Kedorlaomer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-354AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-354AP\"></sup> and the kings allied with him, the king of Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-354AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-354AQ\"></sup> came out to meet him in the Valley of Shaveh (that is, the King’s Valley).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-354AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-354AR\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Melchizedek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-355AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-355AS\"></sup> king of Salem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-355AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-355AT\"></sup> brought out bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-355AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-355AU\"></sup> and wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-355AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-355AV\"></sup> He was priest of God Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-355AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-355AW\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and he blessed Abram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-356AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-356AX\"></sup> saying,“Blessed be Abram by God Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-356AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-356AY\"></sup>Creator of heaven and earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-356AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-356AZ\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And praise be to God Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-357BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-357BA\"></sup>who delivered your enemies into your hand.”Then Abram gave him a tenth of everything.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-357BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-357BB\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king of Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-358BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-358BC\"></sup> said to Abram, “Give me the people and keep the goods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-358BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-358BD\"></sup> for yourself.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Abram said to the king of Sodom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-359BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-359BE\"></sup> “With raised hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-359BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-359BF\"></sup> I have sworn an oath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-359BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-359BG\"></sup> Creator of heaven and earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-359BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-359BH\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>that I will accept nothing belonging to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-360BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-360BI\"></sup> not even a thread or the strap of a sandal, so that you will never be able to say, ‘I made Abram rich.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I will accept nothing but what my men have eaten and the share that belongs to the men who went with me—to Aner, Eshkol and Mamre.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-361BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-361BJ\"></sup> Let them have their share.”"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>After this, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Abram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-362A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-362A\"></sup> in a vision:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-362B\"></sup>“Do not be afraid,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-362C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-362C\"></sup> Abram.I am your shield,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-362D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-362D\"></sup>your very great reward.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-362E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-362E\"></sup>”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Abram said, “Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-363F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-363F\"></sup> what can you give me since I remain childless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-363G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-363G\"></sup> and the one who will inherit my estate is Eliezer of Damascus?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-363H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-363H\"></sup>”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Abram said, “You have given me no children; so a servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-364I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-364I\"></sup> in my household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-364J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-364J\"></sup> will be my heir.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him: “This man will not be your heir, but a son who is your own flesh and blood will be your heir.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-365K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-365K\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He took him outside and said, “Look up at the sky and count the stars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-366L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-366L\"></sup>—if indeed you can count them.” Then he said to him, “So shall your offspring be.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-366M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-366M\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abram believed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he credited it to him as righteousness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-367N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-367N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He also said to him, “I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who brought you out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-368O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-368O\"></sup> of Ur of the Chaldeans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-368P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-368P\"></sup> to give you this land to take possession of it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-368Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-368Q\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Abram said, “Sovereign <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-369R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-369R\"></sup> how can I know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-369S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-369S\"></sup> that I will gain possession of it?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-369T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-369T\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Bring me a heifer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-370U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-370U\"></sup> a goat and a ram, each three years old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-370V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-370V\"></sup> along with a dove and a young pigeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-370W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-370W\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Abram brought all these to him, cut them in two and arranged the halves opposite each other;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-371X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-371X\"></sup> the birds, however, he did not cut in half.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-371Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-371Y\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then birds of prey came down on the carcasses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-372Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-372Z\"></sup> but Abram drove them away.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As the sun was setting, Abram fell into a deep sleep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-373AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-373AA\"></sup> and a thick and dreadful darkness came over him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Know for certain that for four hundred years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-374AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-374AB\"></sup> your descendants will be strangers in a country not their own and that they will be enslaved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-374AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-374AC\"></sup> and mistreated there.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But I will punish the nation they serve as slaves, and afterward they will come out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-375AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-375AD\"></sup> with great possessions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-375AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-375AE\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You, however, will go to your ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-376AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-376AF\"></sup> in peace and be buried at a good old age.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-376AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-376AG\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In the fourth generation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-377AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-377AH\"></sup> your descendants will come back here,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-377AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-377AI\"></sup> for the sin of the Amorites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-377AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-377AJ\"></sup> has not yet reached its full measure.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the sun had set and darkness had fallen, a smoking firepot with a blazing torch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-378AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-378AK\"></sup> appeared and passed between the pieces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-378AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-378AL\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On that day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with Abram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-379AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-379AM\"></sup> and said, “To your descendants I give this land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-379AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-379AN\"></sup> from the Wadi of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-379AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-379AO\"></sup> to the great river, the Euphrates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-379AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-379AP\"></sup>—",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the land of the Kenites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-380AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-380AQ\"></sup> Kenizzites, Kadmonites,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Hittites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-381AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-381AR\"></sup> Perizzites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-381AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-381AS\"></sup> Rephaites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-381AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-381AT\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Amorites, Canaanites, Girgashites and Jebusites.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-382AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-382AU\"></sup>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now Sarai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-383A\"></sup> Abram’s wife, had borne him no children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-383B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-383B\"></sup> But she had an Egyptian slave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-383C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-383C\"></sup> named Hagar;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-383D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-383D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>so she said to Abram, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has kept me from having children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-384E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-384E\"></sup> Go, sleep with my slave; perhaps I can build a family through her.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-384F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-384F\"></sup>Abram agreed to what Sarai said.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So after Abram had been living in Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-385G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-385G\"></sup> ten years,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-385H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-385H\"></sup> Sarai his wife took her Egyptian slave Hagar and gave her to her husband to be his wife.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He slept with Hagar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-386I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-386I\"></sup> and she conceived.When she knew she was pregnant, she began to despise her mistress.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-386J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-386J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Sarai said to Abram, “You are responsible for the wrong I am suffering. I put my slave in your arms, and now that she knows she is pregnant, she despises me. May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> judge between you and me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-387K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-387K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Your slave is in your hands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-388L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-388L\"></sup>” Abram said. “Do with her whatever you think best.” Then Sarai mistreated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-388M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-388M\"></sup> Hagar; so she fled from her.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-389N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-389N\"></sup> found Hagar near a spring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-389O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-389O\"></sup> in the desert; it was the spring that is beside the road to Shur.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-389P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-389P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he said, “Hagar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-390Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-390Q\"></sup> slave of Sarai, where have you come from, and where are you going?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-390R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-390R\"></sup>“I’m running away from my mistress Sarai,” she answered.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> told her, “Go back to your mistress and submit to her.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The angel added, “I will increase your descendants so much that they will be too numerous to count.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-392S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-392S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-393T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-393T\"></sup> also said to her:“You are now pregnantand you will give birth to a son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-393U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-393U\"></sup>You shall name him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-393V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-393V\"></sup> Ishmael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-393W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-393W\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has heard of your misery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-393X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-393X\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He will be a wild donkey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-394Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-394Y\"></sup> of a man;his hand will be against everyoneand everyone’s hand against him,and he will live in hostilitytoward all his brothers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-394Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-394Z\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>She gave this name to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who spoke to her: “You are the God who sees me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-395AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-395AA\"></sup>” for she said, “I have now seen the One who sees me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-395AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-395AB\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>That is why the well<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-396AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-396AC\"></sup> was called Beer Lahai Roi;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-396AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-396AD\"></sup> it is still there, between Kadesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-396AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-396AE\"></sup> and Bered.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Hagar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-397AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-397AF\"></sup> bore Abram a son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-397AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-397AG\"></sup> and Abram gave the name Ishmael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-397AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-397AH\"></sup> to the son she had borne.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Abram was eighty-six years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-398AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-398AI\"></sup> when Hagar bore him Ishmael."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>When Abram was ninety-nine years old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-399A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-399A\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-399B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-399B\"></sup> and said, “I am God Almighty;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-399C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-399C\"></sup> walk before me faithfully and be blameless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-399D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-399D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then I will make my covenant between me and you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-400E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-400E\"></sup> and will greatly increase your numbers.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-400F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-400F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abram fell facedown,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-401G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-401G\"></sup> and God said to him,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“As for me, this is my covenant with you:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-402H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-402H\"></sup> You will be the father of many nations.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-402I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-402I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>No longer will you be called Abram; your name will be Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-403J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-403J\"></sup> for I have made you a father of many nations.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-403K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-403K\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will make you very fruitful;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-404L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-404L\"></sup> I will make nations of you, and kings will come from you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-404M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-404M\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will establish my covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-405N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-405N\"></sup> as an everlasting covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-405O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-405O\"></sup> between me and you and your descendants after you for the generations to come, to be your God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-405P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-405P\"></sup> and the God of your descendants after you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-405Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-405Q\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The whole land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-406R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-406R\"></sup> where you now reside as a foreigner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-406S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-406S\"></sup> I will give as an everlasting possession to you and your descendants after you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-406T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-406T\"></sup> and I will be their God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-406U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-406U\"></sup>”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then God said to Abraham, “As for you, you must keep my covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-407V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-407V\"></sup> you and your descendants after you for the generations to come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-407W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-407W\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This is my covenant with you and your descendants after you, the covenant you are to keep: Every male among you shall be circumcised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-408X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-408X\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You are to undergo circumcision,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-409Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-409Y\"></sup> and it will be the sign of the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-409Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-409Z\"></sup> between me and you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For the generations to come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-410AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-410AA\"></sup> every male among you who is eight days old must be circumcised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-410AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-410AB\"></sup> including those born in your household or bought with money from a foreigner—those who are not your offspring.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Whether born in your household or bought with your money, they must be circumcised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-411AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-411AC\"></sup> My covenant in your flesh is to be an everlasting covenant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-411AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-411AD\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Any uncircumcised male, who has not been circumcised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-412AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-412AE\"></sup> in the flesh, will be cut off from his people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-412AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-412AF\"></sup> he has broken my covenant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-412AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-412AG\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>God also said to Abraham, “As for Sarai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-413AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-413AH\"></sup> your wife, you are no longer to call her Sarai; her name will be Sarah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-413AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-413AI\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will bless her and will surely give you a son by her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-414AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-414AJ\"></sup> I will bless her so that she will be the mother of nations;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-414AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-414AK\"></sup> kings of peoples will come from her.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abraham fell facedown;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-415AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-415AL\"></sup> he laughed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-415AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-415AM\"></sup> and said to himself, “Will a son be born to a man a hundred years old?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-415AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-415AN\"></sup> Will Sarah bear a child at the age of ninety?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-415AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-415AO\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Abraham said to God, “If only Ishmael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-416AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-416AP\"></sup> might live under your blessing!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-416AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-416AQ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then God said, “Yes, but your wife Sarah will bear you a son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-417AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-417AR\"></sup> and you will call him Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-417AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-417AS\"></sup> I will establish my covenant with him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-417AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-417AT\"></sup> as an everlasting covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-417AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-417AU\"></sup> for his descendants after him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And as for Ishmael, I have heard you: I will surely bless him; I will make him fruitful and will greatly increase his numbers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-418AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-418AV\"></sup> He will be the father of twelve rulers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-418AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-418AW\"></sup> and I will make him into a great nation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-418AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-418AX\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But my covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-419AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-419AY\"></sup> I will establish with Isaac, whom Sarah will bear to you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-419AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-419AZ\"></sup> by this time next year.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-419BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-419BA\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When he had finished speaking with Abraham, God went up from him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-420BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-420BB\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>On that very day Abraham took his son Ishmael and all those born in his household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-421BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-421BC\"></sup> or bought with his money, every male in his household, and circumcised them, as God told him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-421BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-421BD\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Abraham was ninety-nine years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-422BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-422BE\"></sup> when he was circumcised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-422BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-422BF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and his son Ishmael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-423BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-423BG\"></sup> was thirteen;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Abraham and his son Ishmael were both circumcised on that very day.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And every male in Abraham’s household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-425BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-425BH\"></sup>, including those born in his household or bought from a foreigner, was circumcised with him."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-426A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-426A\"></sup> near the great trees of Mamre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-426B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-426B\"></sup> while he was sitting at the entrance to his tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-426C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-426C\"></sup> in the heat of the day.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Abraham looked up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-427D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-427D\"></sup> and saw three men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-427E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-427E\"></sup> standing nearby. When he saw them, he hurried from the entrance of his tent to meet them and bowed low to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-427F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-427F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He said, “If I have found favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-428G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-428G\"></sup> my lord, do not pass your servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-428H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-428H\"></sup> by.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Let a little water be brought, and then you may all wash your feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-429I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-429I\"></sup> and rest under this tree.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let me get you something to eat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-430J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-430J\"></sup> so you can be refreshed and then go on your way—now that you have come to your servant.”“Very well,” they answered, “do as you say.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Abraham hurried into the tent to Sarah. “Quick,” he said, “get three seahs of the finest flour and knead it and bake some bread.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-431K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-431K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he ran to the herd and selected a choice, tender calf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-432L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-432L\"></sup> and gave it to a servant, who hurried to prepare it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He then brought some curds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-433M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-433M\"></sup> and milk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-433N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-433N\"></sup> and the calf that had been prepared, and set these before them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-433O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-433O\"></sup> While they ate, he stood near them under a tree.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Where is your wife Sarah?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-434P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-434P\"></sup> they asked him.“There, in the tent,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-434Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-434Q\"></sup>” he said.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then one of them said, “I will surely return to you about this time next year,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-435R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-435R\"></sup> and Sarah your wife will have a son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-435S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-435S\"></sup>Now Sarah was listening at the entrance to the tent, which was behind him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Abraham and Sarah were already very old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-436T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-436T\"></sup> and Sarah was past the age of childbearing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-436U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-436U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Sarah laughed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-437V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-437V\"></sup> to herself as she thought, “After I am worn out and my lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-437W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-437W\"></sup> is old, will I now have this pleasure?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abraham, “Why did Sarah laugh and say, ‘Will I really have a child, now that I am old?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-438X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-438X\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Is anything too hard for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-439Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-439Y\"></sup> I will return to you at the appointed time next year,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-439Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-439Z\"></sup> and Sarah will have a son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-439AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-439AA\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Sarah was afraid, so she lied and said, “I did not laugh.”But he said, “Yes, you did laugh.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-441AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-441AB\"></sup> got up to leave, they looked down toward Sodom, and Abraham walked along with them to see them on their way.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Shall I hide from Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-442AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-442AC\"></sup> what I am about to do?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-442AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-442AD\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Abraham will surely become a great and powerful nation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-443AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-443AE\"></sup> and all nations on earth will be blessed through him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For I have chosen him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-444AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-444AF\"></sup>, so that he will direct his children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-444AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-444AG\"></sup> and his household after him to keep the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-444AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-444AH\"></sup> by doing what is right and just,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-444AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-444AI\"></sup> so that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will bring about for Abraham what he has promised him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-444AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-444AJ\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “The outcry against Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-445AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-445AK\"></sup> and Gomorrah is so great<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-445AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-445AL\"></sup> and their sin so grievous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-445AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-445AM\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>that I will go down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-446AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-446AN\"></sup> and see if what they have done is as bad as the outcry that has reached me. If not, I will know.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-447AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-447AO\"></sup> turned away and went toward Sodom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-447AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-447AP\"></sup> but Abraham remained standing before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-447AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-447AQ\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Abraham approached him and said: “Will you sweep away the righteous with the wicked?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-448AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-448AR\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>What if there are fifty righteous people in the city? Will you really sweep it away and not spare the place for the sake of the fifty righteous people in it?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-449AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-449AS\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Far be it from you to do such a thing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-450AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-450AT\"></sup>—to kill the righteous with the wicked, treating the righteous<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-450AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-450AU\"></sup> and the wicked alike.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-450AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-450AV\"></sup> Far be it from you! Will not the Judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-450AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-450AW\"></sup> of all the earth do right?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-450AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-450AX\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “If I find fifty righteous people in the city of Sodom, I will spare the whole place for their sake.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-451AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-451AY\"></sup>”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Abraham spoke up again: “Now that I have been so bold as to speak to the Lord, though I am nothing but dust and ashes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-452AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-452AZ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>what if the number of the righteous is five less than fifty? Will you destroy the whole city for lack of five people?”“If I find forty-five there,” he said, “I will not destroy it.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Once again he spoke to him, “What if only forty are found there?”He said, “For the sake of forty, I will not do it.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he said, “May the Lord not be angry,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-455BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-455BA\"></sup> but let me speak. What if only thirty can be found there?”He answered, “I will not do it if I find thirty there.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Abraham said, “Now that I have been so bold as to speak to the Lord, what if only twenty can be found there?”He said, “For the sake of twenty, I will not destroy it.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then he said, “May the Lord not be angry, but let me speak just once more.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-457BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-457BB\"></sup> What if only ten can be found there?”He answered, “For the sake of ten,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-457BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-457BC\"></sup> I will not destroy it.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had finished speaking<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-458BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-458BD\"></sup> with Abraham, he left,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-458BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-458BE\"></sup> and Abraham returned home.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-458BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-458BF\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>The two angels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-459A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-459A\"></sup> arrived at Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-459B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-459B\"></sup> in the evening, and Lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-459C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-459C\"></sup> was sitting in the gateway of the city.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-459D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-459D\"></sup> When he saw them, he got up to meet them and bowed down with his face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-459E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-459E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“My lords,” he said, “please turn aside to your servant’s house. You can wash your feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-460F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-460F\"></sup> and spend the night and then go on your way early in the morning.”“No,” they answered, “we will spend the night in the square.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-460G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-460G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But he insisted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-461H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-461H\"></sup> so strongly that they did go with him and entered his house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-461I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-461I\"></sup> He prepared a meal for them, baking bread without yeast,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-461J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-461J\"></sup> and they ate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-461K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-461K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Before they had gone to bed, all the men from every part of the city of Sodom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-462L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-462L\"></sup>—both young and old—surrounded the house.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They called to Lot, “Where are the men who came to you tonight? Bring them out to us so that we can have sex with them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-463M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-463M\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Lot went outside to meet them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-464N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-464N\"></sup> and shut the door behind him",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and said, “No, my friends. Don’t do this wicked thing.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Look, I have two daughters who have never slept with a man. Let me bring them out to you, and you can do what you like with them. But don’t do anything to these men, for they have come under the protection of my roof.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-466O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-466O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Get out of our way,” they replied. “This fellow came here as a foreigner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-467P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-467P\"></sup> and now he wants to play the judge!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-467Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-467Q\"></sup> We’ll treat you worse than them.” They kept bringing pressure on Lot and moved forward to break down the door.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-468R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-468R\"></sup> inside reached out and pulled Lot back into the house and shut the door.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they struck the men who were at the door of the house, young and old, with blindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-469S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-469S\"></sup> so that they could not find the door.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The two men said to Lot, “Do you have anyone else here—sons-in-law, sons or daughters, or anyone else in the city who belongs to you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-470T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-470T\"></sup> Get them out of here,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>because we<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-471U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-471U\"></sup> are going to destroy this place. The outcry to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against its people is so great<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-471V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-471V\"></sup> that he has sent us to destroy it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-471W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-471W\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Lot went out and spoke to his sons-in-law, who were pledged to marry his daughters. He said, “Hurry and get out of this place, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is about to destroy the city!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-472X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-472X\"></sup>” But his sons-in-law thought he was joking.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-472Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-472Y\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>With the coming of dawn, the angels urged Lot, saying, “Hurry! Take your wife and your two daughters who are here, or you will be swept away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-473Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-473Z\"></sup> when the city is punished.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-473AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-473AA\"></sup>”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When he hesitated, the men grasped his hand and the hands of his wife and of his two daughters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-474AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-474AB\"></sup> and led them safely out of the city, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was merciful to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-474AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-474AC\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As soon as they had brought them out, one of them said, “Flee for your lives!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-475AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-475AD\"></sup> Don’t look back,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-475AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-475AE\"></sup> and don’t stop anywhere in the plain!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-475AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-475AF\"></sup> Flee to the mountains<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-475AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-475AG\"></sup> or you will be swept away!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Lot said to them, “No, my lords, please!",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Your servant has found favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-477AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-477AH\"></sup> and you have shown great kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-477AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-477AI\"></sup> to me in sparing my life. But I can’t flee to the mountains;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-477AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-477AJ\"></sup> this disaster will overtake me, and I’ll die.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Look, here is a town near enough to run to, and it is small. Let me flee to it—it is very small, isn’t it? Then my life will be spared.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He said to him, “Very well, I will grant this request<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-479AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-479AK\"></sup> too; I will not overthrow the town you speak of.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But flee there quickly, because I cannot do anything until you reach it.” (That is why the town was called Zoar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-480AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-480AL\"></sup>)",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>By the time Lot reached Zoar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-481AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-481AM\"></sup> the sun had risen over the land.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rained down burning sulfur<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-482AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-482AN\"></sup> on Sodom and Gomorrah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-482AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-482AO\"></sup>—from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of the heavens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-482AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-482AP\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Thus he overthrew those cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-483AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-483AQ\"></sup> and the entire plain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-483AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-483AR\"></sup> destroying all those living in the cities—and also the vegetation in the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-483AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-483AS\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Lot’s wife looked back,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-484AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-484AT\"></sup> and she became a pillar of salt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-484AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-484AU\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Early the next morning Abraham got up and returned to the place where he had stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-485AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-485AV\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He looked down toward Sodom and Gomorrah, toward all the land of the plain, and he saw dense smoke rising from the land, like smoke from a furnace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-486AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-486AW\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So when God destroyed the cities of the plain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-487AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-487AX\"></sup> he remembered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-487AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-487AY\"></sup> Abraham, and he brought Lot out of the catastrophe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-487AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-487AZ\"></sup> that overthrew the cities where Lot had lived.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-487BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-487BA\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Lot and his two daughters left Zoar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-488BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-488BB\"></sup> and settled in the mountains,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-488BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-488BC\"></sup> for he was afraid to stay in Zoar. He and his two daughters lived in a cave.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>One day the older daughter said to the younger, “Our father is old, and there is no man around here to give us children—as is the custom all over the earth.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Let’s get our father to drink wine and then sleep with him and preserve our family line<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-490BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-490BD\"></sup> through our father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-490BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-490BE\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>That night they got their father to drink wine, and the older daughter went in and slept with him. He was not aware of it when she lay down or when she got up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-491BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-491BF\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The next day the older daughter said to the younger, “Last night I slept with my father. Let’s get him to drink wine again tonight, and you go in and sleep with him so we can preserve our family line through our father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-492BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-492BG\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So they got their father to drink wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-493BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-493BH\"></sup> that night also, and the younger daughter went in and slept with him. Again he was not aware of it when she lay down or when she got up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-493BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-493BI\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So both of Lot’s daughters became pregnant by their father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-494BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-494BJ\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The older daughter had a son, and she named him Moab;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-495BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-495BK\"></sup> he is the father of the Moabites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-495BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-495BL\"></sup> of today.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The younger daughter also had a son, and she named him Ben-Ammi; he is the father of the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-496BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-496BM\"></sup> of today."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now Abraham moved on from there<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-497B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-497B\"></sup> into the region of the Negev<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-497C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-497C\"></sup> and lived between Kadesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-497D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-497D\"></sup> and Shur.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-497E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-497E\"></sup> For a while<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-497F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-497F\"></sup> he stayed in Gerar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-497G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-497G\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and there Abraham said of his wife Sarah, “She is my sister.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-498H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-498H\"></sup>” Then Abimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-498I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-498I\"></sup> king of Gerar sent for Sarah and took her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-498J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-498J\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But God came to Abimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-499K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-499K\"></sup> in a dream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-499L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-499L\"></sup> one night and said to him, “You are as good as dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-499M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-499M\"></sup> because of the woman you have taken; she is a married woman.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-499N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-499N\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Abimelek had not gone near her, so he said, “Lord, will you destroy an innocent nation?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-500O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-500O\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Did he not say to me, ‘She is my sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-501P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-501P\"></sup>’ and didn’t she also say, ‘He is my brother’? I have done this with a clear conscience<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-501Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-501Q\"></sup> and clean hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-501R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-501R\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then God said to him in the dream, “Yes, I know you did this with a clear conscience, and so I have kept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-502S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-502S\"></sup> you from sinning against me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-502T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-502T\"></sup> That is why I did not let you touch her.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now return the man’s wife, for he is a prophet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-503U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-503U\"></sup> and he will pray for you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-503V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-503V\"></sup> and you will live. But if you do not return her, you may be sure that you and all who belong to you will die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-503W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-503W\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Early the next morning Abimelek summoned all his officials, and when he told them all that had happened, they were very much afraid.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Abimelek called Abraham in and said, “What have you done to us? How have I wronged you that you have brought such great guilt upon me and my kingdom? You have done things to me that should never be done.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-505X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-505X\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Abimelek asked Abraham, “What was your reason for doing this?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Abraham replied, “I said to myself, ‘There is surely no fear of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-507Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-507Y\"></sup> in this place, and they will kill me because of my wife.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-507Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-507Z\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Besides, she really is my sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-508AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-508AA\"></sup> the daughter of my father though not of my mother; and she became my wife.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when God had me wander<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-509AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-509AB\"></sup> from my father’s household,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-509AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-509AC\"></sup> I said to her, ‘This is how you can show your love to me: Everywhere we go, say of me, “He is my brother.”’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Abimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-510AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-510AD\"></sup> brought sheep and cattle and male and female slaves and gave them to Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-510AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-510AE\"></sup> and he returned Sarah his wife to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Abimelek said, “My land is before you; live wherever you like.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-511AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-511AF\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To Sarah he said, “I am giving your brother a thousand shekels of silver. This is to cover the offense against you before all who are with you; you are completely vindicated.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Abraham prayed to God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-513AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-513AG\"></sup> and God healed Abimelek, his wife and his female slaves so they could have children again,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had kept all the women in Abimelek’s household from conceiving because of Abraham’s wife Sarah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-514AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-514AH\"></sup>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was gracious to Sarah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-515A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-515A\"></sup> as he had said, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did for Sarah what he had promised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-515B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-515B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sarah became pregnant and bore a son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-516C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-516C\"></sup> to Abraham in his old age,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-516D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-516D\"></sup> at the very time God had promised him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-516E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-516E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abraham gave the name Isaac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-517F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-517F\"></sup> to the son Sarah bore him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When his son Isaac was eight days old, Abraham circumcised him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-518G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-518G\"></sup> as God commanded him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Abraham was a hundred years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-519H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-519H\"></sup> when his son Isaac was born to him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Sarah said, “God has brought me laughter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-520I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-520I\"></sup> and everyone who hears about this will laugh with me.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And she added, “Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse children? Yet I have borne him a son in his old age.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-521J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-521J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The child grew and was weaned,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-522K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-522K\"></sup> and on the day Isaac was weaned Abraham held a great feast.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Sarah saw that the son whom Hagar the Egyptian had borne to Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-523L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-523L\"></sup> was mocking,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-523M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-523M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and she said to Abraham, “Get rid of that slave woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-524N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-524N\"></sup> and her son, for that woman’s son will never share in the inheritance with my son Isaac.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-524O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-524O\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The matter distressed Abraham greatly because it concerned his son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-525P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-525P\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But God said to him, “Do not be so distressed about the boy and your slave woman. Listen to whatever Sarah tells you, because it is through Isaac that your offspring will be reckoned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-526Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-526Q\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I will make the son of the slave into a nation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-527R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-527R\"></sup> also, because he is your offspring.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Early the next morning Abraham took some food and a skin of water and gave them to Hagar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-528S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-528S\"></sup> He set them on her shoulders and then sent her off with the boy. She went on her way and wandered in the Desert of Beersheba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-528T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-528T\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the water in the skin was gone, she put the boy under one of the bushes.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then she went off and sat down about a bowshot away, for she thought, “I cannot watch the boy die.” And as she sat there, she began to sob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-530U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-530U\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>God heard the boy crying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-531V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-531V\"></sup> and the angel of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-531W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-531W\"></sup> called to Hagar from heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-531X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-531X\"></sup> and said to her, “What is the matter, Hagar? Do not be afraid;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-531Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-531Y\"></sup> God has heard the boy crying as he lies there.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Lift the boy up and take him by the hand, for I will make him into a great nation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-532Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-532Z\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then God opened her eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-533AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-533AA\"></sup> and she saw a well of water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-533AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-533AB\"></sup> So she went and filled the skin with water and gave the boy a drink.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>God was with the boy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-534AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-534AC\"></sup> as he grew up. He lived in the desert and became an archer.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>While he was living in the Desert of Paran,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-535AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-535AD\"></sup> his mother got a wife for him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-535AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-535AE\"></sup> from Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>At that time Abimelek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-536AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-536AF\"></sup> and Phicol the commander of his forces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-536AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-536AG\"></sup> said to Abraham, “God is with you in everything you do.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-536AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-536AH\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now swear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-537AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-537AI\"></sup> to me here before God that you will not deal falsely with me or my children or my descendants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-537AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-537AJ\"></sup> Show to me and the country where you now reside as a foreigner the same kindness I have shown to you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-537AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-537AK\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Abraham said, “I swear it.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Abraham complained to Abimelek about a well of water that Abimelek’s servants had seized.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-539AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-539AL\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Abimelek said, “I don’t know who has done this. You did not tell me, and I heard about it only today.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Abraham brought sheep and cattle and gave them to Abimelek, and the two men made a treaty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-541AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-541AM\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Abraham set apart seven ewe lambs from the flock,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and Abimelek asked Abraham, “What is the meaning of these seven ewe lambs you have set apart by themselves?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He replied, “Accept these seven lambs from my hand as a witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-544AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-544AN\"></sup> that I dug this well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-544AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-544AO\"></sup>”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So that place was called Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-545AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-545AP\"></sup> because the two men swore an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-545AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-545AQ\"></sup> there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>After the treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-546AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-546AR\"></sup> had been made at Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-546AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-546AS\"></sup> Abimelek and Phicol the commander of his forces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-546AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-546AT\"></sup> returned to the land of the Philistines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-546AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-546AU\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Abraham planted a tamarisk tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-547AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-547AV\"></sup> in Beersheba, and there he called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-547AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-547AW\"></sup> the Eternal God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-547AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-547AX\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Abraham stayed in the land of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-548AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-548AY\"></sup> for a long time."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Some time later God tested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-549A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-549A\"></sup> Abraham. He said to him, “Abraham!”“Here I am,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-549B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-549B\"></sup> he replied.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then God said, “Take your son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-550C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-550C\"></sup>, your only son, whom you love—Isaac—and go to the region of Moriah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-550D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-550D\"></sup> Sacrifice him there as a burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-550E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-550E\"></sup> on a mountain I will show you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-550F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-550F\"></sup>”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Early the next morning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-551G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-551G\"></sup> Abraham got up and loaded his donkey. He took with him two of his servants and his son Isaac. When he had cut enough wood for the burnt offering, he set out for the place God had told him about.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On the third day Abraham looked up and saw the place in the distance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to his servants, “Stay here with the donkey while I and the boy go over there. We will worship and then we will come back to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-553H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-553H\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abraham took the wood for the burnt offering and placed it on his son Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-554I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-554I\"></sup> and he himself carried the fire and the knife.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-554J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-554J\"></sup> As the two of them went on together,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Isaac spoke up and said to his father Abraham, “Father?”“Yes, my son?” Abraham replied.“The fire and wood are here,” Isaac said, “but where is the lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-555K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-555K\"></sup> for the burnt offering?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abraham answered, “God himself will provide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-556L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-556L\"></sup> the lamb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-556M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-556M\"></sup> for the burnt offering, my son.” And the two of them went on together.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they reached the place God had told him about,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-557N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-557N\"></sup> Abraham built an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-557O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-557O\"></sup> there and arranged the wood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-557P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-557P\"></sup> on it. He bound his son Isaac and laid him on the altar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-557Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-557Q\"></sup> on top of the wood.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he reached out his hand and took the knife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-558R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-558R\"></sup> to slay his son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-558S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-558S\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-559T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-559T\"></sup> called out to him from heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-559U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-559U\"></sup> “Abraham! Abraham!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-559V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-559V\"></sup>“Here I am,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-559W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-559W\"></sup> he replied.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Do not lay a hand on the boy,” he said. “Do not do anything to him. Now I know that you fear God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-560X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-560X\"></sup> because you have not withheld from me your son, your only son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-560Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-560Y\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Abraham looked up and there in a thicket he saw a ram caught by its horns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-561Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-561Z\"></sup> He went over and took the ram and sacrificed it as a burnt offering instead of his son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-561AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-561AA\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Abraham called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-562AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-562AB\"></sup> that place The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-562AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-562AC\"></sup> Will Provide. And to this day it is said, “On the mountain of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> it will be provided.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-562AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-562AD\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-563AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-563AE\"></sup> called to Abraham from heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-563AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-563AF\"></sup> a second time",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and said, “I swear by myself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-564AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-564AG\"></sup> declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that because you have done this and have not withheld your son, your only son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-564AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-564AH\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will surely bless you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-565AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-565AI\"></sup> and make your descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-565AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-565AJ\"></sup> as numerous as the stars in the sky<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-565AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-565AK\"></sup> and as the sand on the seashore.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-565AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-565AL\"></sup> Your descendants will take possession of the cities of their enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-565AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-565AM\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and through your offspring all nations on earth will be blessed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-566AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-566AN\"></sup> because you have obeyed me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-566AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-566AO\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Abraham returned to his servants, and they set off together for Beersheba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-567AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-567AP\"></sup> And Abraham stayed in Beersheba.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Some time later Abraham was told, “Milkah is also a mother; she has borne sons to your brother Nahor:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-568AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-568AQ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Uz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-569AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-569AR\"></sup> the firstborn, Buz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-569AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-569AS\"></sup> his brother, Kemuel (the father of Aram),",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Kesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph and Bethuel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-570AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-570AT\"></sup>”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Bethuel became the father of Rebekah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-571AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-571AU\"></sup> Milkah bore these eight sons to Abraham’s brother Nahor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-571AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-571AV\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>His concubine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-572AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-572AW\"></sup> whose name was Reumah, also had sons: Tebah, Gaham, Tahash and Maakah."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Sarah lived to be a hundred and twenty-seven years old.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>She died at Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-574A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-574A\"></sup> (that is, Hebron)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-574B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-574B\"></sup> in the land of Canaan, and Abraham went to mourn for Sarah and to weep over her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-574C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-574C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Abraham rose from beside his dead wife and spoke to the Hittites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-575D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-575D\"></sup> He said,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I am a foreigner and stranger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-576E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-576E\"></sup> among you. Sell me some property for a burial site here so I can bury my dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-576F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-576F\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Hittites replied to Abraham,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Sir, listen to us. You are a mighty prince<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-578G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-578G\"></sup> among us. Bury your dead in the choicest of our tombs. None of us will refuse you his tomb for burying your dead.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Abraham rose and bowed down before the people of the land, the Hittites.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He said to them, “If you are willing to let me bury my dead, then listen to me and intercede with Ephron son of Zohar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-580H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-580H\"></sup> on my behalf",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>so he will sell me the cave of Machpelah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-581I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-581I\"></sup> which belongs to him and is at the end of his field. Ask him to sell it to me for the full price as a burial site among you.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ephron the Hittite was sitting among his people and he replied to Abraham in the hearing of all the Hittites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-582J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-582J\"></sup> who had come to the gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-582K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-582K\"></sup> of his city.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“No, my lord,” he said. “Listen to me; I give<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-583L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-583L\"></sup> you the field, and I give you the cave that is in it. I give it to you in the presence of my people. Bury your dead.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Again Abraham bowed down before the people of the land",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and he said to Ephron in their hearing, “Listen to me, if you will. I will pay the price of the field. Accept it from me so I can bury my dead there.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ephron answered Abraham,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Listen to me, my lord; the land is worth four hundred shekels of silver,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-587M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-587M\"></sup> but what is that between you and me? Bury your dead.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Abraham agreed to Ephron’s terms and weighed out for him the price he had named in the hearing of the Hittites: four hundred shekels of silver,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-588N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-588N\"></sup> according to the weight current among the merchants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-588O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-588O\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Ephron’s field in Machpelah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-589P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-589P\"></sup> near Mamre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-589Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-589Q\"></sup>—both the field and the cave in it, and all the trees within the borders of the field—was deeded",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>to Abraham as his property<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-590R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-590R\"></sup> in the presence of all the Hittites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-590S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-590S\"></sup> who had come to the gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-590T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-590T\"></sup> of the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Afterward Abraham buried his wife Sarah in the cave in the field of Machpelah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-591U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-591U\"></sup> near Mamre (which is at Hebron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-591V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-591V\"></sup>) in the land of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-591W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-591W\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So the field and the cave in it were deeded<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-592X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-592X\"></sup> to Abraham by the Hittites as a burial site.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-592Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-592Y\"></sup>"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Abraham was now very old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-593A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-593A\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-593B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-593B\"></sup> him in every way.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-593C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-593C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said to the senior servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-594D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-594D\"></sup> in his household, the one in charge of all that he had,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-594E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-594E\"></sup> “Put your hand under my thigh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-594F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-594F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I want you to swear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-595G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-595G\"></sup> by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-595H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-595H\"></sup> and the God of earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-595I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-595I\"></sup> that you will not get a wife for my son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-595J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-595J\"></sup> from the daughters of the Canaanites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-595K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-595K\"></sup> among whom I am living,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-595L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-595L\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but will go to my country and my own relatives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-596M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-596M\"></sup> and get a wife for my son Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-596N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-596N\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The servant asked him, “What if the woman is unwilling to come back with me to this land?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-597O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-597O\"></sup> Shall I then take your son back to the country you came from?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-597P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-597P\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Make sure that you do not take my son back there,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-598Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-598Q\"></sup> Abraham said.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-599R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-599R\"></sup> who brought me out of my father’s household and my native land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-599S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-599S\"></sup> and who spoke to me and promised me on oath, saying, ‘To your offspring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-599T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-599T\"></sup> I will give this land’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-599U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-599U\"></sup>—he will send his angel before you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-599V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-599V\"></sup> so that you can get a wife for my son from there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If the woman is unwilling to come back with you, then you will be released from this oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-600W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-600W\"></sup> of mine. Only do not take my son back there.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-600X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-600X\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the servant put his hand under the thigh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-601Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-601Y\"></sup> of his master<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-601Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-601Z\"></sup> Abraham and swore an oath to him concerning this matter.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the servant left, taking with him ten of his master’s camels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-602AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-602AA\"></sup> loaded with all kinds of good things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-602AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-602AB\"></sup> from his master. He set out for Aram Naharaim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-602AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-602AC\"></sup> and made his way to the town of Nahor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-602AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-602AD\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He had the camels kneel down near the well<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-603AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-603AE\"></sup> outside the town; it was toward evening, the time the women go out to draw water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-603AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-603AF\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he prayed, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of my master Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-604AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-604AG\"></sup> make me successful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-604AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-604AH\"></sup> today, and show kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-604AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-604AI\"></sup> to my master Abraham.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>See, I am standing beside this spring, and the daughters of the townspeople are coming out to draw water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-605AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-605AJ\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>May it be that when I say to a young woman, ‘Please let down your jar that I may have a drink,’ and she says, ‘Drink,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-606AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-606AK\"></sup> and I’ll water your camels too’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-606AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-606AL\"></sup>—let her be the one you have chosen for your servant Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-606AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-606AM\"></sup> By this I will know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-606AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-606AN\"></sup> that you have shown kindness to my master.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Before he had finished praying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-607AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-607AO\"></sup> Rebekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-607AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-607AP\"></sup> came out with her jar on her shoulder. She was the daughter of Bethuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-607AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-607AQ\"></sup> son of Milkah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-607AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-607AR\"></sup> who was the wife of Abraham’s brother Nahor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-607AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-607AS\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The woman was very beautiful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-608AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-608AT\"></sup> a virgin;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-608AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-608AU\"></sup> no man had ever slept with her. She went down to the spring, filled her jar and came up again.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The servant hurried to meet her and said, “Please give me a little water from your jar.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-609AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-609AV\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Drink,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-610AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-610AW\"></sup> my lord,” she said, and quickly lowered the jar to her hands and gave him a drink.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After she had given him a drink, she said, “I’ll draw water for your camels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-611AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-611AX\"></sup> too,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-611AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-611AY\"></sup> until they have had enough to drink.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So she quickly emptied her jar into the trough, ran back to the well to draw more water, and drew enough for all his camels.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-612AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-612AZ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Without saying a word, the man watched her closely to learn whether or not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made his journey successful.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-613BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-613BA\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When the camels had finished drinking, the man took out a gold nose ring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-614BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-614BB\"></sup> weighing a beka and two gold bracelets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-614BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-614BC\"></sup> weighing ten shekels.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he asked, “Whose daughter are you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-615BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-615BD\"></sup> Please tell me, is there room in your father’s house for us to spend the night?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-615BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-615BE\"></sup>”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She answered him, “I am the daughter of Bethuel, the son that Milkah bore to Nahor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-616BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-616BF\"></sup>”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And she added, “We have plenty of straw and fodder,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-617BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-617BG\"></sup> as well as room for you to spend the night.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the man bowed down and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-618BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-618BH\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>saying, “Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-619BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-619BI\"></sup> the God of my master Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-619BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-619BJ\"></sup> who has not abandoned his kindness and faithfulness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-619BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-619BK\"></sup> to my master. As for me, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has led me on the journey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-619BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-619BL\"></sup> to the house of my master’s relatives.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-619BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-619BM\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The young woman ran and told her mother’s household about these things.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-620BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-620BN\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now Rebekah had a brother named Laban,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-621BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-621BO\"></sup> and he hurried out to the man at the spring.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As soon as he had seen the nose ring, and the bracelets on his sister’s arms,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-622BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-622BP\"></sup> and had heard Rebekah tell what the man said to her, he went out to the man and found him standing by the camels near the spring.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Come, you who are blessed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-623BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-623BQ\"></sup> he said. “Why are you standing out here? I have prepared the house and a place for the camels.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So the man went to the house, and the camels were unloaded. Straw and fodder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-624BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-624BR\"></sup> were brought for the camels, and water for him and his men to wash their feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-624BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-624BS\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then food was set before him, but he said, “I will not eat until I have told you what I have to say.”“Then tell us,” Laban said.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So he said, “I am Abraham’s servant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-626BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-626BT\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-627BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-627BU\"></sup> my master abundantly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-627BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-627BV\"></sup> and he has become wealthy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-627BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-627BW\"></sup> He has given him sheep and cattle, silver and gold, male and female servants, and camels and donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-627BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-627BX\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>My master’s wife Sarah has borne him a son in her old age,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-628BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-628BY\"></sup> and he has given him everything he owns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-628BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-628BZ\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And my master made me swear an oath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-629CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-629CA\"></sup> and said, ‘You must not get a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I live,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-629CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-629CB\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>but go to my father’s family and to my own clan, and get a wife for my son.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-630CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-630CC\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“Then I asked my master, ‘What if the woman will not come back with me?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-631CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-631CD\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“He replied, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, before whom I have walked faithfully,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-632CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-632CE\"></sup> will send his angel with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-632CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-632CF\"></sup> and make your journey a success,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-632CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-632CG\"></sup> so that you can get a wife for my son from my own clan and from my father’s family.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-632CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-632CH\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You will be released from my oath if, when you go to my clan, they refuse to give her to you—then you will be released from my oath.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-633CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-633CI\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“When I came to the spring today, I said, ‘<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God of my master Abraham, if you will, please grant success<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-634CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-634CJ\"></sup> to the journey on which I have come.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>See, I am standing beside this spring.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-635CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-635CK\"></sup> If a young woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-635CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-635CL\"></sup> comes out to draw water and I say to her, “Please let me drink a little water from your jar,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-635CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-635CM\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and if she says to me, “Drink, and I’ll draw water for your camels too,” let her be the one the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen for my master’s son.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-636CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-636CN\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“Before I finished praying in my heart,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-637CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-637CO\"></sup> Rebekah came out, with her jar on her shoulder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-637CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-637CP\"></sup> She went down to the spring and drew water, and I said to her, ‘Please give me a drink.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-637CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-637CQ\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“She quickly lowered her jar from her shoulder and said, ‘Drink, and I’ll water your camels too.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-638CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-638CR\"></sup> So I drank, and she watered the camels also.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-638CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-638CS\"></sup>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“I asked her, ‘Whose daughter are you?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-639CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-639CT\"></sup>“She said, ‘The daughter of Bethuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-639CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-639CU\"></sup> son of Nahor, whom Milkah bore to him.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-639CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-639CV\"></sup>“Then I put the ring in her nose<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-639CW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CW&quot;&gt;CW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-639CW\"></sup> and the bracelets on her arms,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-639CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-639CX\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and I bowed down and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-640CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-640CY\"></sup> I praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my master Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-640CZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CZ&quot;&gt;CZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-640CZ\"></sup> who had led me on the right road to get the granddaughter of my master’s brother for his son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-640DA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DA&quot;&gt;DA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-640DA\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Now if you will show kindness and faithfulness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-641DB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DB&quot;&gt;DB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-641DB\"></sup> to my master, tell me; and if not, tell me, so I may know which way to turn.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Laban and Bethuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-642DC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DC&quot;&gt;DC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-642DC\"></sup> answered, “This is from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-642DD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DD&quot;&gt;DD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-642DD\"></sup> we can say nothing to you one way or the other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-642DE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DE&quot;&gt;DE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-642DE\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Here is Rebekah; take her and go, and let her become the wife of your master’s son, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has directed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-643DF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DF&quot;&gt;DF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-643DF\"></sup>”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>When Abraham’s servant heard what they said, he bowed down to the ground before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-644DG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DG&quot;&gt;DG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-644DG\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Then the servant brought out gold and silver jewelry and articles of clothing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-645DH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DH&quot;&gt;DH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-645DH\"></sup> and gave them to Rebekah; he also gave costly gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-645DI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DI&quot;&gt;DI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-645DI\"></sup> to her brother and to her mother.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Then he and the men who were with him ate and drank and spent the night there.When they got up the next morning, he said, “Send me on my way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-646DJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DJ&quot;&gt;DJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-646DJ\"></sup> to my master.”",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But her brother and her mother replied, “Let the young woman remain with us ten days or so;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-647DK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DK&quot;&gt;DK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-647DK\"></sup> then you may go.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>But he said to them, “Do not detain me, now that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has granted success<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-648DL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DL&quot;&gt;DL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-648DL\"></sup> to my journey. Send me on my way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-648DM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DM&quot;&gt;DM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-648DM\"></sup> so I may go to my master.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Then they said, “Let’s call the young woman and ask her about it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-649DN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DN&quot;&gt;DN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-649DN\"></sup>",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>So they called Rebekah and asked her, “Will you go with this man?”“I will go,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-650DO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DO&quot;&gt;DO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-650DO\"></sup> she said.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>So they sent their sister Rebekah on her way,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-651DP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DP&quot;&gt;DP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-651DP\"></sup> along with her nurse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-651DQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DQ&quot;&gt;DQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-651DQ\"></sup> and Abraham’s servant and his men.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>And they blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-652DR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DR&quot;&gt;DR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-652DR\"></sup> Rebekah and said to her,“Our sister, may you increaseto thousands upon thousands;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-652DS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DS&quot;&gt;DS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-652DS\"></sup>may your offspring possessthe cities of their enemies.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-652DT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DT&quot;&gt;DT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-652DT\"></sup>",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Then Rebekah and her attendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-653DU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DU&quot;&gt;DU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-653DU\"></sup> got ready and mounted the camels and went back with the man. So the servant took Rebekah and left.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Now Isaac had come from Beer Lahai Roi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-654DV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DV&quot;&gt;DV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-654DV\"></sup> for he was living in the Negev.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-654DW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DW&quot;&gt;DW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-654DW\"></sup>",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>He went out to the field one evening to meditate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-655DX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DX&quot;&gt;DX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-655DX\"></sup> and as he looked up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-655DY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DY&quot;&gt;DY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-655DY\"></sup> he saw camels approaching.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>Rebekah also looked up and saw Isaac. She got down from her camel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-656DZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DZ&quot;&gt;DZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-656DZ\"></sup>",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>and asked the servant, “Who is that man in the field coming to meet us?”“He is my master,” the servant answered. So she took her veil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-657EA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference EA&quot;&gt;EA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-657EA\"></sup> and covered herself.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>Then the servant told Isaac all he had done.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>Isaac brought her into the tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-659EB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference EB&quot;&gt;EB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-659EB\"></sup> of his mother Sarah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-659EC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference EC&quot;&gt;EC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-659EC\"></sup> and he married Rebekah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-659ED&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference ED&quot;&gt;ED&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-659ED\"></sup> So she became his wife, and he loved her;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-659EE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference EE&quot;&gt;EE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-659EE\"></sup> and Isaac was comforted after his mother’s death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-659EF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference EF&quot;&gt;EF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-659EF\"></sup>"
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Abraham had taken another wife, whose name was Keturah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>She bore him Zimran,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-661B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-661B\"></sup> Jokshan, Medan, Midian,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-661C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-661C\"></sup> Ishbak and Shuah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-661D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-661D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jokshan was the father of Sheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-662E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-662E\"></sup> and Dedan;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-662F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-662F\"></sup> the descendants of Dedan were the Ashurites, the Letushites and the Leummites.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Midian were Ephah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-663G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-663G\"></sup> Epher, Hanok, Abida and Eldaah. All these were descendants of Keturah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Abraham left everything he owned to Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-664H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-664H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But while he was still living, he gave gifts to the sons of his concubines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-665I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-665I\"></sup> and sent them away from his son Isaac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-665J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-665J\"></sup> to the land of the east.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-665K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-665K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Abraham lived a hundred and seventy-five years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-666L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-666L\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Abraham breathed his last and died at a good old age,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-667M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-667M\"></sup> an old man and full of years; and he was gathered to his people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-667N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-667N\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>His sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-668O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-668O\"></sup> in the cave of Machpelah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-668P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-668P\"></sup> near Mamre,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-668Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-668Q\"></sup> in the field of Ephron<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-668R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-668R\"></sup> son of Zohar the Hittite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-668S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-668S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the field Abraham had bought from the Hittites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-669T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-669T\"></sup> There Abraham was buried with his wife Sarah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>After Abraham’s death, God blessed his son Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-670U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-670U\"></sup> who then lived near Beer Lahai Roi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-670V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-670V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-671X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-671X\"></sup> of the family line of Abraham’s son Ishmael, whom Sarah’s slave, Hagar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-671Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-671Y\"></sup> the Egyptian, bore to Abraham.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-671Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-671Z\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>These are the names of the sons of Ishmael, listed in the order of their birth: Nebaioth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-672AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-672AA\"></sup> the firstborn of Ishmael, Kedar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-672AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-672AB\"></sup> Adbeel, Mibsam,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Mishma, Dumah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-673AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-673AC\"></sup> Massa,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hadad, Tema,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-674AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-674AD\"></sup> Jetur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-674AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-674AE\"></sup> Naphish and Kedemah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These were the sons of Ishmael, and these are the names of the twelve tribal rulers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-675AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-675AF\"></sup> according to their settlements and camps.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-675AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-675AG\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Ishmael lived a hundred and thirty-seven years. He breathed his last and died, and he was gathered to his people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-676AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-676AH\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>His descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-677AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-677AI\"></sup> settled in the area from Havilah to Shur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-677AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-677AJ\"></sup> near the eastern border of Egypt, as you go toward Ashur. And they lived in hostility toward all the tribes related to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-677AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-677AK\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-678AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-678AL\"></sup> of the family line of Abraham’s son Isaac.Abraham became the father of Isaac,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Isaac was forty years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-679AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-679AM\"></sup> when he married Rebekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-679AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-679AN\"></sup> daughter of Bethuel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-679AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-679AO\"></sup> the Aramean from Paddan Aram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-679AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-679AP\"></sup> and sister of Laban<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-679AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-679AQ\"></sup> the Aramean.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-679AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-679AR\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Isaac prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on behalf of his wife, because she was childless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-680AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-680AS\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered his prayer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-680AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-680AT\"></sup> and his wife Rebekah became pregnant.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The babies jostled each other within her, and she said, “Why is this happening to me?” So she went to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-681AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-681AU\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her,“Two nations<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-682AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-682AV\"></sup> are in your womb,and two peoples from within you will be separated;one people will be stronger than the other,and the older will serve the younger.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-682AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-682AW\"></sup>”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When the time came for her to give birth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-683AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-683AX\"></sup> there were twin boys in her womb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-683AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-683AY\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The first to come out was red,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-684AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-684AZ\"></sup> and his whole body was like a hairy garment;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-684BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-684BA\"></sup> so they named him Esau.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-684BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-684BB\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>After this, his brother came out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-685BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-685BC\"></sup> with his hand grasping Esau’s heel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-685BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-685BD\"></sup> so he was named Jacob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-685BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-685BE\"></sup> Isaac was sixty years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-685BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-685BF\"></sup> when Rebekah gave birth to them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The boys grew up, and Esau became a skillful hunter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-686BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-686BG\"></sup> a man of the open country,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-686BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-686BH\"></sup> while Jacob was content to stay at home among the tents.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Isaac, who had a taste for wild game,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-687BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-687BI\"></sup> loved Esau, but Rebekah loved Jacob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-687BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-687BJ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Once when Jacob was cooking some stew,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-688BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-688BK\"></sup> Esau came in from the open country,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-688BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-688BL\"></sup> famished.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He said to Jacob, “Quick, let me have some of that red stew!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-689BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-689BM\"></sup> I’m famished!” (That is why he was also called Edom.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-689BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-689BN\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jacob replied, “First sell me your birthright.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-690BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-690BO\"></sup>”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Look, I am about to die,” Esau said. “What good is the birthright to me?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But Jacob said, “Swear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-692BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-692BP\"></sup> to me first.” So he swore an oath to him, selling his birthright<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-692BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-692BQ\"></sup> to Jacob.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jacob gave Esau some bread and some lentil stew.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-693BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-693BR\"></sup> He ate and drank, and then got up and left.So Esau despised his birthright."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Now there was a famine in the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-694B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-694B\"></sup>—besides the previous famine in Abraham’s time—and Isaac went to Abimelek king of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-694C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-694C\"></sup> in Gerar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-694D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-694D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-695E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-695E\"></sup> to Isaac and said, “Do not go down to Egypt;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-695F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-695F\"></sup> live in the land where I tell you to live.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-695G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-695G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Stay in this land for a while,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-696H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-696H\"></sup> and I will be with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-696I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-696I\"></sup> and will bless you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-696J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-696J\"></sup> For to you and your descendants I will give all these lands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-696K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-696K\"></sup> and will confirm the oath I swore to your father Abraham.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-696L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-696L\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will make your descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-697M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-697M\"></sup> as numerous as the stars in the sky<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-697N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-697N\"></sup> and will give them all these lands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-697O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-697O\"></sup> and through your offspring all nations on earth will be blessed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-697P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-697P\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>because Abraham obeyed me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-698Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-698Q\"></sup> and did everything I required of him, keeping my commands, my decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-698R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-698R\"></sup> and my instructions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-698S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-698S\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Isaac stayed in Gerar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-699T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-699T\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the men of that place asked him about his wife, he said, “She is my sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-700U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-700U\"></sup>” because he was afraid to say, “She is my wife.” He thought, “The men of this place might kill me on account of Rebekah, because she is beautiful.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Isaac had been there a long time, Abimelek king of the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-701V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-701V\"></sup> looked down from a window and saw Isaac caressing his wife Rebekah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Abimelek summoned Isaac and said, “She is really your wife! Why did you say, ‘She is my sister’?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-702W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-702W\"></sup>”Isaac answered him, “Because I thought I might lose my life on account of her.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Abimelek said, “What is this you have done to us?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-703X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-703X\"></sup> One of the men might well have slept with your wife, and you would have brought guilt upon us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Abimelek gave orders to all the people: “Anyone who harms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-704Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-704Y\"></sup> this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-704Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-704Z\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Isaac planted crops in that land and the same year reaped a hundredfold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-705AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-705AA\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-705AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-705AB\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The man became rich, and his wealth continued to grow until he became very wealthy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-706AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-706AC\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He had so many flocks and herds and servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-707AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-707AD\"></sup> that the Philistines envied him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-707AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-707AE\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So all the wells<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-708AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-708AF\"></sup> that his father’s servants had dug in the time of his father Abraham, the Philistines stopped up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-708AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-708AG\"></sup> filling them with earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Abimelek said to Isaac, “Move away from us;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-709AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-709AH\"></sup> you have become too powerful for us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-709AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-709AI\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Isaac moved away from there and encamped in the Valley of Gerar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-710AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-710AJ\"></sup> where he settled.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Isaac reopened the wells<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-711AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-711AK\"></sup> that had been dug in the time of his father Abraham, which the Philistines had stopped up after Abraham died, and he gave them the same names his father had given them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Isaac’s servants dug in the valley and discovered a well of fresh water there.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But the herders of Gerar quarreled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-713AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-713AL\"></sup> with those of Isaac and said, “The water is ours!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-713AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-713AM\"></sup> So he named the well Esek, because they disputed with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they dug another well, but they quarreled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-714AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-714AN\"></sup> over that one also; so he named it Sitnah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He moved on from there and dug another well, and no one quarreled over it. He named it Rehoboth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-715AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-715AO\"></sup> saying, “Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given us room<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-715AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-715AP\"></sup> and we will flourish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-715AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-715AQ\"></sup> in the land.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>From there he went up to Beersheba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-716AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-716AR\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>That night the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him and said, “I am the God of your father Abraham.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-717AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-717AS\"></sup> Do not be afraid,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-717AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-717AT\"></sup> for I am with you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-717AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-717AU\"></sup> I will bless you and will increase the number of your descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-717AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-717AV\"></sup> for the sake of my servant Abraham.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-717AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-717AW\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Isaac built an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-718AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-718AX\"></sup> there and called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-718AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-718AY\"></sup> There he pitched his tent, and there his servants dug a well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-718AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-718AZ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Meanwhile, Abimelek had come to him from Gerar, with Ahuzzath his personal adviser and Phicol the commander of his forces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-719BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-719BA\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Isaac asked them, “Why have you come to me, since you were hostile to me and sent me away?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-720BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-720BB\"></sup>”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They answered, “We saw clearly that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-721BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-721BC\"></sup> so we said, ‘There ought to be a sworn agreement between us’—between us and you. Let us make a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-721BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-721BD\"></sup> with you",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>that you will do us no harm,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-722BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-722BE\"></sup> just as we did not harm you but always treated you well and sent you away peacefully. And now you are blessed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-722BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-722BF\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Isaac then made a feast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-723BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-723BG\"></sup> for them, and they ate and drank.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Early the next morning the men swore an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-724BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-724BH\"></sup> to each other. Then Isaac sent them on their way, and they went away peacefully.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>That day Isaac’s servants came and told him about the well<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-725BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-725BI\"></sup> they had dug. They said, “We’ve found water!”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He called it Shibah, and to this day the name of the town has been Beersheba.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-726BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-726BJ\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Esau was forty years old,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-727BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-727BK\"></sup> he married Judith daughter of Beeri the Hittite, and also Basemath daughter of Elon the Hittite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-727BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-727BL\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They were a source of grief to Isaac and Rebekah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-728BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-728BM\"></sup>"
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>When Isaac was old and his eyes were so weak that he could no longer see,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-729A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-729A\"></sup> he called for Esau his older son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-729B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-729B\"></sup> and said to him, “My son.”“Here I am,” he answered.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Isaac said, “I am now an old man and don’t know the day of my death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-730C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-730C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now then, get your equipment—your quiver and bow—and go out to the open country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-731D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-731D\"></sup> to hunt some wild game for me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Prepare me the kind of tasty food I like<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-732E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-732E\"></sup> and bring it to me to eat, so that I may give you my blessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-732F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-732F\"></sup> before I die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-732G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-732G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Rebekah was listening as Isaac spoke to his son Esau. When Esau left for the open country<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-733H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-733H\"></sup> to hunt game and bring it back,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Rebekah said to her son Jacob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-734I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-734I\"></sup> “Look, I overheard your father say to your brother Esau,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘Bring me some game and prepare me some tasty food to eat, so that I may give you my blessing in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before I die.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-735J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-735J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now, my son, listen carefully and do what I tell you:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-736K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-736K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Go out to the flock and bring me two choice young goats,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-737L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-737L\"></sup> so I can prepare some tasty food for your father, just the way he likes it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-737M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-737M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then take it to your father to eat, so that he may give you his blessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-738N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-738N\"></sup> before he dies.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, “But my brother Esau is a hairy man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-739O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-739O\"></sup> while I have smooth skin.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>What if my father touches me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-740P\"></sup> I would appear to be tricking him and would bring down a curse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-740Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-740Q\"></sup> on myself rather than a blessing.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>His mother said to him, “My son, let the curse fall on me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-741R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-741R\"></sup> Just do what I say;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-741S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-741S\"></sup> go and get them for me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went and got them and brought them to his mother, and she prepared some tasty food, just the way his father liked it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-742T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-742T\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Rebekah took the best clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-743U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-743U\"></sup> of Esau her older son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-743V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-743V\"></sup> which she had in the house, and put them on her younger son Jacob.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>She also covered his hands and the smooth part of his neck with the goatskins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-744W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-744W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then she handed to her son Jacob the tasty food and the bread she had made.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He went to his father and said, “My father.”“Yes, my son,” he answered. “Who is it?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-746X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-746X\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jacob said to his father, “I am Esau your firstborn.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-747Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-747Y\"></sup> I have done as you told me. Please sit up and eat some of my game,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-747Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-747Z\"></sup> so that you may give me your blessing.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-747AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-747AA\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Isaac asked his son, “How did you find it so quickly, my son?”“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gave me success,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-748AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-748AB\"></sup>” he replied.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Isaac said to Jacob, “Come near so I can touch you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-749AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-749AC\"></sup> my son, to know whether you really are my son Esau or not.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Jacob went close to his father Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-750AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-750AD\"></sup> who touched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-750AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-750AE\"></sup> him and said, “The voice is the voice of Jacob, but the hands are the hands of Esau.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He did not recognize him, for his hands were hairy like those of his brother Esau;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-751AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-751AF\"></sup> so he proceeded to bless him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Are you really my son Esau?” he asked.“I am,” he replied.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then he said, “My son, bring me some of your game to eat, so that I may give you my blessing.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-753AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-753AG\"></sup>Jacob brought it to him and he ate; and he brought some wine and he drank.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then his father Isaac said to him, “Come here, my son, and kiss me.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So he went to him and kissed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-755AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-755AH\"></sup> him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-755AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-755AI\"></sup>. When Isaac caught the smell of his clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-755AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-755AJ\"></sup> he blessed him and said,“Ah, the smell of my sonis like the smell of a fieldthat the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-755AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-755AK\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>May God give you heaven’s dew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-756AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-756AL\"></sup>and earth’s richness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-756AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-756AM\"></sup>—an abundance of grain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-756AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-756AN\"></sup> and new wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-756AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-756AO\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>May nations serve youand peoples bow down to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-757AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-757AP\"></sup>Be lord over your brothers,and may the sons of your mother bow down to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-757AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-757AQ\"></sup>May those who curse you be cursedand those who bless you be blessed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-757AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-757AR\"></sup>”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>After Isaac finished blessing him, and Jacob had scarcely left his father’s presence, his brother Esau came in from hunting.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He too prepared some tasty food and brought it to his father. Then he said to him, “My father, please sit up and eat some of my game, so that you may give me your blessing.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-759AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-759AS\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>His father Isaac asked him, “Who are you?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-760AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-760AT\"></sup>“I am your son,” he answered, “your firstborn, Esau.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-760AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-760AU\"></sup>”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Isaac trembled violently and said, “Who was it, then, that hunted game and brought it to me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-761AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-761AV\"></sup> I ate it just before you came and I blessed him—and indeed he will be blessed!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-761AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-761AW\"></sup>”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Esau heard his father’s words, he burst out with a loud and bitter cry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-762AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-762AX\"></sup> and said to his father, “Bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-762AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-762AY\"></sup> me—me too, my father!”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But he said, “Your brother came deceitfully<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-763AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-763AZ\"></sup> and took your blessing.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-763BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-763BA\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Esau said, “Isn’t he rightly named Jacob?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-764BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-764BB\"></sup> This is the second time he has taken advantage of<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-764BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-764BC\"></sup> me: He took my birthright,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-764BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-764BD\"></sup> and now he’s taken my blessing!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-764BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-764BE\"></sup> Then he asked, “Haven’t you reserved any blessing for me?”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Isaac answered Esau, “I have made him lord over you and have made all his relatives his servants, and I have sustained him with grain and new wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-765BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-765BF\"></sup> So what can I possibly do for you, my son?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Esau said to his father, “Do you have only one blessing, my father? Bless me too, my father!” Then Esau wept aloud.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-766BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-766BG\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>His father Isaac answered him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-767BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-767BH\"></sup>“Your dwelling will beaway from the earth’s richness,away from the dew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-767BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-767BI\"></sup> of heaven above.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-767BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-767BJ\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You will live by the swordand you will serve<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-768BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-768BK\"></sup> your brother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-768BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-768BL\"></sup>But when you grow restless,you will throw his yokefrom off your neck.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-768BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-768BM\"></sup>”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Esau held a grudge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-769BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-769BN\"></sup> against Jacob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-769BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-769BO\"></sup> because of the blessing his father had given him. He said to himself, “The days of mourning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-769BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-769BP\"></sup> for my father are near; then I will kill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-769BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-769BQ\"></sup> my brother Jacob.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-769BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-769BR\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>When Rebekah was told what her older son Esau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-770BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-770BS\"></sup> had said, she sent for her younger son Jacob and said to him, “Your brother Esau is planning to avenge himself by killing you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-770BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-770BT\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Now then, my son, do what I say:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-771BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-771BU\"></sup> Flee at once to my brother Laban<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-771BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-771BV\"></sup> in Harran.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-771BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-771BW\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Stay with him for a while<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-772BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-772BX\"></sup> until your brother’s fury subsides.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When your brother is no longer angry with you and forgets what you did to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-773BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-773BY\"></sup> I’ll send word for you to come back from there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-773BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-773BZ\"></sup> Why should I lose both of you in one day?”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then Rebekah said to Isaac, “I’m disgusted with living because of these Hittite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-774CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-774CA\"></sup> women. If Jacob takes a wife from among the women of this land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-774CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-774CB\"></sup> from Hittite women like these, my life will not be worth living.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-774CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-774CC\"></sup>"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>So Isaac called for Jacob and blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-775A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-775A\"></sup> him. Then he commanded him: “Do not marry a Canaanite woman.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-775B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-775B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Go at once to Paddan Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-776C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-776C\"></sup> to the house of your mother’s father Bethuel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-776D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-776D\"></sup> Take a wife for yourself there, from among the daughters of Laban, your mother’s brother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-776E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-776E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May God Almighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-777F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-777F\"></sup> bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-777G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-777G\"></sup> you and make you fruitful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-777H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-777H\"></sup> and increase your numbers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-777I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-777I\"></sup> until you become a community of peoples.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>May he give you and your descendants the blessing given to Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-778J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-778J\"></sup> so that you may take possession of the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-778K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-778K\"></sup> where you now reside as a foreigner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-778L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-778L\"></sup> the land God gave to Abraham.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Isaac sent Jacob on his way,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-779M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-779M\"></sup> and he went to Paddan Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-779N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-779N\"></sup> to Laban son of Bethuel the Aramean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-779O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-779O\"></sup> the brother of Rebekah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-779P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-779P\"></sup> who was the mother of Jacob and Esau.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Esau learned that Isaac had blessed Jacob and had sent him to Paddan Aram to take a wife from there, and that when he blessed him he commanded him, “Do not marry a Canaanite woman,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-780Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-780Q\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and that Jacob had obeyed his father and mother and had gone to Paddan Aram.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Esau then realized how displeasing the Canaanite women<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-782R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-782R\"></sup> were to his father Isaac;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-782S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-782S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>so he went to Ishmael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-783T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-783T\"></sup> and married Mahalath, the sister of Nebaioth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-783U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-783U\"></sup> and daughter of Ishmael son of Abraham, in addition to the wives he already had.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-783V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-783V\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jacob left Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-784W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-784W\"></sup> and set out for Harran.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-784X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-784X\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When he reached a certain place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-785Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-785Y\"></sup> he stopped for the night because the sun had set. Taking one of the stones there, he put it under his head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-785Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-785Z\"></sup> and lay down to sleep.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He had a dream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-786AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-786AA\"></sup> in which he saw a stairway resting on the earth, with its top reaching to heaven, and the angels of God were ascending and descending on it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-786AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-786AB\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>There above it stood the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-787AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-787AC\"></sup> and he said: “I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your father Abraham and the God of Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-787AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-787AD\"></sup> I will give you and your descendants the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-787AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-787AE\"></sup> on which you are lying.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-787AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-787AF\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Your descendants will be like the dust of the earth, and you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-788AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-788AG\"></sup> will spread out to the west and to the east, to the north and to the south.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-788AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-788AH\"></sup> All peoples on earth will be blessed through you and your offspring.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-788AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-788AI\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I am with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AJ\"></sup> and will watch over you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AK\"></sup> wherever you go,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AL\"></sup> and I will bring you back to this land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AM\"></sup> I will not leave you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AN\"></sup> until I have done what I have promised you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AO\"></sup>”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-789AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-789AP\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Jacob awoke from his sleep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-790AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-790AQ\"></sup> he thought, “Surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is in this place, and I was not aware of it.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He was afraid and said, “How awesome is this place!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-791AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-791AR\"></sup> This is none other than the house of God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-791AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-791AS\"></sup> this is the gate of heaven.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Early the next morning Jacob took the stone he had placed under his head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-792AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-792AT\"></sup> and set it up as a pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-792AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-792AU\"></sup> and poured oil on top of it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-792AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-792AV\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He called that place Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-793AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-793AW\"></sup> though the city used to be called Luz.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-793AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-793AX\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Jacob made a vow,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-794AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-794AY\"></sup> saying, “If God will be with me and will watch over me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-794AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-794AZ\"></sup> on this journey I am taking and will give me food to eat and clothes to wear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-794BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-794BA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>so that I return safely<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-795BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-795BB\"></sup> to my father’s household,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-795BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-795BC\"></sup> then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be my God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-795BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-795BD\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and this stone that I have set up as a pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-796BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-796BE\"></sup> will be God’s house,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-796BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-796BF\"></sup> and of all that you give me I will give you a tenth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-796BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-796BG\"></sup>”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Then Jacob continued on his journey and came to the land of the eastern peoples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-797A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-797A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There he saw a well in the open country, with three flocks of sheep lying near it because the flocks were watered from that well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-798B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-798B\"></sup> The stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-798C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-798C\"></sup> over the mouth of the well was large.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the flocks were gathered there, the shepherds would roll the stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-799D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-799D\"></sup> away from the well’s mouth and water the sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-799E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-799E\"></sup> Then they would return the stone to its place over the mouth of the well.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jacob asked the shepherds, “My brothers, where are you from?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-800F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-800F\"></sup>“We’re from Harran,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-800G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-800G\"></sup>” they replied.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “Do you know Laban, Nahor’s grandson?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-801H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-801H\"></sup>“Yes, we know him,” they answered.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Jacob asked them, “Is he well?”“Yes, he is,” they said, “and here comes his daughter Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-802I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-802I\"></sup> with the sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-802J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-802J\"></sup>”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Look,” he said, “the sun is still high; it is not time for the flocks to be gathered. Water the sheep and take them back to pasture.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“We can’t,” they replied, “until all the flocks are gathered and the stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-804K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-804K\"></sup> has been rolled away from the mouth of the well. Then we will water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-804L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-804L\"></sup> the sheep.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>While he was still talking with them, Rachel came with her father’s sheep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-805M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-805M\"></sup> for she was a shepherd.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Jacob saw Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-806N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-806N\"></sup> daughter of his uncle Laban, and Laban’s sheep, he went over and rolled the stone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-806O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-806O\"></sup> away from the mouth of the well and watered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-806P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-806P\"></sup> his uncle’s sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-806Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-806Q\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Jacob kissed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-807R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-807R\"></sup> Rachel and began to weep aloud.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-807S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-807S\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He had told Rachel that he was a relative<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-808T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-808T\"></sup> of her father and a son of Rebekah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-808U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-808U\"></sup> So she ran and told her father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-808V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-808V\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As soon as Laban<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-809W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-809W\"></sup> heard the news about Jacob, his sister’s son, he hurried to meet him. He embraced him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-809X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-809X\"></sup> and kissed him and brought him to his home, and there Jacob told him all these things.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Laban said to him, “You are my own flesh and blood.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-810Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-810Y\"></sup>After Jacob had stayed with him for a whole month,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Laban said to him, “Just because you are a relative<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-811Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-811Z\"></sup> of mine, should you work for me for nothing? Tell me what your wages<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-811AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-811AA\"></sup> should be.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Laban had two daughters; the name of the older was Leah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-812AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-812AB\"></sup> and the name of the younger was Rachel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-812AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-812AC\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Leah had weak eyes, but Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-813AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-813AD\"></sup> had a lovely figure and was beautiful.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-813AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-813AE\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jacob was in love with Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-814AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-814AF\"></sup> and said, “I’ll work for you seven years in return for your younger daughter Rachel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-814AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-814AG\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Laban said, “It’s better that I give her to you than to some other man. Stay here with me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Jacob served seven years to get Rachel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-816AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-816AH\"></sup> but they seemed like only a few days to him because of his love for her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-816AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-816AI\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Jacob said to Laban, “Give me my wife. My time is completed, and I want to make love to her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-817AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-817AJ\"></sup>”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Laban brought together all the people of the place and gave a feast.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-818AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-818AK\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But when evening came, he took his daughter Leah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-819AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-819AL\"></sup> and brought her to Jacob, and Jacob made love to her.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Laban gave his servant Zilpah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-820AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-820AM\"></sup> to his daughter as her attendant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-820AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-820AN\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When morning came, there was Leah! So Jacob said to Laban, “What is this you have done to me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-821AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-821AO\"></sup> I served you for Rachel, didn’t I? Why have you deceived me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-821AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-821AP\"></sup>”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Laban replied, “It is not our custom here to give the younger daughter in marriage before the older one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-822AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-822AQ\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Finish this daughter’s bridal week;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-823AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-823AR\"></sup> then we will give you the younger one also, in return for another seven years of work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-823AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-823AS\"></sup>”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Jacob did so. He finished the week with Leah, and then Laban gave him his daughter Rachel to be his wife.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-824AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-824AT\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Laban gave his servant Bilhah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-825AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-825AU\"></sup> to his daughter Rachel as her attendant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-825AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-825AV\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Jacob made love to Rachel also, and his love for Rachel was greater than his love for Leah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-826AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-826AW\"></sup> And he worked for Laban another seven years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-826AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-826AX\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that Leah was not loved,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-827AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-827AY\"></sup> he enabled her to conceive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-827AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-827AZ\"></sup> but Rachel remained childless.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Leah became pregnant and gave birth to a son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-828BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-828BA\"></sup> She named him Reuben,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-828BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-828BB\"></sup> for she said, “It is because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has seen my misery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-828BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-828BC\"></sup> Surely my husband will love me now.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>She conceived again, and when she gave birth to a son she said, “Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard that I am not loved,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-829BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-829BD\"></sup> he gave me this one too.” So she named him Simeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-829BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-829BE\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Again she conceived, and when she gave birth to a son she said, “Now at last my husband will become attached to me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-830BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-830BF\"></sup> because I have borne him three sons.” So he was named Levi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-830BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-830BG\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>She conceived again, and when she gave birth to a son she said, “This time I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” So she named him Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-831BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-831BH\"></sup> Then she stopped having children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-831BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-831BI\"></sup>"
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>When Rachel saw that she was not bearing Jacob any children,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-832A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-832A\"></sup> she became jealous of her sister.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-832B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-832B\"></sup> So she said to Jacob, “Give me children, or I’ll die!”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jacob became angry with her and said, “Am I in the place of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-833C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-833C\"></sup> who has kept you from having children?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-833D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-833D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then she said, “Here is Bilhah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-834E\"></sup> my servant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-834F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-834F\"></sup> Sleep with her so that she can bear children for me and I too can build a family through her.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-834G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-834G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So she gave him her servant Bilhah as a wife.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-835H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-835H\"></sup> Jacob slept with her,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-835I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-835I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and she became pregnant and bore him a son.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Rachel said, “God has vindicated me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-837J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-837J\"></sup> he has listened to my plea and given me a son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-837K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-837K\"></sup> Because of this she named him Dan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-837L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-837L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Rachel’s servant Bilhah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-838M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-838M\"></sup> conceived again and bore Jacob a second son.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Rachel said, “I have had a great struggle with my sister, and I have won.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-839N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-839N\"></sup> So she named him Naphtali.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-839O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-839O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Leah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-840P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-840P\"></sup> saw that she had stopped having children,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-840Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-840Q\"></sup> she took her servant Zilpah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-840R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-840R\"></sup> and gave her to Jacob as a wife.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-840S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-840S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Leah’s servant Zilpah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-841T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-841T\"></sup> bore Jacob a son.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Leah said, “What good fortune!” So she named him Gad.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-842U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-842U\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Leah’s servant Zilpah bore Jacob a second son.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Leah said, “How happy I am! The women will call me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-844V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-844V\"></sup> happy.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-844W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-844W\"></sup> So she named him Asher.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-844X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-844X\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>During wheat harvest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-845Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-845Y\"></sup> Reuben went out into the fields and found some mandrake plants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-845Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-845Z\"></sup> which he brought to his mother Leah. Rachel said to Leah, “Please give me some of your son’s mandrakes.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But she said to her, “Wasn’t it enough<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-846AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-846AA\"></sup> that you took away my husband? Will you take my son’s mandrakes too?”“Very well,” Rachel said, “he can sleep with you tonight in return for your son’s mandrakes.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-846AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-846AB\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So when Jacob came in from the fields that evening, Leah went out to meet him. “You must sleep with me,” she said. “I have hired you with my son’s mandrakes.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-847AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-847AC\"></sup> So he slept with her that night.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>God listened to Leah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-848AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-848AD\"></sup> and she became pregnant and bore Jacob a fifth son.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Leah said, “God has rewarded me for giving my servant to my husband.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-849AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-849AE\"></sup> So she named him Issachar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-849AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-849AF\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Leah conceived again and bore Jacob a sixth son.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Leah said, “God has presented me with a precious gift. This time my husband will treat me with honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-851AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-851AG\"></sup> because I have borne him six sons.” So she named him Zebulun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-851AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-851AH\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Some time later she gave birth to a daughter and named her Dinah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-852AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-852AI\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then God remembered Rachel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-853AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-853AJ\"></sup> he listened to her<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-853AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-853AK\"></sup> and enabled her to conceive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-853AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-853AL\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>She became pregnant and gave birth to a son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-854AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-854AM\"></sup> and said, “God has taken away my disgrace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-854AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-854AN\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She named him Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-855AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-855AO\"></sup> and said, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> add to me another son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-855AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-855AP\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>After Rachel gave birth to Joseph, Jacob said to Laban, “Send me on my way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-856AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-856AQ\"></sup> so I can go back to my own homeland.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-856AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-856AR\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Give me my wives and children, for whom I have served you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-857AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-857AS\"></sup> and I will be on my way. You know how much work I’ve done for you.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Laban said to him, “If I have found favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-858AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-858AT\"></sup> please stay. I have learned by divination<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-858AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-858AU\"></sup> that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed me because of you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-858AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-858AV\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He added, “Name your wages,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-859AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-859AW\"></sup> and I will pay them.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jacob said to him, “You know how I have worked for you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-860AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-860AX\"></sup> and how your livestock has fared under my care.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-860AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-860AY\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The little you had before I came has increased greatly, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed you wherever I have been.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-861AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-861AZ\"></sup> But now, when may I do something for my own household?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-861BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-861BA\"></sup>”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“What shall I give you?” he asked.“Don’t give me anything,” Jacob replied. “But if you will do this one thing for me, I will go on tending your flocks and watching over them:",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Let me go through all your flocks today and remove from them every speckled or spotted sheep, every dark-colored lamb and every spotted or speckled goat.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-863BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-863BB\"></sup> They will be my wages.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-863BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-863BC\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And my honesty will testify for me in the future, whenever you check on the wages you have paid me. Any goat in my possession that is not speckled or spotted, or any lamb that is not dark-colored,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-864BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-864BD\"></sup> will be considered stolen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-864BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-864BE\"></sup>”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Agreed,” said Laban. “Let it be as you have said.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>That same day he removed all the male goats that were streaked or spotted, and all the speckled or spotted female goats (all that had white on them) and all the dark-colored lambs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-866BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-866BF\"></sup> and he placed them in the care of his sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-866BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-866BG\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then he put a three-day journey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-867BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-867BH\"></sup> between himself and Jacob, while Jacob continued to tend the rest of Laban’s flocks.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Jacob, however, took fresh-cut branches from poplar, almond<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-868BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-868BI\"></sup> and plane trees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-868BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-868BJ\"></sup> and made white stripes on them by peeling the bark and exposing the white inner wood of the branches.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-868BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-868BK\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then he placed the peeled branches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-869BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-869BL\"></sup> in all the watering troughs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-869BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-869BM\"></sup> so that they would be directly in front of the flocks when they came to drink. When the flocks were in heat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-869BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-869BN\"></sup> and came to drink,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>they mated in front of the branches.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-870BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-870BO\"></sup> And they bore young that were streaked or speckled or spotted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-870BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-870BP\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Jacob set apart the young of the flock by themselves, but made the rest face the streaked and dark-colored animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-871BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-871BQ\"></sup> that belonged to Laban. Thus he made separate flocks for himself and did not put them with Laban’s animals.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Whenever the stronger females were in heat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-872BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-872BR\"></sup> Jacob would place the branches in the troughs in front of the animals so they would mate near the branches,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-872BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-872BS\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>but if the animals were weak, he would not place them there. So the weak animals went to Laban and the strong ones to Jacob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-873BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-873BT\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>In this way the man grew exceedingly prosperous and came to own large flocks, and female and male servants, and camels and donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-874BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-874BU\"></sup>"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>Jacob heard that Laban’s sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-875A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-875A\"></sup> were saying, “Jacob has taken everything our father owned and has gained all this wealth from what belonged to our father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-875B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-875B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jacob noticed that Laban’s attitude toward him was not what it had been.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-876C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-876C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Jacob, “Go back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-877D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-877D\"></sup> to the land of your fathers and to your relatives, and I will be with you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-877E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-877E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Jacob sent word to Rachel and Leah to come out to the fields where his flocks were.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “I see that your father’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-879F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-879F\"></sup> attitude toward me is not what it was before,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-879G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-879G\"></sup> but the God of my father has been with me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-879H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-879H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You know that I’ve worked for your father with all my strength,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-880I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-880I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>yet your father has cheated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-881J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-881J\"></sup> me by changing my wages<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-881K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-881K\"></sup> ten times.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-881L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-881L\"></sup> However, God has not allowed him to harm me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-881M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-881M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If he said, ‘The speckled ones will be your wages,’ then all the flocks gave birth to speckled young; and if he said, ‘The streaked ones will be your wages,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-882N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-882N\"></sup> then all the flocks bore streaked young.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So God has taken away your father’s livestock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-883O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-883O\"></sup> and has given them to me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-883P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-883P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“In breeding season I once had a dream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-884Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-884Q\"></sup> in which I looked up and saw that the male goats mating with the flock were streaked, speckled or spotted.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The angel of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-885R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-885R\"></sup> said to me in the dream,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-885S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-885S\"></sup> ‘Jacob.’ I answered, ‘Here I am.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-885T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-885T\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he said, ‘Look up and see that all the male goats mating with the flock are streaked, speckled or spotted,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-886U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-886U\"></sup> for I have seen all that Laban has been doing to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-886V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-886V\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I am the God of Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-887W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-887W\"></sup> where you anointed a pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-887X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-887X\"></sup> and where you made a vow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-887Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-887Y\"></sup> to me. Now leave this land at once and go back to your native land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-887Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-887Z\"></sup>’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Rachel and Leah replied, “Do we still have any share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-888AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-888AA\"></sup> in the inheritance of our father’s estate?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Does he not regard us as foreigners?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-889AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-889AB\"></sup> Not only has he sold us, but he has used up what was paid for us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-889AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-889AC\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Surely all the wealth that God took away from our father belongs to us and our children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-890AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-890AD\"></sup> So do whatever God has told you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jacob put his children and his wives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-891AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-891AE\"></sup> on camels,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-891AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-891AF\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and he drove all his livestock ahead of him, along with all the goods he had accumulated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-892AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-892AG\"></sup> in Paddan Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-892AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-892AH\"></sup> to go to his father Isaac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-892AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-892AI\"></sup> in the land of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-892AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-892AJ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When Laban had gone to shear his sheep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-893AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-893AK\"></sup> Rachel stole her father’s household gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-893AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-893AL\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Moreover, Jacob deceived<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-894AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-894AM\"></sup> Laban the Aramean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-894AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-894AN\"></sup> by not telling him he was running away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-894AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-894AO\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So he fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-895AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-895AP\"></sup> with all he had, crossed the Euphrates River,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-895AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-895AQ\"></sup> and headed for the hill country of Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-895AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-895AR\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>On the third day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-896AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-896AS\"></sup> Laban was told that Jacob had fled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-896AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-896AT\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Taking his relatives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-897AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-897AU\"></sup> with him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-897AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-897AV\"></sup>, he pursued Jacob for seven days and caught up with him in the hill country of Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-897AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-897AW\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then God came to Laban the Aramean<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-898AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-898AX\"></sup> in a dream at night and said to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-898AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-898AY\"></sup> “Be careful not to say anything to Jacob, either good or bad.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-898AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-898AZ\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jacob had pitched his tent in the hill country of Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-899BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-899BA\"></sup> when Laban overtook him, and Laban and his relatives camped there too.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Laban said to Jacob, “What have you done?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-900BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-900BB\"></sup> You’ve deceived me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-900BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-900BC\"></sup> and you’ve carried off my daughters like captives in war.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-900BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-900BD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Why did you run off secretly and deceive me? Why didn’t you tell me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-901BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-901BE\"></sup> so I could send you away with joy and singing to the music of timbrels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-901BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-901BF\"></sup> and harps?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-901BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-901BG\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You didn’t even let me kiss my grandchildren and my daughters goodbye.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-902BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-902BH\"></sup> You have done a foolish thing.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I have the power to harm you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-903BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-903BI\"></sup> but last night the God of your father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-903BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-903BJ\"></sup> said to me, ‘Be careful not to say anything to Jacob, either good or bad.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-903BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-903BK\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now you have gone off because you longed to return to your father’s household.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-904BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-904BL\"></sup> But why did you steal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-904BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-904BM\"></sup> my gods?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-904BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-904BN\"></sup>”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jacob answered Laban, “I was afraid, because I thought you would take your daughters away from me by force.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-905BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-905BO\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But if you find anyone who has your gods, that person shall not live.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-906BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-906BP\"></sup> In the presence of our relatives, see for yourself whether there is anything of yours here with me; and if so, take it.” Now Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen the gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-906BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-906BQ\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So Laban went into Jacob’s tent and into Leah’s tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-907BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-907BR\"></sup> and into the tent of the two female servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-907BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-907BS\"></sup> but he found nothing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-907BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-907BT\"></sup> After he came out of Leah’s tent, he entered Rachel’s tent.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now Rachel had taken the household gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-908BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-908BU\"></sup> and put them inside her camel’s saddle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-908BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-908BV\"></sup> and was sitting on them. Laban searched<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-908BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-908BW\"></sup> through everything in the tent but found nothing.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Rachel said to her father, “Don’t be angry, my lord, that I cannot stand up in your presence;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-909BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-909BX\"></sup> I’m having my period.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-909BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-909BY\"></sup>” So he searched but could not find the household gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-909BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-909BZ\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Jacob was angry and took Laban to task. “What is my crime?” he asked Laban. “How have I wronged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-910CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-910CA\"></sup> you that you hunt me down?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-910CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-910CB\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now that you have searched through all my goods, what have you found that belongs to your household?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-911CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-911CC\"></sup> Put it here in front of your relatives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-911CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-911CD\"></sup> and mine, and let them judge between the two of us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-911CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-911CE\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“I have been with you for twenty years now.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-912CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-912CF\"></sup> Your sheep and goats have not miscarried,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-912CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-912CG\"></sup> nor have I eaten rams from your flocks.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>I did not bring you animals torn by wild beasts; I bore the loss myself. And you demanded payment from me for whatever was stolen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-913CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-913CH\"></sup> by day or night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-913CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-913CI\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>This was my situation: The heat consumed me in the daytime and the cold at night, and sleep fled from my eyes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-914CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-914CJ\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>It was like this for the twenty years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-915CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-915CK\"></sup> I was in your household. I worked for you fourteen years for your two daughters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-915CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-915CL\"></sup> and six years for your flocks,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-915CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-915CM\"></sup> and you changed my wages<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-915CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-915CN\"></sup> ten times.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-915CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-915CO\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>If the God of my father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-916CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-916CP\"></sup> the God of Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-916CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-916CQ\"></sup> and the Fear of Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-916CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-916CR\"></sup> had not been with me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-916CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-916CS\"></sup> you would surely have sent me away empty-handed. But God has seen my hardship and the toil of my hands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-916CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-916CT\"></sup> and last night he rebuked you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-916CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-916CU\"></sup>”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Laban answered Jacob, “The women are my daughters, the children are my children, and the flocks are my flocks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-917CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-917CV\"></sup> All you see is mine. Yet what can I do today about these daughters of mine, or about the children they have borne?",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Come now, let’s make a covenant,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-918CW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CW&quot;&gt;CW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-918CW\"></sup> you and I, and let it serve as a witness between us.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-918CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-918CX\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>So Jacob took a stone and set it up as a pillar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-919CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-919CY\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>He said to his relatives, “Gather some stones.” So they took stones and piled them in a heap,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-920CZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CZ&quot;&gt;CZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-920CZ\"></sup> and they ate there by the heap.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Laban called it Jegar Sahadutha, and Jacob called it Galeed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-921DA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DA&quot;&gt;DA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-921DA\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Laban said, “This heap<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-922DB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DB&quot;&gt;DB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-922DB\"></sup> is a witness between you and me today.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-922DC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DC&quot;&gt;DC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-922DC\"></sup> That is why it was called Galeed.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>It was also called Mizpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-923DD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DD&quot;&gt;DD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-923DD\"></sup> because he said, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> keep watch between you and me when we are away from each other.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>If you mistreat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-924DE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DE&quot;&gt;DE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-924DE\"></sup> my daughters or if you take any wives besides my daughters, even though no one is with us, remember that God is a witness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-924DF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DF&quot;&gt;DF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-924DF\"></sup> between you and me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-924DG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DG&quot;&gt;DG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-924DG\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Laban also said to Jacob, “Here is this heap,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-925DH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DH&quot;&gt;DH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-925DH\"></sup> and here is this pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-925DI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DI&quot;&gt;DI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-925DI\"></sup> I have set up between you and me.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>This heap is a witness, and this pillar is a witness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-926DJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DJ&quot;&gt;DJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-926DJ\"></sup> that I will not go past this heap to your side to harm you and that you will not go past this heap<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-926DK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DK&quot;&gt;DK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-926DK\"></sup> and pillar to my side to harm me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-926DL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DL&quot;&gt;DL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-926DL\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>May the God of Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-927DM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DM&quot;&gt;DM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-927DM\"></sup> and the God of Nahor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-927DN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DN&quot;&gt;DN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-927DN\"></sup> the God of their father, judge between us.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-927DO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DO&quot;&gt;DO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-927DO\"></sup>So Jacob took an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-927DP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DP&quot;&gt;DP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-927DP\"></sup> in the name of the Fear of his father Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-927DQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DQ&quot;&gt;DQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-927DQ\"></sup>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>He offered a sacrifice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-928DR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DR&quot;&gt;DR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-928DR\"></sup> there in the hill country and invited his relatives to a meal.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-928DS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DS&quot;&gt;DS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-928DS\"></sup> After they had eaten, they spent the night there.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Early the next morning Laban kissed his grandchildren and his daughters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-929DT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DT&quot;&gt;DT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-929DT\"></sup> and blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-929DU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DU&quot;&gt;DU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-929DU\"></sup> them. Then he left and returned home.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-929DV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DV&quot;&gt;DV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-929DV\"></sup>"
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>Jacob also went on his way, and the angels of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-930A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-930A\"></sup> met him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Jacob saw them, he said, “This is the camp of God!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-931B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-931B\"></sup> So he named that place Mahanaim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-931C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-931C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jacob sent messengers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-932D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-932D\"></sup> ahead of him to his brother Esau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-932E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-932E\"></sup> in the land of Seir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-932F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-932F\"></sup> the country of Edom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-932G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-932G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He instructed them: “This is what you are to say to my lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-933H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-933H\"></sup> Esau: ‘Your servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-933I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-933I\"></sup> Jacob says, I have been staying with Laban<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-933J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-933J\"></sup> and have remained there till now.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I have cattle and donkeys, sheep and goats, male and female servants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-934K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-934K\"></sup> Now I am sending this message to my lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-934L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-934L\"></sup> that I may find favor in your eyes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-934M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-934M\"></sup>’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the messengers returned to Jacob, they said, “We went to your brother Esau, and now he is coming to meet you, and four hundred men are with him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-935N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-935N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In great fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-936O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-936O\"></sup> and distress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-936P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-936P\"></sup> Jacob divided the people who were with him into two groups,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-936Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-936Q\"></sup> and the flocks and herds and camels as well.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He thought, “If Esau comes and attacks one group, the group that is left may escape.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Jacob prayed, “O God of my father Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-938R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-938R\"></sup> God of my father Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-938S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-938S\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you who said to me, ‘Go back to your country and your relatives, and I will make you prosper,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-938T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-938T\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I am unworthy of all the kindness and faithfulness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-939U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-939U\"></sup> you have shown your servant. I had only my staff<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-939V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-939V\"></sup> when I crossed this Jordan, but now I have become two camps.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-939W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-939W\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Save me, I pray, from the hand of my brother Esau, for I am afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-940X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-940X\"></sup> he will come and attack me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-940Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-940Y\"></sup> and also the mothers with their children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-940Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-940Z\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But you have said, ‘I will surely make you prosper and will make your descendants like the sand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-941AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-941AA\"></sup> of the sea, which cannot be counted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-941AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-941AB\"></sup>’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He spent the night there, and from what he had with him he selected a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-942AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-942AC\"></sup> for his brother Esau:",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes and twenty rams,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-943AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-943AD\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>thirty female camels with their young, forty cows and ten bulls, and twenty female donkeys and ten male donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-944AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-944AE\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He put them in the care of his servants, each herd by itself, and said to his servants, “Go ahead of me, and keep some space between the herds.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-945AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-945AF\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He instructed the one in the lead: “When my brother Esau meets you and asks, ‘Who do you belong to, and where are you going, and who owns all these animals in front of you?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>then you are to say, ‘They belong to your servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-947AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-947AG\"></sup> Jacob. They are a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-947AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-947AH\"></sup> sent to my lord Esau, and he is coming behind us.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He also instructed the second, the third and all the others who followed the herds: “You are to say the same thing to Esau when you meet him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And be sure to say, ‘Your servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-949AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-949AI\"></sup> Jacob is coming behind us.’” For he thought, “I will pacify him with these gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-949AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-949AJ\"></sup> I am sending on ahead;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-949AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-949AK\"></sup> later, when I see him, perhaps he will receive me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-949AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-949AL\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Jacob’s gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-950AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-950AM\"></sup> went on ahead of him, but he himself spent the night in the camp.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>That night Jacob got up and took his two wives, his two female servants and his eleven sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-951AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-951AN\"></sup> and crossed the ford of the Jabbok.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-951AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-951AO\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After he had sent them across the stream, he sent over all his possessions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-952AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-952AP\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Jacob was left alone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-953AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-953AQ\"></sup> and a man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-953AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-953AR\"></sup> wrestled with him till daybreak.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When the man saw that he could not overpower him, he touched the socket of Jacob’s hip<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-954AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-954AS\"></sup> so that his hip was wrenched as he wrestled with the man.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the man said, “Let me go, for it is daybreak.”But Jacob replied, “I will not let you go unless you bless me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-955AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-955AT\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The man asked him, “What is your name?”“Jacob,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-956AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-956AU\"></sup> he answered.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the man said, “Your name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-957AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-957AV\"></sup> will no longer be Jacob, but Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-957AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-957AW\"></sup> because you have struggled with God and with humans and have overcome.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-957AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-957AX\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jacob said, “Please tell me your name.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-958AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-958AY\"></sup>But he replied, “Why do you ask my name?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-958AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-958AZ\"></sup> Then he blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-958BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-958BA\"></sup> him there.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Jacob called the place Peniel, saying, “It is because I saw God face to face,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-959BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-959BB\"></sup> and yet my life was spared.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The sun rose above him as he passed Peniel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-960BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-960BC\"></sup> and he was limping because of his hip.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Therefore to this day the Israelites do not eat the tendon attached to the socket of the hip,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-961BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-961BD\"></sup> because the socket of Jacob’s hip was touched near the tendon."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>Jacob looked up and there was Esau, coming with his four hundred men;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-962A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-962A\"></sup> so he divided the children among Leah, Rachel and the two female servants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-962B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-962B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He put the female servants and their children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-963C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-963C\"></sup> in front, Leah and her children next, and Rachel and Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-963D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-963D\"></sup> in the rear.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He himself went on ahead and bowed down to the ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-964E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-964E\"></sup> seven times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-964F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-964F\"></sup> as he approached his brother.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But Esau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-965G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-965G\"></sup> ran to meet Jacob and embraced him; he threw his arms around his neck and kissed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-965H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-965H\"></sup> And they wept.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-965I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-965I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Esau looked up and saw the women and children. “Who are these with you?” he asked.Jacob answered, “They are the children God has graciously given your servant.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-966J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-966J\"></sup>”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the female servants and their children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-967K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-967K\"></sup> approached and bowed down.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-967L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-967L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Next, Leah and her children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-968M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-968M\"></sup> came and bowed down.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-968N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-968N\"></sup> Last of all came Joseph and Rachel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-968O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-968O\"></sup> and they too bowed down.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Esau asked, “What’s the meaning of all these flocks and herds I met?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-969P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-969P\"></sup>“To find favor in your eyes, my lord,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-969Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-969Q\"></sup> he said.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Esau said, “I already have plenty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-970R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-970R\"></sup> my brother. Keep what you have for yourself.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“No, please!” said Jacob. “If I have found favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-971S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-971S\"></sup> accept this gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-971T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-971T\"></sup> from me. For to see your face is like seeing the face of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-971U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-971U\"></sup> now that you have received me favorably.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-971V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-971V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Please accept the present<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-972W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-972W\"></sup> that was brought to you, for God has been gracious to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-972X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-972X\"></sup> and I have all I need.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-972Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-972Y\"></sup> And because Jacob insisted,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-972Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-972Z\"></sup> Esau accepted it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Esau said, “Let us be on our way; I’ll accompany you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Jacob said to him, “My lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-974AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-974AA\"></sup> knows that the children are tender and that I must care for the ewes and cows that are nursing their young.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-974AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-974AB\"></sup> If they are driven hard just one day, all the animals will die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So let my lord go on ahead of his servant, while I move along slowly at the pace of the flocks and herds<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-975AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-975AC\"></sup> before me and the pace of the children, until I come to my lord in Seir.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-975AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-975AD\"></sup>”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Esau said, “Then let me leave some of my men with you.”“But why do that?” Jacob asked. “Just let me find favor in the eyes of my lord.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-976AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-976AE\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So that day Esau started on his way back to Seir.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-977AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-977AF\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jacob, however, went to Sukkoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-978AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-978AG\"></sup> where he built a place for himself and made shelters for his livestock. That is why the place is called Sukkoth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>After Jacob came from Paddan Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-979AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-979AH\"></sup> he arrived safely at the city of Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-979AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-979AI\"></sup> in Canaan and camped within sight of the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For a hundred pieces of silver, he bought from the sons of Hamor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-980AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-980AJ\"></sup> the father of Shechem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-980AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-980AK\"></sup> the plot of ground<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-980AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-980AL\"></sup> where he pitched his tent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-980AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-980AM\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There he set up an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-981AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-981AN\"></sup> and called it El Elohe Israel."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>Now Dinah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-982A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-982A\"></sup> the daughter Leah had borne to Jacob, went out to visit the women of the land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Shechem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-983B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-983B\"></sup> son of Hamor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-983C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-983C\"></sup> the Hivite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-983D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-983D\"></sup> the ruler of that area, saw her, he took her and raped her.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-983E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-983E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>His heart was drawn to Dinah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-984F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-984F\"></sup> daughter of Jacob;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-984G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-984G\"></sup> he loved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-984H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-984H\"></sup> the young woman and spoke tenderly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-984I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-984I\"></sup> to her.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Shechem said to his father Hamor, “Get me this girl as my wife.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-985J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-985J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Jacob heard that his daughter Dinah had been defiled,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-986K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-986K\"></sup> his sons were in the fields with his livestock; so he did nothing about it until they came home.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Shechem’s father Hamor went out to talk with Jacob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-987L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-987L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meanwhile, Jacob’s sons had come in from the fields as soon as they heard what had happened. They were shocked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-988M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-988M\"></sup> and furious,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-988N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-988N\"></sup> because Shechem had done an outrageous thing in Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-988O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-988O\"></sup> by sleeping with Jacob’s daughter—a thing that should not be done.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-988P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-988P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Hamor said to them, “My son Shechem has his heart set on your daughter. Please give her to him as his wife.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-989Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-989Q\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Intermarry with us; give us your daughters and take our daughters for yourselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-990R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-990R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You can settle among us;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-991S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-991S\"></sup> the land is open to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-991T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-991T\"></sup> Live in it, trade in it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-991U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-991U\"></sup> and acquire property in it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-991V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-991V\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Shechem said to Dinah’s father and brothers, “Let me find favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-992W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-992W\"></sup> and I will give you whatever you ask.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Make the price for the bride<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-993X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-993X\"></sup> and the gift I am to bring as great as you like, and I’ll pay whatever you ask me. Only give me the young woman as my wife.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Because their sister Dinah had been defiled,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-994Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-994Y\"></sup> Jacob’s sons replied deceitfully<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-994Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-994Z\"></sup> as they spoke to Shechem and his father Hamor.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They said to them, “We can’t do such a thing; we can’t give our sister to a man who is not circumcised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-995AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-995AA\"></sup> That would be a disgrace to us.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>We will enter into an agreement with you on one condition<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-996AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-996AB\"></sup> only: that you become like us by circumcising all your males.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-996AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-996AC\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then we will give you our daughters and take your daughters for ourselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-997AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-997AD\"></sup> We’ll settle among you and become one people with you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-997AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-997AE\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But if you will not agree to be circumcised, we’ll take our sister and go.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Their proposal seemed good to Hamor and his son Shechem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The young man, who was the most honored<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1000AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1000AF\"></sup> of all his father’s family, lost no time in doing what they said, because he was delighted with Jacob’s daughter.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1000AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1000AG\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Hamor and his son Shechem went to the gate of their city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1001AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1001AH\"></sup> to speak to the men of their city.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“These men are friendly toward us,” they said. “Let them live in our land and trade in it;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1002AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1002AI\"></sup> the land has plenty of room for them. We can marry their daughters and they can marry ours.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1002AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1002AJ\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the men will agree to live with us as one people only on the condition that our males be circumcised,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1003AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1003AK\"></sup> as they themselves are.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Won’t their livestock, their property and all their other animals become ours?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1004AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1004AL\"></sup> So let us agree to their terms, and they will settle among us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1004AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1004AM\"></sup>”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the men who went out of the city gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1005AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1005AN\"></sup> agreed with Hamor and his son Shechem, and every male in the city was circumcised.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Three days later, while all of them were still in pain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1006AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1006AO\"></sup> two of Jacob’s sons, Simeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1006AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1006AP\"></sup> and Levi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1006AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1006AQ\"></sup> Dinah’s brothers, took their swords<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1006AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1006AR\"></sup> and attacked the unsuspecting city,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1006AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1006AS\"></sup> killing every male.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1006AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1006AT\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They put Hamor and his son Shechem to the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1007AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1007AU\"></sup> and took Dinah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1007AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1007AV\"></sup> from Shechem’s house and left.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Jacob came upon the dead bodies and looted the city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1008AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1008AW\"></sup> where their sister had been defiled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1008AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1008AX\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They seized their flocks and herds and donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1009AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1009AY\"></sup> and everything else of theirs in the city and out in the fields.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1009AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1009AZ\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They carried off all their wealth and all their women and children,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1010BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1010BA\"></sup> taking as plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1010BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1010BB\"></sup> everything in the houses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1010BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1010BC\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, “You have brought trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1011BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1011BD\"></sup> on me by making me obnoxious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1011BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1011BE\"></sup> to the Canaanites and Perizzites, the people living in this land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1011BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1011BF\"></sup> We are few in number,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1011BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1011BG\"></sup> and if they join forces against me and attack me, I and my household will be destroyed.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But they replied, “Should he have treated our sister like a prostitute?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1012BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1012BH\"></sup>”"
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>Then God said to Jacob, “Go up to Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1013A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1013A\"></sup> and settle there, and build an altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1013B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1013B\"></sup> there to God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1013C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1013C\"></sup> who appeared to you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1013D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1013D\"></sup> when you were fleeing from your brother Esau.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1013E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1013E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Jacob said to his household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1014F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1014F\"></sup> and to all who were with him, “Get rid of the foreign gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1014G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1014G\"></sup> you have with you, and purify yourselves and change your clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1014H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1014H\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then come, let us go up to Bethel, where I will build an altar to God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1015I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1015I\"></sup> who answered me in the day of my distress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1015J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1015J\"></sup> and who has been with me wherever I have gone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1015K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1015K\"></sup>”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So they gave Jacob all the foreign gods they had and the rings in their ears,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1016L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1016L\"></sup> and Jacob buried them under the oak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1016M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1016M\"></sup> at Shechem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1016N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1016N\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then they set out, and the terror of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1017O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1017O\"></sup> fell on the towns all around them so that no one pursued them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1017P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1017P\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jacob and all the people with him came to Luz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1018Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1018Q\"></sup> (that is, Bethel) in the land of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1018R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1018R\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>There he built an altar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1019S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1019S\"></sup> and he called the place El Bethel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1019T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1019T\"></sup> because it was there that God revealed himself to him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1019U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1019U\"></sup> when he was fleeing from his brother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1019V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1019V\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Deborah, Rebekah’s nurse,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1020W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1020W\"></sup> died and was buried under the oak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1020X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1020X\"></sup> outside Bethel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1020Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1020Y\"></sup> So it was named Allon Bakuth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After Jacob returned from Paddan Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1021Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1021Z\"></sup> God appeared to him again and blessed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1021AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1021AA\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>God said to him, “Your name is Jacob, but you will no longer be called Jacob; your name will be Israel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1022AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1022AB\"></sup> So he named him Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And God said to him, “I am God Almighty;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1023AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1023AC\"></sup> be fruitful and increase in number.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1023AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1023AD\"></sup> A nation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1023AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1023AE\"></sup> and a community of nations will come from you, and kings will be among your descendants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1023AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1023AF\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The land I gave to Abraham and Isaac I also give to you, and I will give this land to your descendants after you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1024AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1024AG\"></sup>”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1024AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1024AH\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then God went up from him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1025AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1025AI\"></sup> at the place where he had talked with him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jacob set up a stone pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1026AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1026AJ\"></sup> at the place where God had talked with him, and he poured out a drink offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1026AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1026AK\"></sup> on it; he also poured oil on it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1026AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1026AL\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Jacob called the place where God had talked with him Bethel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1027AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1027AM\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they moved on from Bethel. While they were still some distance from Ephrath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1028AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1028AO\"></sup> Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1028AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1028AP\"></sup> began to give birth and had great difficulty.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And as she was having great difficulty in childbirth, the midwife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1029AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1029AQ\"></sup> said to her, “Don’t despair, for you have another son.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1029AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1029AR\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As she breathed her last—for she was dying—she named her son Ben-Oni.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1030AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1030AS\"></sup> But his father named him Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1030AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1030AT\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1031AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1031AU\"></sup> (that is, Bethlehem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1031AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1031AV\"></sup>).",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Over her tomb Jacob set up a pillar, and to this day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1032AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1032AW\"></sup> that pillar marks Rachel’s tomb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1032AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1032AX\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Israel moved on again and pitched his tent beyond Migdal Eder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1033AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1033AY\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>While Israel was living in that region, Reuben went in and slept with his father’s concubine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1034AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1034AZ\"></sup> Bilhah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1034BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1034BA\"></sup> and Israel heard of it.Jacob had twelve sons:",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Leah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1035BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1035BB\"></sup>Reuben the firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1035BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1035BC\"></sup> of Jacob,Simeon, Levi, Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1035BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1035BD\"></sup> Issachar and Zebulun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1035BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1035BE\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Rachel:Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1036BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1036BF\"></sup> and Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1036BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1036BG\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of Rachel’s servant Bilhah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1037BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1037BH\"></sup>Dan and Naphtali.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1037BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1037BI\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Leah’s servant Zilpah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1038BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1038BJ\"></sup>Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1038BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1038BK\"></sup> and Asher.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1038BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1038BL\"></sup>These were the sons of Jacob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1038BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1038BM\"></sup> who were born to him in Paddan Aram.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1038BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1038BN\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jacob came home to his father Isaac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1039BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1039BO\"></sup> in Mamre,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1039BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1039BP\"></sup> near Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1039BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1039BQ\"></sup> (that is, Hebron),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1039BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1039BR\"></sup> where Abraham and Isaac had stayed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1039BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1039BS\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Isaac lived a hundred and eighty years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1040BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1040BT\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then he breathed his last and died and was gathered to his people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1041BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1041BU\"></sup> old and full of years.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1041BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1041BV\"></sup> And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1041BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1041BW\"></sup>"
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1042C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1042C\"></sup> of the family line of Esau (that is, Edom).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1042D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1042D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Esau took his wives from the women of Canaan:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1043E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1043E\"></sup> Adah daughter of Elon the Hittite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1043F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1043F\"></sup> and Oholibamah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1043G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1043G\"></sup> daughter of Anah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1043H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1043H\"></sup> and granddaughter of Zibeon the Hivite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1043I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1043I\"></sup>—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>also Basemath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1044J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1044J\"></sup> daughter of Ishmael and sister of Nebaioth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1044K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1044K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Adah bore Eliphaz to Esau, Basemath bore Reuel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1045L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1045L\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam and Korah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1046M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1046M\"></sup> These were the sons of Esau, who were born to him in Canaan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Esau took his wives and sons and daughters and all the members of his household, as well as his livestock and all his other animals and all the goods he had acquired in Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1047N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1047N\"></sup> and moved to a land some distance from his brother Jacob.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1047O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1047O\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Their possessions were too great for them to remain together; the land where they were staying could not support them both because of their livestock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1048P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1048P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Esau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1049Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1049Q\"></sup> (that is, Edom)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1049R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1049R\"></sup> settled in the hill country of Seir.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1049S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1049S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1050T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1050T\"></sup> of the family line of Esau the father of the Edomites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1050U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1050U\"></sup> in the hill country of Seir.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>These are the names of Esau’s sons:Eliphaz, the son of Esau’s wife Adah, and Reuel, the son of Esau’s wife Basemath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1051V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1051V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Eliphaz:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1052W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1052W\"></sup>Teman,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1052X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1052X\"></sup> Omar, Zepho, Gatam and Kenaz.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1052Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1052Y\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Esau’s son Eliphaz also had a concubine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1053Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1053Z\"></sup> named Timna, who bore him Amalek.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1053AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1053AA\"></sup> These were grandsons of Esau’s wife Adah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1053AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1053AB\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Reuel:Nahath, Zerah, Shammah and Mizzah. These were grandsons of Esau’s wife Basemath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1054AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1054AC\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Esau’s wife Oholibamah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1055AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1055AD\"></sup> daughter of Anah and granddaughter of Zibeon, whom she bore to Esau:Jeush, Jalam and Korah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1055AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1055AE\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These were the chiefs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1056AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1056AF\"></sup> among Esau’s descendants:The sons of Eliphaz the firstborn of Esau:Chiefs Teman,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1056AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1056AG\"></sup> Omar, Zepho, Kenaz,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1056AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1056AH\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Korah, Gatam and Amalek. These were the chiefs descended from Eliphaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1057AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1057AI\"></sup> in Edom;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1057AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1057AJ\"></sup> they were grandsons of Adah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1057AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1057AK\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Esau’s son Reuel:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1058AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1058AL\"></sup>Chiefs Nahath, Zerah, Shammah and Mizzah. These were the chiefs descended from Reuel in Edom; they were grandsons of Esau’s wife Basemath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1058AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1058AM\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Esau’s wife Oholibamah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1059AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1059AN\"></sup>Chiefs Jeush, Jalam and Korah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1059AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1059AO\"></sup> These were the chiefs descended from Esau’s wife Oholibamah daughter of Anah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were the sons of Esau<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1060AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1060AP\"></sup> (that is, Edom),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1060AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1060AQ\"></sup> and these were their chiefs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1060AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1060AR\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>These were the sons of Seir the Horite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1061AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1061AS\"></sup> who were living in the region:Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1061AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1061AT\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Dishon, Ezer and Dishan. These sons of Seir in Edom were Horite chiefs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1062AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1062AU\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Lotan:Hori and Homam. Timna was Lotan’s sister.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Shobal:Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho and Onam.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Zibeon:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1065AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1065AV\"></sup>Aiah and Anah. This is the Anah who discovered the hot springs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1065AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1065AW\"></sup> in the desert while he was grazing the donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1065AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1065AX\"></sup> of his father Zibeon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The children of Anah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1066AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1066AY\"></sup>Dishon and Oholibamah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1066AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1066AZ\"></sup> daughter of Anah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Dishon:Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran and Keran.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Ezer:Bilhan, Zaavan and Akan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The sons of Dishan:Uz and Aran.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>These were the Horite chiefs:Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1070BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1070BA\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Dishon, Ezer and Dishan. These were the Horite chiefs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1071BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1071BB\"></sup> according to their divisions, in the land of Seir.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These were the kings who reigned in Edom before any Israelite king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1072BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1072BD\"></sup> reigned:",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Bela son of Beor became king of Edom. His city was named Dinhabah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1074BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1074BE\"></sup> succeeded him as king.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1075BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1075BF\"></sup> succeeded him as king.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad, who defeated Midian<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1076BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1076BG\"></sup> in the country of Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1076BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1076BH\"></sup> succeeded him as king. His city was named Avith.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When Hadad died, Samlah from Masrekah succeeded him as king.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When Samlah died, Shaul from Rehoboth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1078BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1078BI\"></sup> on the river succeeded him as king.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>When Shaul died, Baal-Hanan son of Akbor succeeded him as king.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When Baal-Hanan son of Akbor died, Hadad succeeded him as king. His city was named Pau, and his wife’s name was Mehetabel daughter of Matred, the daughter of Me-Zahab.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>These were the chiefs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1081BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1081BJ\"></sup> descended from Esau, by name, according to their clans and regions:Timna, Alvah, Jetheth,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Magdiel and Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom, according to their settlements in the land they occupied.This is the family line of Esau, the father of the Edomites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1084BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1084BK\"></sup>"
		},
		"37": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">37 </span>Jacob lived in the land where his father had stayed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1085A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1085A\"></sup> the land of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1085B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1085B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>This is the account<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086C\"></sup> of Jacob’s family line.Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086D\"></sup> a young man of seventeen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086E\"></sup> was tending the flocks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086F\"></sup> with his brothers, the sons of Bilhah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086G\"></sup> and the sons of Zilpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086H\"></sup> his father’s wives, and he brought their father a bad report<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1086I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1086I\"></sup> about them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1087J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1087J\"></sup> loved Joseph more than any of his other sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1087K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1087K\"></sup> because he had been born to him in his old age;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1087L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1087L\"></sup> and he made an ornate robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1087M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1087M\"></sup> for him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1087N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1087N\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When his brothers saw that their father loved him more than any of them, they hated him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1088O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1088O\"></sup> and could not speak a kind word to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Joseph had a dream,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1089P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1089P\"></sup> and when he told it to his brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1089Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1089Q\"></sup> they hated him all the more.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1089R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1089R\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to them, “Listen to this dream I had:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We were binding sheaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1091S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1091S\"></sup> of grain out in the field when suddenly my sheaf rose and stood upright, while your sheaves gathered around mine and bowed down to it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1091T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1091T\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His brothers said to him, “Do you intend to reign over us? Will you actually rule us?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1092U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1092U\"></sup> And they hated him all the more<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1092V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1092V\"></sup> because of his dream and what he had said.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he had another dream,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1093W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1093W\"></sup> and he told it to his brothers. “Listen,” he said, “I had another dream, and this time the sun and moon and eleven stars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1093X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1093X\"></sup> were bowing down to me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1093Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1093Y\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When he told his father as well as his brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1094Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1094Z\"></sup> his father rebuked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1094AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1094AA\"></sup> him and said, “What is this dream you had? Will your mother and I and your brothers actually come and bow down to the ground before you?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1094AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1094AB\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>His brothers were jealous of him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1095AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1095AC\"></sup> but his father kept the matter in mind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1095AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1095AD\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now his brothers had gone to graze their father’s flocks near Shechem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1096AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1096AE\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1097AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1097AF\"></sup> said to Joseph, “As you know, your brothers are grazing the flocks near Shechem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1097AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1097AG\"></sup> Come, I am going to send you to them.”“Very well,” he replied.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he said to him, “Go and see if all is well with your brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1098AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1098AH\"></sup> and with the flocks, and bring word back to me.” Then he sent him off from the Valley of Hebron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1098AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1098AI\"></sup>When Joseph arrived at Shechem,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>a man found him wandering around in the fields and asked him, “What are you looking for?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He replied, “I’m looking for my brothers. Can you tell me where they are grazing their flocks?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“They have moved on from here,” the man answered. “I heard them say, ‘Let’s go to Dothan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1101AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1101AJ\"></sup>’”So Joseph went after his brothers and found them near Dothan.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But they saw him in the distance, and before he reached them, they plotted to kill him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1102AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1102AK\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Here comes that dreamer!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1103AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1103AL\"></sup>” they said to each other.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Come now, let’s kill him and throw him into one of these cisterns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1104AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1104AM\"></sup> and say that a ferocious animal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1104AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1104AN\"></sup> devoured him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1104AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1104AO\"></sup> Then we’ll see what comes of his dreams.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1104AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1104AP\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Reuben<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1105AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1105AQ\"></sup> heard this, he tried to rescue him from their hands. “Let’s not take his life,” he said.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1105AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1105AR\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Don’t shed any blood. Throw him into this cistern<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1106AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1106AS\"></sup> here in the wilderness, but don’t lay a hand on him.” Reuben said this to rescue him from them and take him back to his father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1106AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1106AT\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So when Joseph came to his brothers, they stripped him of his robe—the ornate robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1107AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1107AU\"></sup> he was wearing—",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and they took him and threw him into the cistern.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1108AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1108AV\"></sup> The cistern was empty; there was no water in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As they sat down to eat their meal, they looked up and saw a caravan of Ishmaelites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1109AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1109AW\"></sup> coming from Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1109AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1109AX\"></sup> Their camels were loaded with spices, balm<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1109AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1109AY\"></sup> and myrrh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1109AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1109AZ\"></sup> and they were on their way to take them down to Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1109BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1109BA\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1110BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1110BB\"></sup> said to his brothers, “What will we gain if we kill our brother and cover up his blood?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1110BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1110BC\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Come, let’s sell him to the Ishmaelites and not lay our hands on him; after all, he is our brother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1111BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1111BD\"></sup> our own flesh and blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1111BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1111BE\"></sup>” His brothers agreed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So when the Midianite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1112BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1112BF\"></sup> merchants came by, his brothers pulled Joseph up out of the cistern<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1112BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1112BG\"></sup> and sold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1112BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1112BH\"></sup> him for twenty shekels of silver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1112BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1112BI\"></sup> to the Ishmaelites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1112BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1112BJ\"></sup> who took him to Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1112BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1112BK\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When Reuben returned to the cistern and saw that Joseph was not there, he tore his clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1113BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1113BL\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He went back to his brothers and said, “The boy isn’t there! Where can I turn now?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1114BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1114BM\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then they got Joseph’s robe,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1115BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1115BN\"></sup> slaughtered a goat and dipped the robe in the blood.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1115BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1115BO\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They took the ornate robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1116BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1116BP\"></sup> back to their father and said, “We found this. Examine it to see whether it is your son’s robe.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He recognized it and said, “It is my son’s robe! Some ferocious animal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1117BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1117BQ\"></sup> has devoured him. Joseph has surely been torn to pieces.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1117BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1117BR\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jacob tore his clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1118BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1118BS\"></sup> put on sackcloth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1118BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1118BT\"></sup> and mourned for his son many days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1118BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1118BU\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All his sons and daughters came to comfort him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1119BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1119BV\"></sup> but he refused to be comforted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1119BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1119BW\"></sup> “No,” he said, “I will continue to mourn until I join my son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1119BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1119BX\"></sup> in the grave.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1119BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1119BY\"></sup>” So his father wept for him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Meanwhile, the Midianites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1120BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1120BZ\"></sup> sold Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1120CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1120CA\"></sup> in Egypt to Potiphar, one of Pharaoh’s officials, the captain of the guard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1120CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1120CB\"></sup>"
		},
		"38": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">38 </span>At that time, Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1121A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1121A\"></sup> left his brothers and went down to stay with a man of Adullam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1121B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1121B\"></sup> named Hirah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1121C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1121C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There Judah met the daughter of a Canaanite man named Shua.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1122D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1122D\"></sup> He married her and made love to her;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>she became pregnant and gave birth to a son, who was named Er.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1123E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1123E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>She conceived again and gave birth to a son and named him Onan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1124F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1124F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>She gave birth to still another son and named him Shelah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1125G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1125G\"></sup> It was at Kezib that she gave birth to him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Judah got a wife for Er, his firstborn, and her name was Tamar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1126H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1126H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But Er, Judah’s firstborn, was wicked in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s sight;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1127I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1127I\"></sup> so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put him to death.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1127J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1127J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Judah said to Onan, “Sleep with your brother’s wife and fulfill your duty to her as a brother-in-law to raise up offspring for your brother.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1128K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1128K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Onan knew that the child would not be his; so whenever he slept with his brother’s wife, he spilled his semen on the ground to keep from providing offspring for his brother.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>What he did was wicked in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s sight; so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put him to death also.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1130L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1130L\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Judah then said to his daughter-in-law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1131M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1131M\"></sup> Tamar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1131N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1131N\"></sup> “Live as a widow in your father’s household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1131O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1131O\"></sup> until my son Shelah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1131P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1131P\"></sup> grows up.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1131Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1131Q\"></sup> For he thought, “He may die too, just like his brothers.” So Tamar went to live in her father’s household.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After a long time Judah’s wife, the daughter of Shua,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1132R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1132R\"></sup> died. When Judah had recovered from his grief, he went up to Timnah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1132S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1132S\"></sup> to the men who were shearing his sheep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1132T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1132T\"></sup> and his friend Hirah the Adullamite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1132U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1132U\"></sup> went with him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Tamar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1133V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1133V\"></sup> was told, “Your father-in-law is on his way to Timnah to shear his sheep,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1133W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1133W\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>she took off her widow’s clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1134X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1134X\"></sup> covered herself with a veil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1134Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1134Y\"></sup> to disguise herself, and then sat down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1134Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1134Z\"></sup> at the entrance to Enaim, which is on the road to Timnah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1134AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1134AA\"></sup> For she saw that, though Shelah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1134AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1134AB\"></sup> had now grown up, she had not been given to him as his wife.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Judah saw her, he thought she was a prostitute,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1135AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1135AC\"></sup> for she had covered her face.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Not realizing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1136AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1136AD\"></sup> that she was his daughter-in-law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1136AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1136AE\"></sup> he went over to her by the roadside and said, “Come now, let me sleep with you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1136AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1136AF\"></sup>“And what will you give me to sleep with you?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1136AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1136AG\"></sup> she asked.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“I’ll send you a young goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1137AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1137AH\"></sup> from my flock,” he said.“Will you give me something as a pledge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1137AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1137AI\"></sup> until you send it?” she asked.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “What pledge should I give you?”“Your seal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1138AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1138AJ\"></sup> and its cord, and the staff<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1138AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1138AK\"></sup> in your hand,” she answered. So he gave them to her and slept with her, and she became pregnant by him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1138AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1138AL\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After she left, she took off her veil and put on her widow’s clothes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1139AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1139AM\"></sup> again.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Meanwhile Judah sent the young goat by his friend the Adullamite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1140AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1140AN\"></sup> in order to get his pledge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1140AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1140AO\"></sup> back from the woman, but he did not find her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He asked the men who lived there, “Where is the shrine prostitute<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1141AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1141AP\"></sup> who was beside the road at Enaim?”“There hasn’t been any shrine prostitute here,” they said.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So he went back to Judah and said, “I didn’t find her. Besides, the men who lived there said, ‘There hasn’t been any shrine prostitute here.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Judah said, “Let her keep what she has,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1143AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1143AQ\"></sup> or we will become a laughingstock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1143AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1143AR\"></sup> After all, I did send her this young goat, but you didn’t find her.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>About three months later Judah was told, “Your daughter-in-law Tamar is guilty of prostitution, and as a result she is now pregnant.”Judah said, “Bring her out and have her burned to death!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1144AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1144AS\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As she was being brought out, she sent a message to her father-in-law. “I am pregnant by the man who owns these,” she said. And she added, “See if you recognize whose seal and cord and staff these are.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1145AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1145AT\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Judah recognized them and said, “She is more righteous than I,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1146AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1146AU\"></sup> since I wouldn’t give her to my son Shelah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1146AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1146AV\"></sup>” And he did not sleep with her again.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the time came for her to give birth, there were twin boys in her womb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1147AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1147AW\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>As she was giving birth, one of them put out his hand; so the midwife<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1148AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1148AX\"></sup> took a scarlet thread and tied it on his wrist<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1148AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1148AY\"></sup> and said, “This one came out first.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But when he drew back his hand, his brother came out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1149AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1149AZ\"></sup> and she said, “So this is how you have broken out!” And he was named Perez.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1149BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1149BA\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then his brother, who had the scarlet thread on his wrist,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1150BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1150BB\"></sup> came out. And he was named Zerah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1150BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1150BC\"></sup>"
		},
		"39": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">39 </span>Now Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1151A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1151A\"></sup> had been taken down to Egypt. Potiphar, an Egyptian who was one of Pharaoh’s officials, the captain of the guard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1151B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1151B\"></sup> bought him from the Ishmaelites who had taken him there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1151C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1151C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1152D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1152D\"></sup> so that he prospered, and he lived in the house of his Egyptian master.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When his master saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1153E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1153E\"></sup> and that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave him success in everything he did,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1153F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1153F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Joseph found favor in his eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1154G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1154G\"></sup> and became his attendant. Potiphar put him in charge of his household,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1154H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1154H\"></sup> and he entrusted to his care everything he owned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1154I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1154I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From the time he put him in charge of his household and of all that he owned, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed the household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1155J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1155J\"></sup> of the Egyptian because of Joseph.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1155K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1155K\"></sup> The blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on everything Potiphar had, both in the house and in the field.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1155L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1155L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Potiphar left everything he had in Joseph’s care;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1156M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1156M\"></sup> with Joseph in charge, he did not concern himself with anything except the food he ate.Now Joseph was well-built and handsome,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1156N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1156N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and after a while his master’s wife took notice of Joseph and said, “Come to bed with me!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1157O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1157O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he refused.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1158P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1158P\"></sup> “With me in charge,” he told her, “my master does not concern himself with anything in the house; everything he owns he has entrusted to my care.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1158Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1158Q\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>No one is greater in this house than I am.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1159R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1159R\"></sup> My master has withheld nothing from me except you, because you are his wife. How then could I do such a wicked thing and sin against God?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1159S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1159S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And though she spoke to Joseph day after day, he refused<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1160T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1160T\"></sup> to go to bed with her or even be with her.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>One day he went into the house to attend to his duties,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1161U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1161U\"></sup> and none of the household servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1161V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1161V\"></sup> was inside.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>She caught him by his cloak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1162W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1162W\"></sup> and said, “Come to bed with me!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1162X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1162X\"></sup> But he left his cloak in her hand and ran out of the house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1162Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1162Y\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When she saw that he had left his cloak in her hand and had run out of the house,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>she called her household servants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1164Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1164Z\"></sup> “Look,” she said to them, “this Hebrew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1164AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1164AA\"></sup> has been brought to us to make sport of us!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1164AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1164AB\"></sup> He came in here to sleep with me, but I screamed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1164AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1164AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he heard me scream for help, he left his cloak beside me and ran out of the house.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1165AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1165AD\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>She kept his cloak beside her until his master came home.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then she told him this story:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1167AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1167AE\"></sup> “That Hebrew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1167AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1167AF\"></sup> slave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1167AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1167AG\"></sup> you brought us came to me to make sport of me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But as soon as I screamed for help, he left his cloak beside me and ran out of the house.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When his master heard the story his wife told him, saying, “This is how your slave treated me,” he burned with anger.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1169AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1169AH\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Joseph’s master took him and put him in prison,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1170AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1170AI\"></sup> the place where the king’s prisoners were confined.But while Joseph was there in the prison,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1171AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1171AJ\"></sup> he showed him kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1171AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1171AK\"></sup> and granted him favor in the eyes of the prison warden.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1171AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1171AL\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the warden put Joseph in charge of all those held in the prison, and he was made responsible for all that was done there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1172AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1172AM\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The warden paid no attention to anything under Joseph’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1173AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1173AN\"></sup> care, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joseph and gave him success in whatever he did.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1173AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1173AO\"></sup>"
		},
		"40": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">40 </span>Some time later, the cupbearer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1174A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1174A\"></sup> and the baker<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1174B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1174B\"></sup> of the king of Egypt offended their master, the king of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Pharaoh was angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1175C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1175C\"></sup> with his two officials,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1175D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1175D\"></sup> the chief cupbearer and the chief baker,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and put them in custody in the house of the captain of the guard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1176E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1176E\"></sup> in the same prison where Joseph was confined.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The captain of the guard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1177F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1177F\"></sup> assigned them to Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1177G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1177G\"></sup> and he attended them.After they had been in custody<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1177H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1177H\"></sup> for some time,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>each of the two men—the cupbearer and the baker of the king of Egypt, who were being held in prison—had a dream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1178I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1178I\"></sup> the same night, and each dream had a meaning of its own.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1178J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1178J\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Joseph came to them the next morning, he saw that they were dejected.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he asked Pharaoh’s officials who were in custody<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1180K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1180K\"></sup> with him in his master’s house, “Why do you look so sad today?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1180L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1180L\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“We both had dreams,” they answered, “but there is no one to interpret them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1181M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1181M\"></sup>Then Joseph said to them, “Do not interpretations belong to God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1181N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1181N\"></sup> Tell me your dreams.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the chief cupbearer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1182O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1182O\"></sup> told Joseph his dream. He said to him, “In my dream I saw a vine in front of me,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and on the vine were three branches. As soon as it budded, it blossomed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1183P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1183P\"></sup> and its clusters ripened into grapes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Pharaoh’s cup was in my hand, and I took the grapes, squeezed them into Pharaoh’s cup and put the cup in his hand.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“This is what it means,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1185Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1185Q\"></sup>” Joseph said to him. “The three branches are three days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1185R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1185R\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Within three days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1186S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1186S\"></sup> Pharaoh will lift up your head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1186T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1186T\"></sup> and restore you to your position, and you will put Pharaoh’s cup in his hand, just as you used to do when you were his cupbearer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1186U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1186U\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But when all goes well with you, remember me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1187V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1187V\"></sup> and show me kindness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1187W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1187W\"></sup> mention me to Pharaoh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1187X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1187X\"></sup> and get me out of this prison.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I was forcibly carried off from the land of the Hebrews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1188Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1188Y\"></sup> and even here I have done nothing to deserve being put in a dungeon.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1188Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1188Z\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the chief baker<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1189AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1189AA\"></sup> saw that Joseph had given a favorable interpretation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1189AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1189AB\"></sup> he said to Joseph, “I too had a dream: On my head were three baskets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1189AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1189AC\"></sup> of bread.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In the top basket were all kinds of baked goods for Pharaoh, but the birds were eating them out of the basket on my head.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“This is what it means,” Joseph said. “The three baskets are three days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1191AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1191AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Within three days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1192AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1192AE\"></sup> Pharaoh will lift off your head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1192AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1192AF\"></sup> and impale your body on a pole.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1192AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1192AG\"></sup> And the birds will eat away your flesh.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1192AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1192AH\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now the third day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1193AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1193AI\"></sup> was Pharaoh’s birthday,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1193AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1193AJ\"></sup> and he gave a feast for all his officials.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1193AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1193AK\"></sup> He lifted up the heads of the chief cupbearer and the chief baker<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1193AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1193AL\"></sup> in the presence of his officials:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He restored the chief cupbearer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1194AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1194AM\"></sup> to his position,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1194AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1194AN\"></sup> so that he once again put the cup into Pharaoh’s hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1194AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1194AO\"></sup>—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>but he impaled the chief baker,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1195AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1195AP\"></sup> just as Joseph had said to them in his interpretation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1195AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1195AQ\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The chief cupbearer, however, did not remember Joseph; he forgot him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1196AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1196AR\"></sup>"
		},
		"41": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">41 </span>When two full years had passed, Pharaoh had a dream:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1197A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1197A\"></sup> He was standing by the Nile,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1197B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1197B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>when out of the river there came up seven cows, sleek and fat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1198C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1198C\"></sup> and they grazed among the reeds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1198D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1198D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>After them, seven other cows, ugly and gaunt, came up out of the Nile and stood beside those on the riverbank.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the cows that were ugly and gaunt ate up the seven sleek, fat cows. Then Pharaoh woke up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1200E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1200E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He fell asleep again and had a second dream: Seven heads of grain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1201F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1201F\"></sup> healthy and good, were growing on a single stalk.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After them, seven other heads of grain sprouted—thin and scorched by the east wind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1202G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1202G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The thin heads of grain swallowed up the seven healthy, full heads. Then Pharaoh woke up;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1203H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1203H\"></sup> it had been a dream.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the morning his mind was troubled,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1204I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1204I\"></sup> so he sent for all the magicians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1204J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1204J\"></sup> and wise men of Egypt. Pharaoh told them his dreams, but no one could interpret them for him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1204K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1204K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the chief cupbearer said to Pharaoh, “Today I am reminded of my shortcomings.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1205L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1205L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Pharaoh was once angry with his servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1206M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1206M\"></sup> and he imprisoned me and the chief baker in the house of the captain of the guard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1206N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1206N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Each of us had a dream the same night, and each dream had a meaning of its own.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1207O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1207O\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now a young Hebrew<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1208P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1208P\"></sup> was there with us, a servant of the captain of the guard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1208Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1208Q\"></sup> We told him our dreams, and he interpreted them for us, giving each man the interpretation of his dream.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1208R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1208R\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And things turned out exactly as he interpreted them to us: I was restored to my position, and the other man was impaled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1209S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1209S\"></sup>”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Pharaoh sent for Joseph, and he was quickly brought from the dungeon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1210T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1210T\"></sup> When he had shaved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1210U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1210U\"></sup> and changed his clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1210V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1210V\"></sup> he came before Pharaoh.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Pharaoh said to Joseph, “I had a dream, and no one can interpret it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1211W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1211W\"></sup> But I have heard it said of you that when you hear a dream you can interpret it.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1211X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1211X\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“I cannot do it,” Joseph replied to Pharaoh, “but God will give Pharaoh the answer he desires.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1212Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1212Y\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “In my dream I was standing on the bank of the Nile,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1213Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1213Z\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>when out of the river there came up seven cows, fat and sleek, and they grazed among the reeds.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1214AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1214AA\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After them, seven other cows came up—scrawny and very ugly and lean. I had never seen such ugly cows in all the land of Egypt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The lean, ugly cows ate up the seven fat cows that came up first.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But even after they ate them, no one could tell that they had done so; they looked just as ugly as before. Then I woke up.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“In my dream I saw seven heads of grain, full and good, growing on a single stalk.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After them, seven other heads sprouted—withered and thin and scorched by the east wind.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The thin heads of grain swallowed up the seven good heads. I told this to the magicians, but none of them could explain it to me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1220AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1220AB\"></sup>”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, “The dreams of Pharaoh are one and the same.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1221AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1221AC\"></sup> God has revealed to Pharaoh what he is about to do.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1221AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1221AD\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The seven good cows<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1222AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1222AE\"></sup> are seven years, and the seven good heads of grain are seven years; it is one and the same dream.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The seven lean, ugly cows that came up afterward are seven years, and so are the seven worthless heads of grain scorched by the east wind: They are seven years of famine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1223AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1223AF\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“It is just as I said to Pharaoh: God has shown Pharaoh what he is about to do.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1224AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1224AG\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Seven years of great abundance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1225AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1225AH\"></sup> are coming throughout the land of Egypt,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but seven years of famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1226AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1226AI\"></sup> will follow them. Then all the abundance in Egypt will be forgotten, and the famine will ravage the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1226AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1226AJ\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The abundance in the land will not be remembered, because the famine that follows it will be so severe.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The reason the dream was given to Pharaoh in two forms is that the matter has been firmly decided<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1228AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1228AK\"></sup> by God, and God will do it soon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1228AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1228AL\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“And now let Pharaoh look for a discerning and wise man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1229AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1229AM\"></sup> and put him in charge of the land of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1229AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1229AN\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Let Pharaoh appoint commissioners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1230AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1230AO\"></sup> over the land to take a fifth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1230AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1230AP\"></sup> of the harvest of Egypt during the seven years of abundance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1230AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1230AQ\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They should collect all the food of these good years that are coming and store up the grain under the authority of Pharaoh, to be kept in the cities for food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1231AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1231AR\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>This food should be held in reserve for the country, to be used during the seven years of famine that will come upon Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1232AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1232AS\"></sup> so that the country may not be ruined by the famine.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The plan seemed good to Pharaoh and to all his officials.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1233AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1233AT\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So Pharaoh asked them, “Can we find anyone like this man, one in whom is the spirit of God?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1234AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1234AU\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Since God has made all this known to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1235AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1235AV\"></sup> there is no one so discerning and wise as you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1235AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1235AW\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>You shall be in charge of my palace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1236AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1236AX\"></sup> and all my people are to submit to your orders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1236AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1236AY\"></sup> Only with respect to the throne will I be greater than you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1236AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1236AZ\"></sup>”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>So Pharaoh said to Joseph, “I hereby put you in charge of the whole land of Egypt.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1237BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1237BA\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then Pharaoh took his signet ring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1238BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1238BB\"></sup> from his finger and put it on Joseph’s finger. He dressed him in robes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1238BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1238BC\"></sup> of fine linen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1238BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1238BD\"></sup> and put a gold chain around his neck.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1238BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1238BE\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>He had him ride in a chariot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1239BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1239BF\"></sup> as his second-in-command,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1239BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1239BG\"></sup> and people shouted before him, “Make way!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1239BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1239BH\"></sup> Thus he put him in charge of the whole land of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1239BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1239BI\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “I am Pharaoh, but without your word no one will lift hand or foot in all Egypt.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1240BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1240BJ\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Pharaoh gave Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1241BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1241BK\"></sup> the name Zaphenath-Paneah and gave him Asenath daughter of Potiphera, priest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1241BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1241BL\"></sup> of On,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1241BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1241BM\"></sup> to be his wife.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1241BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1241BN\"></sup> And Joseph went throughout the land of Egypt.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Joseph was thirty years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1242BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1242BO\"></sup> when he entered the service<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1242BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1242BP\"></sup> of Pharaoh king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from Pharaoh’s presence and traveled throughout Egypt.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>During the seven years of abundance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1243BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1243BQ\"></sup> the land produced plentifully.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Joseph collected all the food produced in those seven years of abundance in Egypt and stored it in the cities.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1244BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1244BR\"></sup> In each city he put the food grown in the fields surrounding it.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Joseph stored up huge quantities of grain, like the sand of the sea;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1245BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1245BS\"></sup> it was so much that he stopped keeping records because it was beyond measure.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Before the years of famine came, two sons were born to Joseph by Asenath daughter of Potiphera, priest of On.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1246BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1246BT\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Joseph named his firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1247BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1247BU\"></sup> Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1247BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1247BV\"></sup> and said, “It is because God has made me forget all my trouble and all my father’s household.”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>The second son he named Ephraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1248BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1248BW\"></sup> and said, “It is because God has made me fruitful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1248BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1248BX\"></sup> in the land of my suffering.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>The seven years of abundance in Egypt came to an end,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>and the seven years of famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1250BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1250BY\"></sup> began,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1250BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1250BZ\"></sup> just as Joseph had said. There was famine in all the other lands, but in the whole land of Egypt there was food.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>When all Egypt began to feel the famine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1251CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1251CA\"></sup> the people cried to Pharaoh for food. Then Pharaoh told all the Egyptians, “Go to Joseph and do what he tells you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1251CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1251CB\"></sup>",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>When the famine had spread over the whole country, Joseph opened all the storehouses and sold grain to the Egyptians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1252CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1252CC\"></sup> for the famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1252CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1252CD\"></sup> was severe throughout Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1252CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1252CE\"></sup>",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>And all the world came to Egypt to buy grain from Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1253CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1253CF\"></sup> because the famine was severe everywhere.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1253CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1253CG\"></sup>"
		},
		"42": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">42 </span>When Jacob learned that there was grain in Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1254A\"></sup> he said to his sons, “Why do you just keep looking at each other?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He continued, “I have heard that there is grain in Egypt. Go down there and buy some for us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1255B\"></sup> so that we may live and not die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1255C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then ten of Joseph’s brothers went down to buy grain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1256D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1256D\"></sup> from Egypt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But Jacob did not send Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1257E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1257E\"></sup> Joseph’s brother, with the others, because he was afraid that harm might come to him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1257F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1257F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Israel’s sons were among those who went to buy grain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1258G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1258G\"></sup> for there was famine in the land of Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1258H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1258H\"></sup> also.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1258I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1258I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Joseph was the governor of the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1259J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1259J\"></sup> the person who sold grain to all its people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1259K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1259K\"></sup> So when Joseph’s brothers arrived, they bowed down to him with their faces to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1259L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1259L\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As soon as Joseph saw his brothers, he recognized them, but he pretended to be a stranger and spoke harshly to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1260M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1260M\"></sup> “Where do you come from?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1260N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1260N\"></sup> he asked.“From the land of Canaan,” they replied, “to buy food.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Although Joseph recognized his brothers, they did not recognize him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1261O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1261O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he remembered his dreams<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1262P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1262P\"></sup> about them and said to them, “You are spies!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1262Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1262Q\"></sup> You have come to see where our land is unprotected.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1262R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1262R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“No, my lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1263S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1263S\"></sup>” they answered. “Your servants have come to buy food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1263T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1263T\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>We are all the sons of one man. Your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1264U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1264U\"></sup> are honest men,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1264V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1264V\"></sup> not spies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1264W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1264W\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“No!” he said to them. “You have come to see where our land is unprotected.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1265X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1265X\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But they replied, “Your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1266Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1266Y\"></sup> were twelve brothers, the sons of one man, who lives in the land of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1266Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1266Z\"></sup> The youngest is now with our father, and one is no more.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1266AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1266AA\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Joseph said to them, “It is just as I told you: You are spies!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1267AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1267AB\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And this is how you will be tested: As surely as Pharaoh lives,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1268AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1268AC\"></sup> you will not leave this place unless your youngest brother comes here.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1268AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1268AD\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Send one of your number to get your brother;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1269AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1269AE\"></sup> the rest of you will be kept in prison,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1269AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1269AF\"></sup> so that your words may be tested to see if you are telling the truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1269AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1269AG\"></sup> If you are not, then as surely as Pharaoh lives, you are spies!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1269AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1269AH\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he put them all in custody<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1270AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1270AI\"></sup> for three days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On the third day, Joseph said to them, “Do this and you will live, for I fear God:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1271AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1271AJ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If you are honest men,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1272AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1272AK\"></sup> let one of your brothers stay here in prison,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1272AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1272AL\"></sup> while the rest of you go and take grain back for your starving households.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1272AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1272AM\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But you must bring your youngest brother to me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1273AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1273AN\"></sup> so that your words may be verified and that you may not die.” This they proceeded to do.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They said to one another, “Surely we are being punished because of our brother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1274AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1274AO\"></sup> We saw how distressed he was when he pleaded with us for his life, but we would not listen; that’s why this distress<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1274AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1274AP\"></sup> has come on us.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Reuben replied, “Didn’t I tell you not to sin against the boy?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1275AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1275AQ\"></sup> But you wouldn’t listen! Now we must give an accounting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1275AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1275AR\"></sup> for his blood.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1275AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1275AS\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They did not realize<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1276AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1276AT\"></sup> that Joseph could understand them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1276AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1276AU\"></sup> since he was using an interpreter.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He turned away from them and began to weep,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1277AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1277AV\"></sup> but then came back and spoke to them again. He had Simeon taken from them and bound before their eyes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1277AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1277AW\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Joseph gave orders to fill their bags with grain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1278AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1278AX\"></sup> to put each man’s silver back in his sack,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1278AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1278AY\"></sup> and to give them provisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1278AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1278AZ\"></sup> for their journey.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1278BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1278BA\"></sup> After this was done for them,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>they loaded their grain on their donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1279BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1279BB\"></sup> and left.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>At the place where they stopped for the night one of them opened his sack to get feed for his donkey,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1280BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1280BC\"></sup> and he saw his silver in the mouth of his sack.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1280BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1280BD\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“My silver has been returned,” he said to his brothers. “Here it is in my sack.”Their hearts sank<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1281BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1281BE\"></sup> and they turned to each other trembling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1281BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1281BF\"></sup> and said, “What is this that God has done to us?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1281BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1281BG\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When they came to their father Jacob in the land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1282BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1282BH\"></sup> they told him all that had happened to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1282BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1282BI\"></sup> They said,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“The man who is lord over the land spoke harshly to us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1283BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1283BJ\"></sup> and treated us as though we were spying on the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1283BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1283BK\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But we said to him, ‘We are honest men; we are not spies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1284BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1284BL\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>We were twelve brothers, sons of one father. One is no more, and the youngest is now with our father in Canaan.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1285BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1285BM\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Then the man who is lord over the land said to us, ‘This is how I will know whether you are honest men: Leave one of your brothers here with me, and take food for your starving households and go.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1286BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1286BN\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But bring your youngest brother to me so I will know that you are not spies but honest men.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1287BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1287BO\"></sup> Then I will give your brother back to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1287BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1287BP\"></sup> and you can trade in the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1287BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1287BQ\"></sup>’”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>As they were emptying their sacks, there in each man’s sack was his pouch of silver!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1288BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1288BR\"></sup> When they and their father saw the money pouches, they were frightened.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1288BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1288BS\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Their father Jacob said to them, “You have deprived me of my children. Joseph is no more and Simeon is no more,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1289BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1289BT\"></sup> and now you want to take Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1289BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1289BU\"></sup> Everything is against me!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1289BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1289BV\"></sup>”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Reuben said to his father, “You may put both of my sons to death if I do not bring him back to you. Entrust him to my care,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1290BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1290BW\"></sup> and I will bring him back.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1290BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1290BX\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But Jacob said, “My son will not go down there with you; his brother is dead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1291BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1291BY\"></sup> and he is the only one left. If harm comes to him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1291BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1291BZ\"></sup> on the journey you are taking, you will bring my gray head down to the grave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1291CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1291CA\"></sup> in sorrow.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1291CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1291CB\"></sup>”"
		},
		"43": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">43 </span>Now the famine was still severe in the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1292A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1292A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So when they had eaten all the grain they had brought from Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1293B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1293B\"></sup> their father said to them, “Go back and buy us a little more food.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1293C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1293C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1294D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1294D\"></sup> said to him, “The man warned us solemnly, ‘You will not see my face again unless your brother is with you.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1294E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1294E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If you will send our brother along with us, we will go down and buy food for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1295F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1295F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But if you will not send him, we will not go down, because the man said to us, ‘You will not see my face again unless your brother is with you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1296G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1296G\"></sup>’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1297H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1297H\"></sup> asked, “Why did you bring this trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1297I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1297I\"></sup> on me by telling the man you had another brother?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They replied, “The man questioned us closely about ourselves and our family. ‘Is your father still living?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1298J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1298J\"></sup> he asked us. ‘Do you have another brother?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1298K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1298K\"></sup> We simply answered his questions. How were we to know he would say, ‘Bring your brother down here’?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1298L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1298L\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1299M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1299M\"></sup> said to Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1299N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1299N\"></sup> his father, “Send the boy along with me and we will go at once, so that we and you and our children may live and not die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1299O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1299O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I myself will guarantee his safety; you can hold me personally responsible for him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1300P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1300P\"></sup> If I do not bring him back to you and set him here before you, I will bear the blame<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1300Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1300Q\"></sup> before you all my life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1300R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1300R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As it is, if we had not delayed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1301S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1301S\"></sup> we could have gone and returned twice.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then their father Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1302T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1302T\"></sup> said to them, “If it must be, then do this: Put some of the best products<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1302U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1302U\"></sup> of the land in your bags and take them down to the man as a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1302V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1302V\"></sup>—a little balm<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1302W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1302W\"></sup> and a little honey, some spices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1302X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1302X\"></sup> and myrrh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1302Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1302Y\"></sup> some pistachio nuts and almonds.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Take double the amount<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1303Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1303Z\"></sup> of silver with you, for you must return the silver that was put back into the mouths of your sacks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1303AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1303AA\"></sup> Perhaps it was a mistake.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Take your brother also and go back to the man at once.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1304AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1304AB\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And may God Almighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1305AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1305AC\"></sup> grant you mercy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1305AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1305AD\"></sup> before the man so that he will let your other brother and Benjamin come back with you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1305AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1305AE\"></sup> As for me, if I am bereaved, I am bereaved.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1305AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1305AF\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the men took the gifts and double the amount of silver,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1306AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1306AG\"></sup> and Benjamin also. They hurried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1306AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1306AH\"></sup> down to Egypt and presented themselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1306AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1306AI\"></sup> to Joseph.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Joseph saw Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1307AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1307AJ\"></sup> with them, he said to the steward of his house,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1307AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1307AK\"></sup> “Take these men to my house, slaughter an animal and prepare a meal;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1307AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1307AL\"></sup> they are to eat with me at noon.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The man did as Joseph told him and took the men to Joseph’s house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1308AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1308AM\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the men were frightened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1309AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1309AN\"></sup> when they were taken to his house.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1309AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1309AO\"></sup> They thought, “We were brought here because of the silver that was put back into our sacks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1309AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1309AP\"></sup> the first time. He wants to attack us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1309AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1309AQ\"></sup> and overpower us and seize us as slaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1309AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1309AR\"></sup> and take our donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1309AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1309AS\"></sup>”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So they went up to Joseph’s steward<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1310AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1310AT\"></sup> and spoke to him at the entrance to the house.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“We beg your pardon, our lord,” they said, “we came down here the first time to buy food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1311AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1311AU\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But at the place where we stopped for the night we opened our sacks and each of us found his silver—the exact weight—in the mouth of his sack. So we have brought it back with us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1312AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1312AV\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>We have also brought additional silver with us to buy food. We don’t know who put our silver in our sacks.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“It’s all right,” he said. “Don’t be afraid. Your God, the God of your father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1314AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1314AW\"></sup> has given you treasure in your sacks;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1314AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1314AX\"></sup> I received your silver.” Then he brought Simeon out to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1314AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1314AY\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The steward took the men into Joseph’s house,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1315AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1315AZ\"></sup> gave them water to wash their feet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1315BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1315BA\"></sup> and provided fodder for their donkeys.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They prepared their gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1316BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1316BB\"></sup> for Joseph’s arrival at noon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1316BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1316BC\"></sup> because they had heard that they were to eat there.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Joseph came home,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1317BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1317BD\"></sup> they presented to him the gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1317BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1317BE\"></sup> they had brought into the house, and they bowed down before him to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1317BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1317BF\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He asked them how they were, and then he said, “How is your aged father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1318BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1318BG\"></sup> you told me about? Is he still living?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1318BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1318BH\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They replied, “Your servant our father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1319BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1319BI\"></sup> is still alive and well.” And they bowed down,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1319BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1319BJ\"></sup> prostrating themselves before him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1319BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1319BK\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As he looked about and saw his brother Benjamin, his own mother’s son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1320BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1320BL\"></sup> he asked, “Is this your youngest brother, the one you told me about?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1320BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1320BM\"></sup> And he said, “God be gracious to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1320BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1320BN\"></sup> my son.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Deeply moved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1321BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1321BO\"></sup> at the sight of his brother, Joseph hurried out and looked for a place to weep. He went into his private room and wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1321BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1321BP\"></sup> there.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After he had washed his face, he came out and, controlling himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1322BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1322BQ\"></sup> said, “Serve the food.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1322BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1322BR\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They served him by himself, the brothers by themselves, and the Egyptians who ate with him by themselves, because Egyptians could not eat with Hebrews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1323BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1323BS\"></sup> for that is detestable to Egyptians.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1323BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1323BT\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The men had been seated before him in the order of their ages, from the firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1324BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1324BU\"></sup> to the youngest;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1324BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1324BV\"></sup> and they looked at each other in astonishment.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When portions were served to them from Joseph’s table, Benjamin’s portion was five times as much as anyone else’s.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1325BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1325BW\"></sup> So they feasted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1325BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1325BX\"></sup> and drank freely with him."
		},
		"44": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">44 </span>Now Joseph gave these instructions to the steward of his house:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1326A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1326A\"></sup> “Fill the men’s sacks with as much food as they can carry, and put each man’s silver in the mouth of his sack.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1326B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1326B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then put my cup,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1327C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1327C\"></sup> the silver one,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1327D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1327D\"></sup> in the mouth of the youngest one’s sack, along with the silver for his grain.” And he did as Joseph said.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As morning dawned, the men were sent on their way with their donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1328E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1328E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They had not gone far from the city when Joseph said to his steward,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1329F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1329F\"></sup> “Go after those men at once, and when you catch up with them, say to them, ‘Why have you repaid good with evil?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1329G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1329G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Isn’t this the cup<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1330H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1330H\"></sup> my master drinks from and also uses for divination?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1330I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1330I\"></sup> This is a wicked thing you have done.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When he caught up with them, he repeated these words to them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But they said to him, “Why does my lord say such things? Far be it from your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1332J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1332J\"></sup> to do anything like that!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1332K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1332K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>We even brought back to you from the land of Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1333L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1333L\"></sup> the silver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1333M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1333M\"></sup> we found inside the mouths of our sacks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1333N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1333N\"></sup> So why would we steal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1333O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1333O\"></sup> silver or gold from your master’s house?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If any of your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1334P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1334P\"></sup> is found to have it, he will die;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1334Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1334Q\"></sup> and the rest of us will become my lord’s slaves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1334R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1334R\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Very well, then,” he said, “let it be as you say. Whoever is found to have it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1335S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1335S\"></sup> will become my slave;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1335T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1335T\"></sup> the rest of you will be free from blame.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1335U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1335U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Each of them quickly lowered his sack to the ground and opened it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the steward<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1337V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1337V\"></sup> proceeded to search,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1337W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1337W\"></sup> beginning with the oldest and ending with the youngest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1337X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1337X\"></sup> And the cup was found in Benjamin’s sack.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1337Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1337Y\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>At this, they tore their clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1338Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1338Z\"></sup> Then they all loaded their donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1338AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1338AA\"></sup> and returned to the city.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Joseph was still in the house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1339AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1339AB\"></sup> when Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1339AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1339AC\"></sup> and his brothers came in, and they threw themselves to the ground before him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1339AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1339AD\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Joseph said to them, “What is this you have done?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1340AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1340AE\"></sup> Don’t you know that a man like me can find things out by divination?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1340AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1340AF\"></sup>”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“What can we say to my lord?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1341AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1341AG\"></sup>” Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1341AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1341AH\"></sup> replied. “What can we say? How can we prove our innocence?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1341AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1341AI\"></sup> God has uncovered your servants’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1341AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1341AJ\"></sup> guilt. We are now my lord’s slaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1341AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1341AK\"></sup>—we ourselves and the one who was found to have the cup.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1341AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1341AL\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Joseph said, “Far be it from me to do such a thing!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1342AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1342AM\"></sup> Only the man who was found to have the cup will become my slave.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1342AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1342AN\"></sup> The rest of you, go back to your father in peace.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1342AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1342AO\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1343AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1343AP\"></sup> went up to him and said: “Pardon your servant, my lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1343AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1343AQ\"></sup> let me speak a word to my lord. Do not be angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1343AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1343AR\"></sup> with your servant, though you are equal to Pharaoh himself.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>My lord asked his servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1344AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1344AS\"></sup> ‘Do you have a father or a brother?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1344AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1344AT\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And we answered, ‘We have an aged father, and there is a young son born to him in his old age.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1345AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1345AU\"></sup> His brother is dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1345AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1345AV\"></sup> and he is the only one of his mother’s sons left, and his father loves him.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1345AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1345AW\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Then you said to your servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1346AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1346AX\"></sup> ‘Bring him down to me so I can see him for myself.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1346AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1346AY\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And we said to my lord,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1347AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1347AZ\"></sup> ‘The boy cannot leave his father; if he leaves him, his father will die.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1347BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1347BA\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But you told your servants, ‘Unless your youngest brother comes down with you, you will not see my face again.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1348BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1348BB\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When we went back to your servant my father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1349BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1349BC\"></sup> we told him what my lord<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1349BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1349BD\"></sup> had said.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1349BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1349BE\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Then our father said, ‘Go back and buy a little more food.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1350BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1350BF\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But we said, ‘We cannot go down. Only if our youngest brother is with us will we go. We cannot see the man’s face unless our youngest brother is with us.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1351BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1351BG\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Your servant my father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1352BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1352BH\"></sup> said to us, ‘You know that my wife bore me two sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1352BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1352BI\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>One of them went away from me, and I said, “He has surely been torn to pieces.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1353BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1353BJ\"></sup> And I have not seen him since.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1353BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1353BK\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If you take this one from me too and harm comes to him, you will bring my gray head down to the grave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1354BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1354BL\"></sup> in misery.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1354BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1354BM\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“So now, if the boy is not with us when I go back to your servant my father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1355BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1355BN\"></sup> and if my father, whose life is closely bound up with the boy’s life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1355BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1355BO\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>sees that the boy isn’t there, he will die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1356BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1356BP\"></sup> Your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1356BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1356BQ\"></sup> will bring the gray head of our father down to the grave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1356BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1356BR\"></sup> in sorrow.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Your servant guaranteed the boy’s safety to my father. I said, ‘If I do not bring him back to you, I will bear the blame before you, my father, all my life!’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1357BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1357BS\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“Now then, please let your servant remain here as my lord’s slave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1358BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1358BT\"></sup> in place of the boy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1358BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1358BU\"></sup> and let the boy return with his brothers.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>How can I go back to my father if the boy is not with me? No! Do not let me see the misery<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1359BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1359BV\"></sup> that would come on my father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1359BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1359BW\"></sup>"
		},
		"45": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">45 </span>Then Joseph could no longer control himself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1360A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1360A\"></sup> before all his attendants, and he cried out, “Have everyone leave my presence!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1360B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1360B\"></sup> So there was no one with Joseph when he made himself known to his brothers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1361C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1361C\"></sup> so loudly that the Egyptians heard him, and Pharaoh’s household heard about it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1361D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1361D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Joseph said to his brothers, “I am Joseph! Is my father still living?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1362E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1362E\"></sup> But his brothers were not able to answer him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1362F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1362F\"></sup> because they were terrified at his presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1362G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1362G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Joseph said to his brothers, “Come close to me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1363H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1363H\"></sup> When they had done so, he said, “I am your brother Joseph, the one you sold into Egypt!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1363I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1363I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And now, do not be distressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1364J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1364J\"></sup> and do not be angry with yourselves for selling me here,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1364K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1364K\"></sup> because it was to save lives that God sent me ahead of you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1364L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1364L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For two years now there has been famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1365M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1365M\"></sup> in the land, and for the next five years there will be no plowing and reaping.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But God sent me ahead of you to preserve for you a remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1366N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1366N\"></sup> on earth and to save your lives by a great deliverance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1366O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1366O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“So then, it was not you who sent me here, but God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1367P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1367P\"></sup> He made me father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1367Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1367Q\"></sup> to Pharaoh, lord of his entire household and ruler of all Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1367R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1367R\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now hurry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1368S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1368S\"></sup> back to my father and say to him, ‘This is what your son Joseph says: God has made me lord of all Egypt. Come down to me; don’t delay.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1368T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1368T\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall live in the region of Goshen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1369U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1369U\"></sup> and be near me—you, your children and grandchildren, your flocks and herds, and all you have.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1369V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1369V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I will provide for you there,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1370W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1370W\"></sup> because five years of famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1370X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1370X\"></sup> are still to come. Otherwise you and your household and all who belong to you will become destitute.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1370Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1370Y\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“You can see for yourselves, and so can my brother Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1371Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1371Z\"></sup> that it is really I who am speaking to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1371AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1371AA\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Tell my father about all the honor accorded me in Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1372AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1372AB\"></sup> and about everything you have seen. And bring my father down here quickly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1372AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1372AC\"></sup>”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he threw his arms around his brother Benjamin and wept, and Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1373AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1373AD\"></sup> embraced him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1373AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1373AE\"></sup> weeping.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he kissed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1374AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1374AF\"></sup> all his brothers and wept over them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1374AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1374AG\"></sup> Afterward his brothers talked with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1374AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1374AH\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the news reached Pharaoh’s palace that Joseph’s brothers had come,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1375AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1375AI\"></sup> Pharaoh and all his officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1375AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1375AJ\"></sup> were pleased.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1375AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1375AK\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Tell your brothers, ‘Do this: Load your animals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1376AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1376AL\"></sup> and return to the land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1376AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1376AM\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and bring your father and your families back to me. I will give you the best of the land of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1377AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1377AN\"></sup> and you can enjoy the fat of the land.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1377AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1377AO\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“You are also directed to tell them, ‘Do this: Take some carts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1378AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1378AP\"></sup> from Egypt for your children and your wives, and get your father and come.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Never mind about your belongings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1379AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1379AQ\"></sup> because the best of all Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1379AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1379AR\"></sup> will be yours.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the sons of Israel did this. Joseph gave them carts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1380AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1380AS\"></sup> as Pharaoh had commanded, and he also gave them provisions for their journey.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1380AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1380AT\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>To each of them he gave new clothing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1381AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1381AU\"></sup> but to Benjamin he gave three hundred shekels of silver and five sets of clothes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1381AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1381AV\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And this is what he sent to his father: ten donkeys<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1382AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1382AW\"></sup> loaded with the best things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1382AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1382AX\"></sup> of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain and bread and other provisions for his journey.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1382AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1382AY\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then he sent his brothers away, and as they were leaving he said to them, “Don’t quarrel on the way!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1383AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1383AZ\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So they went up out of Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1384BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1384BA\"></sup> and came to their father Jacob in the land of Canaan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1384BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1384BB\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They told him, “Joseph is still alive! In fact, he is ruler of all Egypt.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1385BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1385BC\"></sup> Jacob was stunned; he did not believe them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1385BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1385BD\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But when they told him everything Joseph had said to them, and when he saw the carts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1386BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1386BE\"></sup> Joseph had sent to carry him back, the spirit of their father Jacob revived.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Israel said, “I’m convinced!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1387BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1387BF\"></sup> My son Joseph is still alive. I will go and see him before I die.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1387BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1387BG\"></sup>"
		},
		"46": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">46 </span>So Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1388A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1388A\"></sup> set out with all that was his, and when he reached Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1388B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1388B\"></sup> he offered sacrifices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1388C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1388C\"></sup> to the God of his father Isaac.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1388D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1388D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And God spoke to Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1389E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1389E\"></sup> in a vision at night<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1389F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1389F\"></sup> and said, “Jacob! Jacob!”“Here I am,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1389G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1389G\"></sup> he replied.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“I am God, the God of your father,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1390H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1390H\"></sup> he said. “Do not be afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1390I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1390I\"></sup> to go down to Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1390J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1390J\"></sup> for I will make you into a great nation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1390K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1390K\"></sup> there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1390L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1390L\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I will go down to Egypt with you, and I will surely bring you back again.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1391M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1391M\"></sup> And Joseph’s own hand will close your eyes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1391N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1391N\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jacob left Beersheba,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1392O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1392O\"></sup> and Israel’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1392P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1392P\"></sup> sons took their father Jacob and their children and their wives in the carts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1392Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1392Q\"></sup> that Pharaoh had sent to transport him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Jacob and all his offspring went to Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1393R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1393R\"></sup> taking with them their livestock and the possessions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1393S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1393S\"></sup> they had acquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1393T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1393T\"></sup> in Canaan.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jacob brought with him to Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1394U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1394U\"></sup> his sons and grandsons and his daughters and granddaughters—all his offspring.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1394V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1394V\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>These are the names of the sons of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1395W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1395W\"></sup> (Jacob and his descendants) who went to Egypt:Reuben the firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1395X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1395X\"></sup> of Jacob.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Reuben:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1396Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1396Y\"></sup>Hanok, Pallu,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1396Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1396Z\"></sup> Hezron and Karmi.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1396AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1396AA\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The sons of Simeon:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1397AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1397AB\"></sup>Jemuel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1397AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1397AC\"></sup> Jamin, Ohad, Jakin, Zohar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1397AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1397AD\"></sup> and Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Levi:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1398AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1398AE\"></sup>Gershon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1398AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1398AF\"></sup> Kohath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1398AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1398AG\"></sup> and Merari.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1398AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1398AH\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Judah:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AI\"></sup>Er,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AJ\"></sup> Onan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AK\"></sup> Shelah, Perez<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AL\"></sup> and Zerah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AM\"></sup> (but Er and Onan had died in the land of Canaan).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AN\"></sup>The sons of Perez:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AO\"></sup>Hezron and Hamul.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1399AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1399AP\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Issachar:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1400AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1400AQ\"></sup>Tola, Puah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1400AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1400AR\"></sup> Jashub<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1400AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1400AS\"></sup> and Shimron.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Zebulun:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1401AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1401AT\"></sup>Sered, Elon and Jahleel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These were the sons Leah bore to Jacob in Paddan Aram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1402AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1402AU\"></sup> besides his daughter Dinah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1402AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1402AV\"></sup> These sons and daughters of his were thirty-three in all.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Gad:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1403AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1403AW\"></sup>Zephon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1403AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1403AX\"></sup> Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi and Areli.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Asher:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1404AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1404AY\"></sup>Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi and Beriah.Their sister was Serah.The sons of Beriah:Heber and Malkiel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>These were the children born to Jacob by Zilpah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1405AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1405AZ\"></sup> whom Laban had given to his daughter Leah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1405BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1405BA\"></sup>—sixteen in all.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Jacob’s wife Rachel:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1406BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1406BB\"></sup>Joseph and Benjamin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1406BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1406BC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In Egypt, Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1407BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1407BD\"></sup> and Ephraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1407BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1407BE\"></sup> were born to Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1407BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1407BF\"></sup> by Asenath daughter of Potiphera, priest of On.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1407BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1407BG\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Benjamin:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1408BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1408BH\"></sup>Bela, Beker, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim and Ard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1408BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1408BI\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These were the sons of Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1409BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1409BJ\"></sup> who were born to Jacob—fourteen in all.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The son of Dan:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1410BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1410BK\"></sup>Hushim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1410BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1410BL\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Naphtali:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1411BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1411BM\"></sup>Jahziel, Guni, Jezer and Shillem.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>These were the sons born to Jacob by Bilhah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1412BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1412BN\"></sup> whom Laban had given to his daughter Rachel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1412BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1412BO\"></sup>—seven in all.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>All those who went to Egypt with Jacob—those who were his direct descendants, not counting his sons’ wives—numbered sixty-six persons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1413BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1413BP\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>With the two sons who had been born to Joseph in Egypt,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1414BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1414BQ\"></sup> the members of Jacob’s family, which went to Egypt, were seventy in all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1414BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1414BR\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now Jacob sent Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1415BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1415BS\"></sup> ahead of him to Joseph to get directions to Goshen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1415BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1415BT\"></sup> When they arrived in the region of Goshen,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Joseph had his chariot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1416BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1416BU\"></sup> made ready and went to Goshen to meet his father Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1416BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1416BV\"></sup> As soon as Joseph appeared before him, he threw his arms around his father and wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1416BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1416BW\"></sup> for a long time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1416BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1416BX\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1417BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1417BY\"></sup> said to Joseph, “Now I am ready to die, since I have seen for myself that you are still alive.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1417BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1417BZ\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Joseph said to his brothers and to his father’s household, “I will go up and speak to Pharaoh and will say to him, ‘My brothers and my father’s household, who were living in the land of Canaan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1418CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1418CA\"></sup> have come to me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1418CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1418CB\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The men are shepherds;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1419CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1419CC\"></sup> they tend livestock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1419CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1419CD\"></sup> and they have brought along their flocks and herds and everything they own.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1419CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1419CE\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Pharaoh calls you in and asks, ‘What is your occupation?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1420CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1420CF\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>you should answer, ‘Your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1421CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1421CG\"></sup> have tended livestock from our boyhood on, just as our fathers did.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1421CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1421CH\"></sup> Then you will be allowed to settle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1421CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1421CI\"></sup> in the region of Goshen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1421CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1421CJ\"></sup> for all shepherds are detestable to the Egyptians.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1421CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1421CK\"></sup>”"
		},
		"47": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">47 </span>Joseph went and told Pharaoh, “My father and brothers, with their flocks and herds and everything they own, have come from the land of Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1422A\"></sup> and are now in Goshen.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1422B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1422B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He chose five of his brothers and presented them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1423C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1423C\"></sup> before Pharaoh.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Pharaoh asked the brothers, “What is your occupation?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1424D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1424D\"></sup>“Your servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1424E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1424E\"></sup> are shepherds,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1424F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1424F\"></sup>” they replied to Pharaoh, “just as our fathers were.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They also said to him, “We have come to live here for a while,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1425G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1425G\"></sup> because the famine is severe in Canaan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1425H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1425H\"></sup> and your servants’ flocks have no pasture.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1425I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1425I\"></sup> So now, please let your servants settle in Goshen.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1425J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1425J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Your father and your brothers have come to you,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the land of Egypt is before you; settle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1427K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1427K\"></sup> your father and your brothers in the best part of the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1427L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1427L\"></sup> Let them live in Goshen. And if you know of any among them with special ability,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1427M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1427M\"></sup> put them in charge of my own livestock.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1427N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1427N\"></sup>”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Joseph brought his father Jacob in and presented him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1428O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1428O\"></sup> before Pharaoh. After Jacob blessed Pharaoh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1428P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1428P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Pharaoh asked him, “How old are you?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jacob said to Pharaoh, “The years of my pilgrimage are a hundred and thirty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1430Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1430Q\"></sup> My years have been few and difficult,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1430R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1430R\"></sup> and they do not equal the years of the pilgrimage of my fathers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1430S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1430S\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Jacob blessed Pharaoh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1431T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1431T\"></sup> and went out from his presence.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Joseph settled his father and his brothers in Egypt and gave them property in the best part of the land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1432U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1432U\"></sup> the district of Rameses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1432V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1432V\"></sup> as Pharaoh directed.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joseph also provided his father and his brothers and all his father’s household with food, according to the number of their children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1433W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1433W\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>There was no food, however, in the whole region because the famine was severe; both Egypt and Canaan wasted away because of the famine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1434X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1434X\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Joseph collected all the money that was to be found in Egypt and Canaan in payment for the grain they were buying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1435Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1435Y\"></sup> and he brought it to Pharaoh’s palace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1435Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1435Z\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the money of the people of Egypt and Canaan was gone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1436AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1436AA\"></sup> all Egypt came to Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1436AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1436AB\"></sup> and said, “Give us food. Why should we die before your eyes?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1436AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1436AC\"></sup> Our money is all gone.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Then bring your livestock,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1437AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1437AD\"></sup>” said Joseph. “I will sell you food in exchange for your livestock, since your money is gone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1437AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1437AE\"></sup>”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and he gave them food in exchange for their horses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1438AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1438AF\"></sup> their sheep and goats, their cattle and donkeys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1438AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1438AG\"></sup> And he brought them through that year with food in exchange for all their livestock.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When that year was over, they came to him the following year and said, “We cannot hide from our lord the fact that since our money is gone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1439AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1439AH\"></sup> and our livestock belongs to you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1439AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1439AI\"></sup> there is nothing left for our lord except our bodies and our land.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why should we perish before your eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1440AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1440AJ\"></sup>—we and our land as well? Buy us and our land in exchange for food,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1440AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1440AK\"></sup> and we with our land will be in bondage to Pharaoh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1440AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1440AL\"></sup> Give us seed so that we may live and not die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1440AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1440AM\"></sup> and that the land may not become desolate.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Joseph bought all the land in Egypt for Pharaoh. The Egyptians, one and all, sold their fields, because the famine was too severe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1441AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1441AN\"></sup> for them. The land became Pharaoh’s,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and Joseph reduced the people to servitude,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1442AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1442AO\"></sup> from one end of Egypt to the other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>However, he did not buy the land of the priests,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1443AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1443AP\"></sup> because they received a regular allotment from Pharaoh and had food enough from the allotment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1443AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1443AQ\"></sup> Pharaoh gave them. That is why they did not sell their land.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Joseph said to the people, “Now that I have bought you and your land today for Pharaoh, here is seed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1444AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1444AR\"></sup> for you so you can plant the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1444AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1444AS\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But when the crop comes in, give a fifth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1445AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1445AT\"></sup> of it to Pharaoh. The other four-fifths you may keep as seed for the fields and as food for yourselves and your households and your children.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“You have saved our lives,” they said. “May we find favor in the eyes of our lord;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1446AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1446AU\"></sup> we will be in bondage to Pharaoh.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1446AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1446AV\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So Joseph established it as a law concerning land in Egypt—still in force today—that a fifth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1447AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1447AW\"></sup> of the produce belongs to Pharaoh. It was only the land of the priests that did not become Pharaoh’s.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1447AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1447AX\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now the Israelites settled in Egypt in the region of Goshen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1448AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1448AY\"></sup> They acquired property there<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1448AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1448AZ\"></sup> and were fruitful and increased greatly in number.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1448BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1448BA\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jacob lived in Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1449BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1449BB\"></sup> seventeen years, and the years of his life were a hundred and forty-seven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1449BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1449BC\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When the time drew near for Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1450BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1450BD\"></sup> to die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1450BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1450BE\"></sup> he called for his son Joseph and said to him, “If I have found favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1450BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1450BF\"></sup> put your hand under my thigh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1450BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1450BG\"></sup> and promise that you will show me kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1450BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1450BH\"></sup> and faithfulness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1450BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1450BI\"></sup> Do not bury me in Egypt,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but when I rest with my fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1451BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1451BJ\"></sup> carry me out of Egypt and bury me where they are buried.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1451BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1451BK\"></sup>“I will do as you say,” he said.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Swear to me,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1452BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1452BL\"></sup> he said. Then Joseph swore to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1452BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1452BM\"></sup> and Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1452BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1452BN\"></sup> worshiped as he leaned on the top of his staff.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1452BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1452BO\"></sup>"
		},
		"48": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">48 </span>Some time later Joseph was told, “Your father is ill.” So he took his two sons Manasseh and Ephraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1453A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1453A\"></sup> along with him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Jacob was told, “Your son Joseph has come to you,” Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1454B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1454B\"></sup> rallied his strength and sat up on the bed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jacob said to Joseph, “God Almighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1455C\"></sup> appeared to me at Luz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1455D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1455D\"></sup> in the land of Canaan, and there he blessed me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1455E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1455E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and said to me, ‘I am going to make you fruitful and increase your numbers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1456F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1456F\"></sup> I will make you a community of peoples, and I will give this land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1456G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1456G\"></sup> as an everlasting possession to your descendants after you.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1456H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1456H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Now then, your two sons born to you in Egypt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1457I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1457I\"></sup> before I came to you here will be reckoned as mine; Ephraim and Manasseh will be mine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1457J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1457J\"></sup> just as Reuben<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1457K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1457K\"></sup> and Simeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1457L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1457L\"></sup> are mine.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Any children born to you after them will be yours; in the territory they inherit they will be reckoned under the names of their brothers.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As I was returning from Paddan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1459M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1459M\"></sup> to my sorrow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1459N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1459N\"></sup> Rachel died in the land of Canaan while we were still on the way, a little distance from Ephrath. So I buried her there beside the road to Ephrath” (that is, Bethlehem).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1459O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1459O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1460P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1460P\"></sup> saw the sons of Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1460Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1460Q\"></sup> he asked, “Who are these?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“They are the sons God has given me here,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1461R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1461R\"></sup> Joseph said to his father.Then Israel said, “Bring them to me so I may bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1461S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1461S\"></sup> them.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Israel’s eyes were failing because of old age, and he could hardly see.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1462T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1462T\"></sup> So Joseph brought his sons close to him, and his father kissed them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1462U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1462U\"></sup> and embraced them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1462V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1462V\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1463W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1463W\"></sup> said to Joseph, “I never expected to see your face again,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1463X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1463X\"></sup> and now God has allowed me to see your children too.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1463Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1463Y\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Joseph removed them from Israel’s knees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1464Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1464Z\"></sup> and bowed down with his face to the ground.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1464AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1464AA\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Joseph took both of them, Ephraim on his right toward Israel’s left hand and Manasseh on his left toward Israel’s right hand,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1465AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1465AB\"></sup> and brought them close to him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1466AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1466AC\"></sup> reached out his right hand and put it on Ephraim’s head,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1466AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1466AD\"></sup> though he was the younger,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1466AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1466AE\"></sup> and crossing his arms, he put his left hand on Manasseh’s head, even though Manasseh was the firstborn.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1466AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1466AF\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1467AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1467AG\"></sup> Joseph and said,“May the God before whom my fathersAbraham and Isaac walked faithfully,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1467AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1467AH\"></sup>the God who has been my shepherd<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1467AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1467AI\"></sup>all my life to this day,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the Angel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1468AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1468AJ\"></sup> who has delivered me from all harm<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1468AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1468AK\"></sup>—may he bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1468AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1468AL\"></sup> these boys.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1468AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1468AM\"></sup>May they be called by my nameand the names of my fathers Abraham and Isaac,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1468AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1468AN\"></sup>and may they increase greatlyon the earth.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1468AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1468AO\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Joseph saw his father placing his right hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1469AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1469AP\"></sup> on Ephraim’s head<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1469AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1469AQ\"></sup> he was displeased; so he took hold of his father’s hand to move it from Ephraim’s head to Manasseh’s head.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joseph said to him, “No, my father, this one is the firstborn; put your right hand on his head.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1470AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1470AR\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But his father refused and said, “I know, my son, I know. He too will become a people, and he too will become great.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1471AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1471AS\"></sup> Nevertheless, his younger brother will be greater than he,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1471AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1471AT\"></sup> and his descendants will become a group of nations.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1471AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1471AU\"></sup>”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1472AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1472AV\"></sup> them that day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1472AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1472AW\"></sup> and said,“In your name will Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1472AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1472AX\"></sup> pronounce this blessing:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1472AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1472AY\"></sup>‘May God make you like Ephraim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1472AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1472AZ\"></sup> and Manasseh.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1472BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1472BA\"></sup>’”So he put Ephraim ahead of Manasseh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Israel said to Joseph, “I am about to die, but God will be with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1473BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1473BB\"></sup> and take you back to the land of your fathers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1473BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1473BC\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And to you I give one more ridge of land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1474BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1474BD\"></sup> than to your brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1474BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1474BE\"></sup> the ridge I took from the Amorites with my sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1474BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1474BF\"></sup> and my bow.”"
		},
		"49": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">49 </span>Then Jacob called for his sons and said: “Gather around so I can tell you what will happen to you in days to come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1475B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1475B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Assemble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1476C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1476C\"></sup> and listen, sons of Jacob;listen to your father Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1476D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1476D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Reuben, you are my firstborn,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1477E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1477E\"></sup>my might, the first sign of my strength,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1477F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1477F\"></sup>excelling in honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1477G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1477G\"></sup> excelling in power.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Turbulent as the waters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1478H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1478H\"></sup> you will no longer excel,for you went up onto your father’s bed,onto my couch and defiled it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1478I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1478I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Simeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1479J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1479J\"></sup> and Levi<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1479K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1479K\"></sup> are brothers—their swords are weapons of violence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1479L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1479L\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Let me not enter their council,let me not join their assembly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1480M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1480M\"></sup>for they have killed men in their anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1480N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1480N\"></sup>and hamstrung<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1480O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1480O\"></sup> oxen as they pleased.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Cursed be their anger, so fierce,and their fury,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1481P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1481P\"></sup> so cruel!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1481Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1481Q\"></sup>I will scatter them in Jacoband disperse them in Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1481R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1481R\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1482S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1482S\"></sup> your brothers will praise you;your hand will be on the neck<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1482T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1482T\"></sup> of your enemies;your father’s sons will bow down to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1482U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1482U\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You are a lion’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1483V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1483V\"></sup> cub,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1483W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1483W\"></sup> Judah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1483X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1483X\"></sup>you return from the prey,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1483Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1483Y\"></sup> my son.Like a lion he crouches and lies down,like a lioness—who dares to rouse him?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The scepter will not depart from Judah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1484Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1484Z\"></sup>nor the ruler’s staff from between his feet,until he to whom it belongs shall come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1484AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1484AA\"></sup>and the obedience of the nations shall be his.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1484AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1484AB\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He will tether his donkey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1485AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1485AC\"></sup> to a vine,his colt to the choicest branch;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1485AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1485AD\"></sup>he will wash his garments in wine,his robes in the blood of grapes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1485AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1485AE\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>His eyes will be darker than wine,his teeth whiter than milk.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1486AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1486AF\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Zebulun<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1487AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1487AG\"></sup> will live by the seashoreand become a haven for ships;his border will extend toward Sidon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1487AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1487AH\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Issachar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1488AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1488AI\"></sup> is a rawboned donkeylying down among the sheep pens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1488AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1488AJ\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he sees how good is his resting placeand how pleasant is his land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1489AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1489AK\"></sup>he will bend his shoulder to the burden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1489AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1489AL\"></sup>and submit to forced labor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1489AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1489AM\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Dan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1490AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1490AN\"></sup> will provide justice for his peopleas one of the tribes of Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1490AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1490AO\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Dan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1491AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1491AP\"></sup> will be a snake by the roadside,a viper along the path,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1491AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1491AQ\"></sup>that bites the horse’s heels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1491AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1491AR\"></sup>so that its rider tumbles backward.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“I look for your deliverance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1492AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1492AS\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1492AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1492AT\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1493AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1493AU\"></sup> will be attacked by a band of raiders,but he will attack them at their heels.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1493AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1493AV\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Asher’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1494AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1494AW\"></sup> food will be rich;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1494AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1494AX\"></sup>he will provide delicacies fit for a king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1494AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1494AY\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Naphtali<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1495AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1495AZ\"></sup> is a doe set freethat bears beautiful fawns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1495BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1495BA\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Joseph<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1496BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1496BB\"></sup> is a fruitful vine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1496BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1496BC\"></sup>a fruitful vine near a spring,whose branches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1496BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1496BD\"></sup> climb over a wall.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>With bitterness archers attacked him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1497BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1497BE\"></sup>they shot at him with hostility.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1497BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1497BF\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But his bow remained steady,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1498BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1498BG\"></sup>his strong arms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1498BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1498BH\"></sup> stayed limber,because of the hand of the Mighty One of Jacob,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1498BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1498BI\"></sup>because of the Shepherd,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1498BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1498BJ\"></sup> the Rock of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1498BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1498BK\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>because of your father’s God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1499BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1499BL\"></sup> who helps<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1499BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1499BM\"></sup> you,because of the Almighty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1499BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1499BN\"></sup> who blesses youwith blessings of the skies above,blessings of the deep springs below,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1499BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1499BO\"></sup>blessings of the breast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1499BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1499BP\"></sup> and womb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1499BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1499BQ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Your father’s blessings are greaterthan the blessings of the ancient mountains,than the bounty of the age-old hills.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1500BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1500BR\"></sup>Let all these rest on the head of Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1500BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1500BS\"></sup>on the brow of the prince among his brothers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1500BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1500BT\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1501BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1501BU\"></sup> is a ravenous wolf;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1501BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1501BV\"></sup>in the morning he devours the prey,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1501BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1501BW\"></sup>in the evening he divides the plunder.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1501BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1501BX\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All these are the twelve tribes of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1502BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1502BY\"></sup> and this is what their father said to them when he blessed them, giving each the blessing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1502BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1502BZ\"></sup> appropriate to him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then he gave them these instructions:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1503CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1503CA\"></sup> “I am about to be gathered to my people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1503CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1503CB\"></sup> Bury me with my fathers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1503CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1503CC\"></sup> in the cave in the field of Ephron the Hittite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1503CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1503CD\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the cave in the field of Machpelah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1504CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1504CE\"></sup> near Mamre<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1504CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1504CF\"></sup> in Canaan, which Abraham bought along with the field<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1504CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1504CG\"></sup> as a burial place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1504CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1504CH\"></sup> from Ephron the Hittite.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>There Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1505CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1505CI\"></sup> and his wife Sarah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1505CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1505CJ\"></sup> were buried, there Isaac and his wife Rebekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1505CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1505CK\"></sup> were buried, and there I buried Leah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1505CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1505CL\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The field and the cave in it were bought from the Hittites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1506CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1506CM\"></sup>”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Jacob had finished giving instructions to his sons, he drew his feet up into the bed, breathed his last and was gathered to his people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1507CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1507CN\"></sup>"
		},
		"50": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">50 </span>Joseph threw himself on his father and wept over him and kissed him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1508A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1508A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Joseph directed the physicians in his service to embalm his father Israel. So the physicians embalmed him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1509B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1509B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>taking a full forty days, for that was the time required for embalming. And the Egyptians mourned for him seventy days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1510C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1510C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the days of mourning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1511D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1511D\"></sup> had passed, Joseph said to Pharaoh’s court,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1511E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1511E\"></sup> “If I have found favor in your eyes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1511F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1511F\"></sup> speak to Pharaoh for me. Tell him,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘My father made me swear an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1512G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1512G\"></sup> and said, “I am about to die;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1512H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1512H\"></sup> bury me in the tomb I dug for myself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1512I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1512I\"></sup> in the land of Canaan.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1512J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1512J\"></sup> Now let me go up and bury my father;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1512K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1512K\"></sup> then I will return.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Pharaoh said, “Go up and bury your father, as he made you swear to do.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joseph went up to bury his father. All Pharaoh’s officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1514L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1514L\"></sup> accompanied him—the dignitaries of his court<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1514M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1514M\"></sup> and all the dignitaries of Egypt—",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>besides all the members of Joseph’s household and his brothers and those belonging to his father’s household.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1515N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1515N\"></sup> Only their children and their flocks and herds were left in Goshen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1515O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1515O\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1516P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1516P\"></sup> and horsemen also went up with him. It was a very large company.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When they reached the threshing floor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1517Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1517Q\"></sup> of Atad, near the Jordan, they lamented loudly and bitterly;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1517R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1517R\"></sup> and there Joseph observed a seven-day period<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1517S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1517S\"></sup> of mourning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1517T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1517T\"></sup> for his father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1517U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1517U\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the Canaanites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1518V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1518V\"></sup> who lived there saw the mourning at the threshing floor of Atad, they said, “The Egyptians are holding a solemn ceremony of mourning.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1518W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1518W\"></sup> That is why that place near the Jordan is called Abel Mizraim.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Jacob’s sons did as he had commanded them:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1519X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1519X\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in the cave in the field of Machpelah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1520Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1520Y\"></sup> near Mamre,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1520Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1520Z\"></sup> which Abraham had bought along with the field<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1520AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1520AA\"></sup> as a burial place from Ephron the Hittite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1520AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1520AB\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After burying his father, Joseph returned to Egypt, together with his brothers and all the others who had gone with him to bury his father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1521AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1521AC\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Joseph’s brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, “What if Joseph holds a grudge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1522AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1522AD\"></sup> against us and pays us back for all the wrongs we did to him?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1522AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1522AE\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they sent word to Joseph, saying, “Your father left these instructions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1523AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1523AF\"></sup> before he died:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘This is what you are to say to Joseph: I ask you to forgive your brothers the sins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1524AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1524AG\"></sup> and the wrongs they committed in treating you so badly.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1524AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1524AH\"></sup> Now please forgive the sins of the servants of the God of your father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1524AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1524AI\"></sup>” When their message came to him, Joseph wept.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1524AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1524AJ\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>His brothers then came and threw themselves down before him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1525AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1525AK\"></sup> “We are your slaves,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1525AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1525AL\"></sup> they said.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Joseph said to them, “Don’t be afraid. Am I in the place of God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1526AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1526AM\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You intended to harm me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1527AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1527AN\"></sup> but God intended<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1527AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1527AO\"></sup> it for good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1527AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1527AP\"></sup> to accomplish what is now being done, the saving of many lives.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1527AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1527AQ\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So then, don’t be afraid. I will provide for you and your children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1528AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1528AR\"></sup>” And he reassured them and spoke kindly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1528AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1528AS\"></sup> to them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Joseph stayed in Egypt, along with all his father’s family. He lived a hundred and ten years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1529AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1529AT\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and saw the third generation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1530AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1530AU\"></sup> of Ephraim’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1530AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1530AV\"></sup> children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1530AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1530AW\"></sup> Also the children of Makir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1530AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1530AX\"></sup> son of Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1530AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1530AY\"></sup> were placed at birth on Joseph’s knees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1530AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1530AZ\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Joseph said to his brothers, “I am about to die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1531BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1531BA\"></sup> But God will surely come to your aid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1531BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1531BB\"></sup> and take you up out of this land to the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1531BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1531BC\"></sup> he promised on oath to Abraham,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1531BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1531BD\"></sup> Isaac<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1531BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1531BE\"></sup> and Jacob.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1531BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1531BF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Joseph made the Israelites swear an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1532BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1532BG\"></sup> and said, “God will surely come to your aid, and then you must carry my bones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1532BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1532BH\"></sup> up from this place.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1532BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1532BI\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So Joseph died<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1533BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1533BJ\"></sup> at the age of a hundred and ten.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1533BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1533BK\"></sup> And after they embalmed him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-1533BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-1533BL\"></sup> he was placed in a coffin in Egypt."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;